Franz Juschkat ( 12 February 1917 -- 3 December 1967 ) was an Oberfeldwebel in the German Wehrmacht during the Second World War who was awarded the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross and the rare Close Combat Clasp in gold , one of only 631 such awards .
4INFO is ranked 1742 on the 2015 Inc. 5000 as one of America 's fastest - growing private companies .
Philip Ledger was appointed Commander of the Order of the British Empire in the 1985 New Year Honours , and knighted in the Queen 's Birthday Honours in 1999 for services to music .
Geneviève Brisac ( born 18 October 1951 in Paris ) is a French writer and winner of the Prix Femina , 1996 , for Week - end de chasse à la mère , a novel translated in English as Losing Eugenio ( 2000 ) and referred to in The New York Times as a `` mildly compelling text . ''
Inga Saffron ( born November 9 , 1957 ) is an American journalist who won the 2014 Pulitzer Prize for Criticism while writing for the Philadelphia Inquirer .
Friedrich - Georg Eberhardt ( 15 January 1892 -- 9 September 1964 ) was a Generalleutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II . He was a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Dorothy Ruth Hoogstraten ( February 28 , 1960 -- August 14 , 1980 ) , who took the stage name Dorothy Stratten , was a Canadian Playboy Playmate , model , and actress .
Franz - Josef Högl ( 21 October 1916 -- 29 November 1996 ) was a highly decorated Oberstleutnant in the German Wehrmacht during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Franz Graßmel ( 8 January 1906 -- 30 June 1985 ) , was a highly decorated German Fallschirmjäger ( paratrooper ) during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub ) .
Espen Lie ( born January 3 , 1984 ) is a Norwegian chess player who currently holds the title of International Master , and was the Norwegian Chess Champion for 2007 .
Patrick Thomas Leonard ( 1828 -- March 1 , 1905 ) was a United States Army sergeant who received the Medal of Honor during the Indian Wars .
Lieutenant Colonel John Manners Smith VC CIE CVO ( 30 August 1864 -- 6 January 1920 ) was a recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Klaus Bischoff ( born 9 June 1961 in Ulm ) is a German chess player who was awarded the Grandmaster title by FIDE in 1990 .
Maria Kouvatsou ( Greek : Μαρία Κουβάτσου ; born November 2 , 1979 in Athens , Greece ) is a Greek chess Woman Grandmaster ( WGM ) .
Jean - Mathieu - Philibert Sérurier , 1st Comte Sérurier ( 8 December 1742 -- 21 December 1819 ) led a division in the War of the First Coalition and became a Marshal of France under Emperor Napoleon .
Rani Hamid ( Bengali : রাণী হামিদ ; born 1944 ) is a Bangladeshi chess Woman International Master .
Azer Mirzoev ( Azerbaijani : Azər Mirzəyev ) , ( born 20 March 1978 ) is an Azerbaijani chess Grandmaster ( 2001 ) .
Davit G. Petrosian ( born September 20 , 1984 ) is an Armenian chess Grandmaster ( 2009 ) .

Joseph Van Matre ( October 9 , 1828 -- January 14 , 1892 ) was a United States Army soldier who received the Medal of Honor for his actions during the American Civil War .
Antoni Dunin ( 1907 - -1939 ) was a Polish nobleman ( szlachta ) , a Hrabia ( Count ) , and an army officer who received the Virtuti Militari award .
Charles Hull VC ( 24 July 1890 -- 21 February 1953 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces during the First World War .

Major General Francis Arthur Sutton M.C. ( born England 14 February 1884 , died Hong Kong 22 October 1944 ) was an English adventurer known as `` One Arm Sutton '' after losing part of an arm by a hand grenade at the Battle of Gallipoli where he was awarded the Military Cross .

Rajesh Kotecha ( born 18 July 1963 ) is an Indian Ayurveda physician who received a Padma Shri Award for Medicine in 2015 .
Henry A. McMasters ( 1848 -- November 11 , 1872 ) was a United States Army Corporal during the Indian Wars who received the Medal of Honor on November 19 , 1872 , for service at Red River , Texas on September 29 , 1872 .
Emil von Behring ( Emil Adolf von Behring ) , as Emil Adolf Behring born ( 15 March 1854 -- 31 March 1917 ) was a German physiologist who received the 1901 Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine , the first one awarded , for his discovery of a diphtheria antitoxin .

Alfred Saalwächter ( 10 January 1883 -- 6 December 1945 ) was a German U - boat commander during World War I and General Admiral during World War II .

Paul A. Hodgson ( November 19 , 1891 - October 7 , 1955 ) was a West Point graduate who served in World War I and World War II . While at West Point , he roomed with the future President of the United States , Dwight D. Eisenhower .
Duke Charles of Mecklenburg ( German : Herzog Carl zu Mecklenburg ) ( 30 November 1785 -- 21 September 1837 ) was a member of the House of Mecklenburg - Strelitz and a Prussian soldier who served in the Napoleonic Wars .

Georg Dörffel ( 27 July 1914 -- 26 May 1944 ) was a highly decorated Oberstleutnant in the Luftwaffe during World War II , and one of only 882 recipients of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves ( Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub ) .
John FitzAlan , 14th Earl of Arundel , 4th Baron Maltravers KG ( 14 February 1408 -- 12 June 1435 ) was an English nobleman and military commander during the later phases of the Hundred Years ' War .

Williams Carter Wickham ( September 21 , 1820 -- July 23 , 1888 ) was a lawyer , judge , politician , and an important Confederate cavalry general who fought in the Virginia campaigns during the American Civil War .
Charlotte Stanley , Countess of Derby ( 1599 - -1664 ) , born Charlotte de La Trémoille , is famous for her robust defence of Lathom House during the English Civil War .
Charles Huntziger ( 25 June 1880 -- 11 November 1941 ) was a French Army general during World War I and World War II . Born at Lesneven ( Finistère ) , he graduated from Saint - Cyr in 1900 and joined the colonial infantry .
Werner Winter ( 26 March 1912 -- 9 September 1972 ) was a German U - boat commander in World War II and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .

NGC 6756 is a small open star cluster in the constellation Aquila , close to NGC 6755 .
Mu Geminorum ( μ Gem , μ Geminorum ) is the Bayer designation for a star in the northern constellation of Gemini .
R Aquarii ( R Aqr ) is a variable star in the constellation Aquarius .
BO Microscopii ( BO Mic ) is a star in the constellation Microscopium located about 170 light years from the Sun . It has been dubbed `` Speedy Mic '' because of the ultra - rapid rotation rate .
139 Tauri ( 139 Tau ) is a blue supergiant star in the constellation Taurus .
11 Cancri ( 11 Cnc ) is a star in the constellation Cancer .

Eta Scuti ( η Sct , η Scuti ) is a star in the constellation Scutum .

Lake Vostok ( Russian : Озеро Восток , Ozero Vostok , lit . `` Lake East '' ) is the largest of Antarctica 's almost 400 known subglacial lakes .
The Rouen Mountains ( 69 ° 10′S 70 ° 53′W ) are a prominent mountain range , reaching to about 2,800 m and extending 35 miles ( 60 km ) NW - SE from Mount Bayonne to Care Heights and Mount Cupola , in north Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Framryggen Ridge ( 72 ° 30′S 3 ° 54′W ) is a small rock ridge about 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) west of Borg Mountain in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
The Ljubljanica has become a popular attraction in Europe for treasure hunters .
Jaques Nunatak ( 67 ° 53′S 66 ° 12′E ) is a small nunatak lying 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) south - southwest of Mount Kennedy in the Gustav Bull Mountains of Mac . Robertson Land , Antarctica .
Farmer Glacier ( 81 ° 47′S 159 ° 48′E ) is a glacier flowing north west into Starshot Glacier , and located between Mount McKerrow to the north and Thompson Mountain to the south , at the southern end of the Surveyors Range in Antarctica .
McCarthy Valley ( 85 ° 18′S 119 ° 20′W ) is an ice - filled valley , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) long , between Peters Butte and Todd Ridge in the northwest part of the Long Hills , Horlick Mountains , Antarctica .
The Geode Nunataks ( 69 ° 50′S 70 ° 5′W ) are a group of small nunataks on the west side of Sibelius Glacier , immediately north of the northern extremity of the Finlandia Foothills , in northeast Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Caughley Beach is the northernmost beach on the ice - free coast south - west of Cape Bird , Ross Island , Antarctica .
Mount Goodale ( 85 ° 45′S 157 ° 43′W ) is a mountain with double summits , 2,420 and 2,570 metres ( 7,940 and 8,430 ft ) high , standing 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) southeast of Mount Thorne in the Hays Mountains of the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
Danao - Danao Island ( variously Danao Danao island , Danao Island , Dunad Island Dunao Island or Dunao Islet ) is a small , low - lying island in northeastern Iloilo , Philippines .
The Schottenstift ( English : Scottish Abbey ) , formally called Benediktinerabtei unserer Lieben Frau zu den Schotten ( English : Benedictine Abbey of Our Dear Lady of the Scots ) , is a Roman Catholic monastery founded in Vienna in 1155 when Henry II of Austria brought Irish monks to Vienna .
Rahimiabad ( Persian : رحيمي آباد‎ , also Romanized as Raḩīmīābād ) is a village in Kahir Rural District , in the Central District of Konarak County , Sistan and Baluchestan Province , Iran .

Santa Bernardina is a suburb of Durazno , the capital city of Durazno Department , in central Uruguay .

Oliver Guy - Watkins ( born 6 October 1979 ) is a British film director , writer and artist .
Paul Sikes ( born in Nashville , Tennessee in 1982 ) is an American singer - songwriter and music producer who has released his debut album Craft : by Paul Sikes on 10 July 2012 .
Norman Macgeorge ( 8 July 1872 -- 2 September 1952 ) was an artist and art critic in the colony and State of Victoria .
Herbert Kenneth Airy Shaw ( 7 April 1902 - -1985 ) was a notable English botanist and classicist .
Mathieu d'Escouchy ( Le Quesnoy , Nord , 1420 -- 1482 ) was a Picard chronicler during the last stages of the Hundred Years War .
Ferdinand Carl Valentin Haecker ( 15 September 1864 -- 19 December 1927 ) was a German zoologist , reader at Freiburg University from 1892 .
John Denne D.D. ( 1693 - -1767 ) was an English churchman and antiquarian , Archdeacon of Rochester from 1728 .
`` Woody '' Vernon Crompton Woodward DFC and Bar RAF ( 22 December 1916 -- 26 May 2000 ) was a Canadian who flew for the RAF as a fighter pilot during WWII .
Bill Unwin ( 25 November 1915 -- 16 June 1999 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ferde Grofé ( 27 March 1892 -- 3 April 1972 ) was an American composer , arranger and pianist .
John Okill ( c.1687 -- August 20 , 1773 ) was a pioneering and successful 18th century shipbuilder from Liverpool , England .
Lu Dadong ( Chinese : 鲁大东 ; 1915 -- 28 August 1998 ) was a communist revolutionary and politician of the People 's Republic of China .
Bertha of Savoy ( 21 September 1051 -- 27 December 1087 ) , also called Bertha of Turin , a member of the Burgundian House of Savoy , was Queen consort of Germany from 1066 and Empress consort of the Holy Roman Empire from 1084 until 1087 as the first wife of the Salian emperor Henry IV .
Ella Némethy ( 5 April 1895 in Sátoraljaújhely -- 14 June 1961 in Budapest ) was a Hungarian mezzo - soprano who had an active international career in operas and concerts from 1919 - 1948 .
Lewis Grassic Gibbon was the pseudonym of James Leslie Mitchell ( 13 February 1901 -- 7 February 1935 ) , a Scottish writer .
Charles Cavendish , Viscount Mansfield ( c. 1626 - -1659 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1644 .
Reverend Robert William Eyton ( 1815 - -1881 ) was an English Church of England clergyman who was author of The Antiquities of Shropshire .
Moshe Rynecki ( 1881 - -1943 ) was a Polish artist of Jewish origins .
Maximos of Gallipoli ( Greek : Μάξιμος Καλλιπολίτης ; Latin : Maximus Callipolites ; died 1633 ) was a hieromonk who made the first translation of the New Testament into modern Greek after 1629 .
Ellen Einan ( 15 June 1931 -- 25 March 2013 ) was a Norwegian poet and illustrator .
Isabella Gilmore ( née Morris ; 1842 - -1923 ) was an English churchwoman who oversaw the revival of the Deaconess Order in the Anglican Communion .
On 27 October 1965 , Ferdinand Sigg died unexpectedly in office .
Sir James Falshaw , 1st Baronet JP , DL , FRSE ( 21 March 1810 -- 14 June 1889 ) , was a British railway engineer and politician .
Palle Lykke Jensen ( 4 November 1936 -- 19 April 2013 ) was a Danish cyclist who was active between 1956 and 1969 .
Ernest Cadman Colwell ( 19 January 1901 -- 24 September 1974 ) was an American biblical scholar , textual critic and palaeographer .
Sir Edward Waterhouse ( 1535 - -1591 ) was an English - born Chancellor of the Exchequer of Ireland from 1586 to 1589 .
Laurens Bake or Baak , Baeck ( 1629 , Amsterdam -- buried 18 December 1702 , Amsterdam ) was a Dutch poet of the seventeenth century .
Datuk Robert Lau Hoi Chew ( simplified Chinese : 刘会洲 ; traditional Chinese : 劉會洲 ; pinyin : Liú Huì Zhōu ; 15 September 1942 -- 9 April 2010 ) was a Malaysian politician .
Roderick Macleod , 2nd of Cadboll ( died 1770 ) was a Scottish laird who supported the Jacobite cause and fought for Bonnie Prince Charlie in The ' Forty - Five ' .
Walter Pope ( c. 1627 -- 1714 ) was an English astronomer and poet .
William Birdlip ( fl . 1402 - 1417 ) of Gloucester , was an English politician .
Leoncio Prado Gutiérrez ( 25 August 1853 -- 15 July 1883 ) was a Peruvian mariner .
Abdullah Cevdet ( Ottoman Turkish : عبدالله جودت‎‎ ; 9 September 1869 -- 29 November 1932 ) was an Ottoman Kurdish intellectual and medical doctor .
Francesco Nullo ( 1 March 1826 -- 5 May 1863 ) was an Italian patriot , military officer and merchant , and a close friend and confidant of Giuseppe Garibaldi .
John George Burnett , OBE ( 1876 - -1962 ) was Unionist Party ( Scotland ) MP for Aberdeen North from 1931 to 1935 , defeating William Wedgwood Benn in the 1931 election .
Joachim Gutkeled ( died in April 1277 ) was an influential lord in the Kingdom of Hungary .
Íñigo López ( floruit 1040 - -1076 ; dead by 1079 ? ) was the first Lord of Biscay .
John de Critz or John Decritz ( 1551/2 -- 14 March 1642 ( buried ) ) was one of a number of painters of Flemish and Dutch origin active at the English royal court during the reigns of James I of England and Charles I of England .
Walter Butterfield ( 6 August 1870 -- 19 July 1954 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Derbyshire in 1896 .
Salil Chowdhury ( Bengali : সলিল চৌধুরী ; ' Sholil Choudhuri ' in phonetic Wiki - Bengali ; 19 November 1923 -- 5 September 1995 ) was an Indian music composer , who mainly composed for Bengali , Hindi and Malayalam films .
Horace See ( 1835 - 1909 ) was an American mechanical engineer , inventor , and superintendent , known as President of the American Society of Mechanical Engineers in the year 1888 - 89 .
Émile Grémaux ( 1893 - 18 September 1959 in Lille ) - boxer , coach and businessman .
Marcos Maturana del Campo ( c. 1802 - -August 29 , 1871 ) was a Chilean military and political figure who served in the Chilean War of Independence and the War of the Confederation .
Kate Williams ( 1875 -- 1946 ) , sometimes called Kate Roberts , better known by her stage name Vulcana , was a Welsh strongwoman born of Irish parents in Abergavenny , Monmouthshire .
Joseph Haslewood ( 5 November 1769 -- 21 September 1833 ) , was an English writer and antiquary .
Marguerite Bériza ( 1880 -- 1970 ) was a French opera singer who had an active international career during the first half of the 20th century .
Octavio Ianni ( 1926 in Itu , São Paulo -- 2004 in São Paulo , São Paulo ) , Brazilian sociologist graduated , mastered and doctored at the University of São Paulo ( USP ) and was one of the founders of Cebrap .
Elizabeth von Arnim ( 31 August 1866 -- 9 February 1941 ) , born Mary Annette Beauchamp , was an Australian - born British novelist .
George Brisbane Scott Douglas ( 1856 - -1935 ) was a Scottish poet and writer , as well as a Baronet .
Matthew Caffyn ( christened 26 October 1628 -- buried June 1714 ) was a British General Baptist preacher and writer .
Robert Bruce Inverarity ( 1909 - -1999 ) was an American artist , art educator , museum director , author , and anthropologist .
General Gore Browne ( c.1764 - 12 January 1843 ) was a British Army officer who became Lieutenant - Governor of Plymouth .
Teddy Petersen ( 21 November 1892 - 15 April 1991 ) was a Danish bandleader and violinist .
Du Xunhe ( traditional Chinese : 杜荀鶴 ; simplified Chinese : 杜荀鹤 ; pinyin : Dù Xúnhè ; 846 - 904 ) was a Chinese poet of the late Tang dynasty , with one of his poems being included in the anthology Three Hundred Tang Poems .
Simon François Bernard ( 28 January 1817 -- 25 November 1862 ) was a French surgeon and republican revolutionary .
Henry Sass ( 24 April 1788 -- 1844 ) was an English artist and teacher of painting , who founded an important art school , Sass 's Academy ( later `` Cary 's Academy '' ) , in London , to provide training for those seeking to enter the Royal Academy .
Nikola Kavaja ( Serbian Cyrillic : Никола Каваја ; 3 October 1932 -- 10 November 2008 ) , nicknamed Tito 's hunter , was a Serbian nationalist and anti - communist known for his 1979 bombing of a Yugoslav consul 's home and the hijacking of American Airlines Flight 293 .
Sergo Kobuladze ( Georgian : სერგო ქობულაძე ; 1909 - -1978 ) was a Georgian painter and illustrator .
On 24 June 2012 , at 8:00 am local time , Edwin Naula , Director of the Galápagos National Park , announced that Lonesome George had been found dead by his caretaker of 40 years , Fausto Llerena .
Sir Alexander Frederick Whyte KCSI ( 1883 - -1970 ) was a British civil servant , Liberal Party politician , writer , and journalist .
Steve Fairnie ( 1951 - -1993 ) was a British musician , artist and actor , the frontman of the post - punk band Writz , and as one half - with his wife Bev Sage - of the 1980s pop outfit Techno Twins ( later just The Technos ) .
Elizabeth Sprague Coolidge aka Liz Coolidge ( 30 October 1864 -- 4 November 1953 ) , born Elizabeth Penn Sprague , was an American pianist and patron of music , especially of chamber music .
Aurora Castillo ( 1914 - -1998 ) was a Mexican - American environmentalist from Los Angeles , California .
Prince Chiêu Văn Trần Nhật Duật ( 1255 - -1330 ) was the sixth prince of Trần Thái Tông , first emperor of Trần Dynasty .
Uriel Nespoli ( January 15 , 1884 -- June 1973 ) was an Italian conductor born in Naples .
William Gwenlyn Parry ( 1932 -- 5 November 1991 ) was a Welsh dramatist .
Julius Rudel ( 6 March 1921 -- 26 June 2014 ) was an American opera and orchestra conductor .
Pop Wea , also known as Lori Tanner ( died 1966 ) , was a Native American artist associated with the Taos Pueblo .
Stanisław Szukalski ( 13 December 1893 -- 19 May 1987 ) was a Polish - born painter and sculptor who became a part of the Chicago Renaissance .
Samuli Mansikka ( 28 July 1978 -- 24 March 2015 ) , was a Finnish mountaineer , trekking guide and expedition leader .
Demeter de Mézes ( Hungarian : Mézesi Demeter ) ( d. 1372 ) was the bishop of Nagyvárad ( Oradea ) between 1345 and 1372 .
Paul Parquet ( 1856 - -1916 ) was a French perfumer and joint owner of Houbigant .
Johann Heinrich Bisterfeld ( 1605 -- 16 February 1655 ) was a German philosopher , logician and encyclopedic writer from Siegen .
Major General Toru Okabe ( 1889 - -1961 ) was a senior officer in the Imperial Japanese Army during World War II . He was born in 1889 .
Brigadier General Marshall Magruder ( 12 October 1885 -- 4 July 1956 ) Father of Peyton M. Magruder was born in Washington , D. C. He served in both World War I and World War II . He retired from the US Army in 1946 as a Brigadier General .
Wong Chin Foo ( Chinese : 王清福 ; pinyin : Wáng Qīngfú ; 1847 - 1898 ) was a Chinese - American activist , journalist , lecturer , and one of the most prolific Chinese writers in the San Francisco press of the 19th century .
Jørgen Buckhøj ( 10 January 1935 -- 13 April 1994 ) was a Danish actor , working on stage , TV and film .
Hansken ( 1630 -- Florence , 9 November 1655 ) was a female elephant that became famous in early 17th - century Europe .
Henry Albin ( 20 June 1624 -- 5 September 1696 ) was an English minister , ejected for nonconformity .
Arthur Frederick Ostrander , Sr . ( February 14 , 1895 - February 1978 ) , was an assistant scientist .
Roger Marston ( Rogerus de Marston ) ( died c. 1303 ) was an English Franciscan scholastic philosopher and theologian .
Michelino , stage name of Michele Gramazio ( 1937 -- 27 December 2010 ) was an Italian singer .
Honoré Savy ( 1725 - 1790 ) was the founder of a factory that manufactured Faïence wares in Marseille , France between 1749 and 1790 .
Esther Rahim ( 25 June 1904 - 31 March 1963 ) , also known as Esmet Rahim , was a significant Pakistani painter .
Matthias Ulungura ( 1921 - -1980 ) ( in some sources also referred to as Matthias Ngapiatulawai ) was an Indigenous Australian from the Tiwi Islands , who in 1942 became the first Australian to take a Japanese prisoner of war on Australian soil .
Samuel Stretton ( 1731 --11 May 1811 ) was a builder and architect in Nottingham who is noted for building the first powered cotton mill .
Levi Yitzchak Schneerson , ( 1878 - 1944 ) , was a Chabad - Lubavitch Hasidic rabbi in Yekatrinoslav , Ukraine .
Georges Johin ( 31 July 1877 -- 6 December 1955 ) was a French croquet player and Olympic champion .
Thomas William Baxter Aveling ( 11 May 1815 -- 3 July 1884 ) , was an independent congregational minister , born at Castletown in the Isle of Man , the son of a soldier and an Irish mother .
Saint Marcellus of Tangier or Saint Marcellus the Centurion ( Spanish : San Marcelo ) ( c. mid 3rd century -- 298 AD ) is venerated as a Martyr Saint by the Catholic Church and the Eastern Orthodox Church .
Ibrahim Tannous ( 1929 - 26 December 2012 ) was a former commander of the Lebanese Armed Forces .
Kazimierz Chodziński ( Casimir ) ( 1861 -- 1919 or 1921 ) was a Polish sculptor , and a student of Jan Matejko .
Eugène - Louis Lequesne ( or Le Quesne ) ( 15 February 1815 -- 3 June 1887 ) was a French sculptor .
Sir John Chalers or Deschalers ( 1361 - 1388 ) , of Whaddon , Cambridgeshire and Wyddial , Hertfordshire , was an English politician .

John Bryans ( died 2 March 1989 ) was a British actor , who appeared frequently on television .
Lorenzo Masi , known as Lorenzo da Firenze ( Magister Laurentius de Florentia ) ( d. December 1372 or January 1373 ) , was an Italian composer and music teacher of the Trecento .
Hector Neil McLarty ( 15 March 1851 -- 24 November 1912 ) was a Western Australian Police officer , and customs detective .
Dr Richard Baylie ( 1585 -- 27 July 1667 ) was twice President of St John 's College , Oxford , twice Vice - Chancellor of Oxford University and Dean of Salisbury .
James Phinney Munroe ( b. 1862 d. 1929 ) was an American author , businessman , professor and genealogist of the Clan Munro .
Marjorie Wintermute ( 1919 - -2007 ) was an American architect in Oregon .
Henry Travers ( 5 March 1874 -- 18 October 1965 ) was an English film and stage character actor .

Sydney Goodsir Smith ( 26 October 1915 -- 15 January 1975 ) was a Scottish poet , artist , dramatist and novelist .
John Murray , 11th Duke of Atholl ( 19 January 1929 -- 15 May 2012 ) was a South African - born hereditary peer of the Peerage of Scotland , hereditary Clan Chief of Clan Murray , and Colonel - in - Chief of the Atholl Highlanders .
Thomas Docwra ( 1458 ? -- 1527 ) was Grand Prior of the English Knights Hospitaller .
Dr Meirion Pennar ( 24 December 1944 -- 9 December 2010 ) was a Welsh poet and academic , who translated two works of Welsh language literature .
Zamir Niazi ( 1932 - -2004 ) was a Pakistani journalist , known for his commitment to freedom of the press .
Shripad Raghunath Joshi ( Marathi : श्रीपाद रघुनाथ जोशी ) ( 1920 -- 2002 ) was a Marathi author from Maharashtra , India .
Mustafa Krantja ( 10 April 1921 - 4 January 2002 ) was an Albanian classical music conductor and composer .
Richard of York , 3rd Duke of York KG ( 21 September 1411 -- 30 December 1460 ) , was a leading English magnate , a great - grandson of King Edward III through his father , and a great - great - great - grandson of the same king through his mother .
Colonel Sir Henry George Lyons FRS ( 11 October 1864 -- 1944 ) was a geologist and director of the Science Museum in London .
Durga Charan Banerjee ( 1898 - 1952 ) was a Bengali speaking Indian jurist and a member of parliament of the first Lok Sabha .
Indumadhab Mallick ( Bengali : ইন্দুমাধব মল্লিক ; 4 December 1869 -- 8 May 1917 ) was an Indian polymath who invented the Icmic cooker and made it commercial success .
Bernice Cross ( 1912 - 1996 ) was an American artist and art instructor born in Iowa City , Iowa , who was based in Washington , D.C. for most of her professional career .

Sir Alexander Seton , 1st Viscount of Kingston ( 13 March 1620 -- 21 October 1691 ) , a Cavalier , was the first dignity Charles II conferred as King .
Harald Leupold - Löwenthal ( 6 August 1926 -- 13 March 2007 ) was an Austrian neurologist and psychoanalyst known for his involvement in the establishment in 1971 of the Sigmund Freud Museum and in its further development .

James Marley ( 6 May 1893 -- 11 April 1954 ) was a schoolmaster and a Labour politician who sat in the House of Commons between December 1923 and October 1924 and , again , between May 1929 and October 1931 .
Maurice Kyle ( 8 November 1937 -- 1981 ) was a former English footballer who played for Oxford United , Southend United , Worcester City and Bath City .
Billie West ( 5 August 1891 -- 7 June 1967 ) , was an American actress of the silent era .
John Feltham ( fl . 1780 - -1813 ) was an English writer , particularly for travel and antiquarian works .
Sir David Scott Fox KCMG ( 20 June 1910 -- 25 January 1985 ) was a British diplomat and writer .
Dimitra Tserkezou ( 1920 -- 2007 ) was a famous Greek sculptress .
Chief Kepuha ( died February 2 , 1669 ) , also spelled Kipuhá or Quipuha , was the island of Guam 's first Catholic chief .
Maria Piłsudska , née Koplewska ( 1865 -- 17 August 1921 ) , was the first wife of Poland 's Marshal Józef Piłsudski and ostensibly the first lady of Poland during most of his service as Poland 's Chief of State .
Sittişah Hatun , ( c. 1435 -- April 1467 ) , was the third wife of Ottoman Sultan Mehmed II and the real - biological mother of Ottoman Sultan Bayezid II . She was one of the daughters of Zülkadiroğlu Süleyman Bey , the sixth ruler of Dulkadir State .
Mirza Ali Khan ( Urdu / Pashto : مرزا علی خان ; born 1897 , died 1960 ) , known as the Faqir of Ipi , was a Pashtun from today 's North - Waziristan Pakistan , Federally Administrated Tribal Areas .
Robert Sholto Johnstone Douglas ( 3 December 1871 -- 10 March 1958 ) , known as Sholto Douglas , or more formally as Sholto Johnstone Douglas , was a Scottish figurative artist , a painter chiefly of portraits and landscapes .

William Byron , 5th Baron Byron ( 5 November 1722 -- 19 May 1798 ) , also known as `` the Wicked Lord '' and `` the Devil Byron '' , was the poet George Gordon Byron 's great uncle .

Christopher Dillon Bellew , Irish catholic gentleman and activist , 1763 - -1826 .
Giovanna d'Aragona , Duchess of Amalfi ( 1478 - -1510 ) was an Italian aristocrat whose tragic life inspired several works of literature , most notably John Webster 's play , The Duchess of Malfi .

William Gordon Lennox ( 1884 - -1960 ) was an American neurologist who was a pioneer in the use of electroencephalography ( EEG ) for the diagnosis and treatment of epilepsy .

Christopher Cartwright ( 1602 - -1658 ) was an English clergyman , known as a Hebraist and for his use of targums in Biblical exegesis , following the lead of Henry Ainsworth with John Weemes .
Bernhard Helander ( born 1958 , death 2001 ) was an anthropologist and well known Scholar on Somalia .
Barry Reckord ( 19 November 1926 -- 20 December 2011 ) was a Jamaican playwright , one of the earliest Caribbean writers to make a contribution to theatre in Britain .
Kaarlo Linkola ( born Collan ) ( 1888 - -1942 ) was a Finnish botanist and phytogeographer .
Arthur Nigel Davenport ( 23 May 1928 -- 25 October 2013 ) was an English stage , television and film actor .
Susan Edmonstone Ferrier ( 7 September 1782 -- 5 November 1854 ) was a Scottish novelist .
Sidrach Simpson ( c.1600 - 1655 ) was an English Independent minister , one of the leaders of the Independent faction in the Westminster Assembly .
Cyril Bavin ( 1878 -- 20 February 1956 ) was a New Zealand - born Australian Methodist minister and missionary to Fiji who became General Secretary to the YMCA Migration Department and Honorary Secretary of the Migration Bureau of the Overseas League based in London .
Amdo Jampa ( born 1911 in Chentsa , Amdo , Tibet , died 28 March 2002 , Lhasa , Tibet Autonomous Region , China ) , also known as Jampa Tseten , was a Tibetan painter .
Alexandre Berthier ( 1638 - -1708 ) was a captain in the French army who was born Isaac Berthier and a Huguenot ; became known as Alexandre after his arrival in New France in 1665 .
Georg Sigurd Wettenhovi - Aspa ( born . Wetterhoff - Asp , 7 May 1870 , Helsinki -- 18 February 1946 ) was a Finnish artist and amateur egyptologist .
Tamilvanan ( Tamil : தமிழ்வாணன் ) ( 1921 - -1977 ) was a Tamil language author and publisher based in Chennai .
John Leycester Adolphus ( 1795 - -1862 ) was an English lawyer , jurist and author .
Al - Mu'ayyad Abbas ( died 1880 ) was an Imam of Yemen who ruled briefly in 1850 .
Klausjürgen Wussow ( 30 April 1929 -- 19 June 2007 ) was a German theatre- and television actor .
Mikko Mutenia ( 3 February 1980 -- 21 June 2015 ) , better known by his stage name Ezkimo , was a Finnish hip hop musician .
Veit Dietrich , also Vitus Theodorus or Vitus Diterichus , ( 8 December 1506 -- 25 March 1549 ) was a German theologian , writer and reformer .
Charles Norman Greenfield ( 4 April 1907 -- 17 September 1997 ) was a fireman with the Manchester City Fire Brigade who precipitated a significant legal case in British trade union history , particularly regarding the Fire Brigades Union ( FBU ) .
Togodumnus ( d. AD 43 ) was a historical king of the British Catuvellauni tribe at the time of the Roman conquest .
Guo Si ( died 197 ) , also known as Guo Duo ( 郭多 ) , was a general serving under the warlord Dong Zhuo during the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Meenakshi Sundaram Pillai , who left behind him a treasure of Tamil palm leaf manuscripts , died in poverty in 1876 .

Huangfu Song ( died 195 ) , courtesy name Yizhen ( 義真 ) , was a military general of the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Maxwell Henry Close ( 1822 -- 12 September 1903 ) was an Irish Church of Ireland clergyman and geologist who also contributed to the preservation of the Irish language .
Geo Omori ( died 1938 ) was a Japanese - born Brazilian martial artist , and one of the creators of judo - based martial arts in Brazil .
Aster Ganno ( c.1872 - -1964 ) was an Ethiopian Bible translator who worked with the better known Onesimos Nesib as a translator of the Oromo Bible , published in 1899 .
Gaston Aime Camille Fontanille ( 11 May 1883 - 1923 ) , also known just as Delandre , was a French entrepreneur and conman born in Valence , the son of a Magistrate .

Patrick Leslie , 1st Lord Lindores ( died between 22 May and 5 October 1608 ) was a member of the Scottish nobility .
Harry Wheatcroft ( 1898 - -1977 ) was a famous English rose grower .
Lee Lawrence ( born Leon Siroto , 1920 -- 26 February 1961 ) was a British singer who was popular in the 1950s .
Jani Lehtonen ( 11 August 1968 in Mäntsälä -- 22 December 2008 in Tampere ) was a Finnish pole vaulter .
Sergio Endrigo ( 15 June 1933 -- 7 September 2005 ) was an Italian singer - songwriter .
Muelle was a trademark signature and design by Juan Carlos Argüello , Spanish graffiti pioneer ( circa 1966 - -1995 ) .
Jacob Johann Hagenbach ( 1802 ? in Basle -- 1 January 1825 ) was a Swiss entomologist .
Alfred Harley , 6th Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer ( 10 January 1809 - 19 January 1853 ) , styled Lord Harley between 1828 and 1849 , was a British peer and the last holder of the title of Earl of Oxford and Mortimer .
Burnum Burnum ( 10 January 1936 -- 18 August 1997 ) was an Australian Aboriginal activist , actor , and author .
Charles Wolfran Cornwall ( 15 June 1735 -- 2 January 1789 ) was a British politician who became Speaker of the House of Commons .
Elsa Granger ( died 8 February 1955 ) was an Australian actress who studied acting with P.J. Ramster and appeared in several of his films .
Giuseppe Appiani ( 1740 - -1812 ) was an Italian painter of the Neoclassic periods .
Johan Schatter ( 4 October 1594 -- 28 June 1673 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age brewer and mayor of Haarlem .
Major Robert Stobo ( 1727 - -1770 ) was an 18th - century Scottish - born colonial American frontiersman and soldier .
Thomas Rudyard ( 1640 -- buried 2 November 1692 ) was a deputy governor of East Jersey .
Robert of Rhuddlan ( died 3 July 1093 ) was a Norman adventurer who became lord of much of north - east Wales and for a period lord of all North Wales .
Dr. Alfonso Elder ( February 26 , 1898 -- August 1974 ) was the second president of North Carolina Central University .
Amza Pellea ( Romanian pronunciation : ( ˈamza ˈpele̯a ) ; 7 April 1931 -- 12 December 1983 ) was a Romanian actor noted for playing Romanian national heroes on film .
Rudolf Moralt ( 26 February 1902 -- 16 December 1958 ) was a German conductor , particularly associated with Mozart and the German repertory .
Shi Lang ( Chinese : 施琅 ; pinyin : Shī Láng ; 1621 - -1696 ) was a Chinese admiral who served under the Ming and Qing dynasties in the 17th century .
Patsy Smart ( died 6 February 1996 ) was an English actress who is best remembered for her performance as Miss Roberts in the 1970s ITV television drama Upstairs , Downstairs .
Norman Lawson ( died 25 September 2011 ) was an English footballer and cricketer .
Benno Walter ( 17 June 1847 -- 23 October 1901 ) was a German violinist and teacher , who had associations with Richard Strauss and his family , to whom he was closely related , and also with Richard Wagner .
Gysbert Behagen ( 8 March 1725 -- 17 December 1783 ) was a German - Danish merchant , ship owner and director of Danish Asia Company .
Girolamo Genga ( c. 1476 -- 11 July 1551 ) was an Italian painter and architect of the late Renaissance , Mannerist style .
Rosemary Nelson ( née Magee ; 4 September 1958 -- 15 March 1999 ) was a prominent Irish human rights solicitor who was assassinated by an Ulster loyalist paramilitary group in 1999 .
John Gray Bell ( 21 September 1823 -- 21 February 1866 ) was an English bookseller .
Yin Yuying ( 殷玉英 ) ( died 453 ) was briefly an empress of the Chinese dynasty Liu Song .
Kitaw Ejigu died at the age of 58 on 13 January 2006 in the United States ; prior to his death , he was planning to work with the founder of Africa Needs Community Development Corporation , Tad Worku .
Alireza Afzalipour ( 26 March 1909 - 7 April 1993 ) ( Persian : علیرضا افضلی‌پور ‎ ) was an Iranian engineer , businessman and philanthropist who is known as the founder of Shahid Bahonar University of Kerman because of his financial support and outstanding donation to Shahid Bahonar University of Kerman as well as Kerman Medical University .
Cecil Clifford Dobell FRS ( 22 February 1886 , Birkenhead -- 23 December 1949 , London ) was a biologist , specifically a protozoologist .
Parveen Babi ( 4 April 1949 -- 20 January 2005 ) was an Indian actress , who is most remembered for her glamorous roles alongside top heroes of the 1970s and early 1980s in blockbusters like Deewar , Namak Halaal , Amar Akbar Anthony and Shaan .
Sir Watkin Williams - Wynn , 6th Baronet ( 22 May 1820 -- 9 May 1885 ) was a Welsh Conservative Party politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1841 to 1885 .
Zoe Incrocci ( 21 September 1917 -- 6 November 2003 ) , was an Italian actress and voice actress .
Thomas Pleasants ( 1729 - 1818 ) was a notable merchant , property developer and philanthropist in Dublin , Ireland , after whom Pleasants Street in Dublin is named .
Anthemiolus ( died c. 471 AD ) was the son of the Western Roman Emperor Anthemius ( 467 - -472 ) and Marcia Euphemia , daughter of the Eastern Roman emperor Marcian .

Wilhelm Nienstädt ( 16 October 1784 -- 28 April 1862 ) was a Prussian educator and writer .
Herman de Coninck ( 21 February 1944 -- 22 May 1997 ) was a Belgian poet , essayist , journalist and publisher .

Felix Milgrom ( 12 October 1919 -- 2 September 2007 ) was a Polish American immunologist who was State University of New York Distinguished Professor Emeritus at the University at Buffalo School of Medicine and Biomedical Sciences .
Joseph - Émile Barbier ( 1839 - -1889 ) was a French astronomer and mathematician , known for Barbier 's theorem on the perimeter of curves of constant width .

Thanasis Costakis ( Greek : Θανάσης Κωστάκης , 1907 - -2009 ) was a Greek linguist and lexicographer best known for his work on the now - moribund Tsakonian language spoken in the eastern Peloponnese .

Lee E. McMahon ( 1931 - -1989 ) was an American computer scientist .
Laurence Bradford Dakin ( 1904 - 1972 ) was a Nova Scotian author and poet who lived throughout Europe , eventually moving to Laguna Hills , California where he died .
Oba Ewuare ( also Ewuare the Great ) was the king of the Benin Empire from 1440 until 1473 .
Frances Mabel Robinson ( 1858 - 1954 ) , who wrote some of her works by the pen name WS Gregg , was an English novelist and critic .
William Westwood , 1st Baron Westwood OBE ( 28 August 1880 - 13 September 1953 ) , was a British trade unionist and Labour politician .
Frank Silva died on 13 September 1995 , aged 44 , from complications of AIDS .
John Cecil , 7th Earl of Exeter ( c. 1700 - -1722 ) was an English peer and member of the House of Lords , styled Lord Burghley from 1721 to 1722 .
Věra Waldes - Hromádková ( 3 June 1914 - 24 November 1995 ) was a prominent fighter in communist anti - nazi resistance in Paris during WWII .
Antonio Fernández de Córdoba y Cardona , 5th Duke of Sessa ( 2 December 1550 -- 6 January 1606 ) , was a Spanish nobleman .

Charles Tiffin ( 1833 - -1873 ) was an English architect , who spent most of his career in Queensland , Australia where he held the post of Queensland Colonial Architect .
Holger Werfel Scheuermann ( 12 February 1877 -- 3 March 1960 ) was a Danish surgeon after whom Scheuermann 's disease is named .
Stanley Patrick Evelyn Simon ( 14 March 1920 -- 22 May 2008 ) , known as Pat Simon , was a veteran English Master of Wine , wine - merchant and writer on wine .

J. H. Kelly Robinson ( 21 November 1873 -- 5 December 1944 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

Emilio Berio ( 13 October 1905 -- 28 October 1993 , Genoa ) was an Italian entomologist and lawyer .

George Herbert Baker ( February 14 , 1878 -- 1943 ) was an American Impressionist artist who worked primarily in the Richmond , Indiana area and was a member of the `` Richmond Group '' of painters .
Sophie Fedorovitch ( Belarusian : Сафія Федаровіч ; 3 December 1893 -- 25 January 1953 ) was a Russian - born theatrical designer who worked with ballet choreographer Sir Frederick Ashton from his first choreographed ballet in 1926 until her accidental death in 1953 .

János Sándor de Csíkszentmihály ( 14 November 1860 -- 16 July 1922 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Interior Minister between 1913 and 1917 in István Tisza 's second cabinet .

Eufemiusz Czaplic ( Ефим Игнатьевич Чаплиц , Yefim Chaplits ) ( 1768 - -1825 ) was a Polish general and military commander in the service of the Russian Empire .
