Anne Christine of Sulzbach , Princess of Piedmont ( Anne Christine Louise ; 5 February 1704 -- 12 March 1723 ) , also called Anne of the Palatinate , was a princess of the Bavarian Circle of the Holy Roman Empire and first wife of Charles Emmanuel , Prince of Piedmont .
Filippo Abbiati ( 1640 - -1715 ) was an Italian painter of the early - Baroque period , active in Lombardy and Turin , together with Andrea Lanzani and Stefano Maria Legnani , he was a prominent mannerist painters from the School of Lombardy .
Samuel Hallifax or Halifax ( 1733 - -1790 ) was an English churchman and academic , holder of several chairs at Cambridge and bishop of two sees .
Elias , Duke of Parma and Piacenza ( Italian : Elia di Borbone - Parma ; 23 July 1880 -- 27 June 1959 ) was the head of the House of Bourbon - Parma and pretender to the defunct throne of Parma between 1950 and 1959 .
Shi Jian ( 石鑒 ) ( died 350 ) was briefly ( for 103 days ) an emperor of the Chinese / Jie state Later Zhao .
Marie - Thérèse Bardet ( 2 June 1898 -- 8 June 2012 ) was a French supercentenarian .
Magnús Jónsson or Magnús prúði ( c. 1530 -- 1591 ) was an Icelandic official and poet .
Fortunat Alojzy Gonzaga Żółkowski , Ziółkowski ( 2 November 1777 -- 11 September 1822 ) , was a Polish actor , comedist , adaptor , translator , editor of humour magazines , and head of a Polish theatrical family .
Arnold Loxam died , aged 93 , on 14 March 2010 .
Georgios Kasassoglou ( December 1 , 1908 -- June 2 , 1984 ) was a Greek classical musician .
Paschal Robinson , O.F.M. ( 26 April 1870 -- 27 August 1948 ) was an Irish ecclesiastical diplomat .
Airemón mac Áedo ( died 886 ) ( also Éiremón ) was a Dál Fiatach king of Ulaid , which is now Ulster , Ireland .
Marit Allen ( 17 September 1941 -- 26 November 2007 ) was an English fashion journalist and costume designer who specialized in costumes for films .
Jacobus Johannes Uys ( 30 May 1921 -- 29 January 1996 ) , better known as Jamie Uys , was a South African film director , best known for directing The Gods Must Be Crazy .
Milton Shulman ( 1 September 1913 -- 24 May 2004 ) was a Canadian author , film and theatre critic .
James Clayton Barr , CB ( 1856 -- 29 March 1937 ) was a Senior Commodore of the Cunard line .
Lloyd Motz ( June 5 , 1909 , Susquehanna , Pennsylvania -- March 14 , 2004 , New York City ) was an American astronomer .
Tsewang Lhamo ( died 1812 ) was the Queen of the Kingdom of Derge for eight years .
Günther Scholz ( 1911 - 2014 ) was a fighter ace in the Luftwaffe , and was the last surviving member of the Condor Legion during the Spanish Civil War .
Henry Whitaker ( c 1622 - 6 April 1695 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1659 and 1679 .
Wilson Worsdell ( 7 September 1850 -- 14 April 1920 ) was an English locomotive engineer who was locomotive superintendent of the North Eastern Railway from 1890 to 1910 .
Ethel Mary Wood ( 1876 - 1970 ) was the daughter of Quintin Hogg , a businessman and philanthropist who established the Regent Street Polytechnic ( now University of Westminster ) , the largest London - based adult education provider of its day .
Bernard Rudofsky ( April 19 1905 - March 12 , 1988 ) was a Moravian - born American writer , architect , collector , teacher , designer , and social historian .
Muiris mac Torna Ó Maolconaire , Irish scribe , historian and poet , died 1645 .
Henry Maynard , 3rd Viscount Maynard ( 13 March 1788 -- 19 May 1865 ) , was a British peer .
Robert of Shrewsbury ( died 1212 ) was an English cleric , administrator , and judge of the Angevin period .
Stanislav Melnyk ( 11 July 1961 -- 9 March 2015 ) was a Ukrainian businessman and politician .
Richard Smoke ( October 21 , 1944 , Huntingdon , Pennsylvania -- May 1995 , Sarasota , California ) was an American historian , and political scientist .
Air Vice - Marshal William Ernest Staton CB , DSO & Bar , MC , DFC & Bar ( 27 August 1898 -- 22 July 1983 ) was a British airman who began his career as a First World War flying ace credited with 26 victories .
Theodore Augustine Mann , known as the Abbé Mann ( 22 June 1735 - -23 February 1809 ) , was an English naturalist and historian , and a Carthusian monk .
Thomas James Montgomery Priestley , also known as Tommy Priestley or Tom Priestley ( 11 March 1911 -- 28 July 1985 ) was a Northern Irish footballer who played at both professional and international levels as a striker .
Jess Julius Engelstad ( 1822 -- 1896 ) was a Norwegian engineer and railroad administrator .
Giacomo Raibolini ( 1484 -- 3 January 1557 ) , alternative names ;
George Heber Jones ( 14 August 1867 -- 11 May 1919 ) was an American Christian missionary in Korea .
Qurra ibn Sharik al - Absi was the governor of Egypt in 709 - -715 , under the Umayyad Caliphate .
James Hay , Lord Hay and Lord Slains ( c.1797 -- 16 June 1815 ) was a British soldier .
Abbie Burgess Grant ( 1839 - -1892 ) was an American lighthouse keeper known for her bravery in tending the Matinicus Rock Light in Maine during a raging winter storm in 1856 .
John Walson Sr . ( 1915 - -1993 ) , from Mahanoy City , Pennsylvania , is recognized by the U.S. Congress and the National Cable Television Association as having invented cable TV in the spring of 1948 .
George Somes Layard ( 1857 - -1925 ) was an English barrister and man of letters .
John Myles , also known as John Miles , ( c. 1621 - -1683 ) was the founder of Swansea , Massachusetts and founder of the earliest recorded Baptist churches in Wales ( U.K. ) and Massachusetts ( U.S.A. ) .
Austin Quinn ( 1892 - -1974 ) was an Irish prelate of the Roman Catholic Church who served as the Bishop of Kilmore from 1950 to 1972 .
Lucas Franchoys the Younger or Lucas Franchoys II ( alternative spellings of name : Lucas Franchois , Lucas François , Louis Franchoys ) ( 28 June 1616 in Mechelen -- 3 April 1681 in Mechelen ) was a Flemish Baroque painter from Mechelen , who painted numerous altarpieces and portraits in a style reminiscent of Anthony van Dyck .
Rear - Admiral Rafe Grenville Rowley - Conwy , CMG ( 11 September 1875 - 4 April 1951 ) , was a Royal Navy officer and Lord Lieutenant of Flintshire .
Halbert Powers Gillette ( 1869 - 1958 ) was an American engineer and prolific author of textbooks and handbooks for the engineering and construction fields .
Italina Lida `` Ida '' Kravanja ( 7 July 1907 -- 10 May 1979 ) , known under her pseudonym Ita Rina , was a Slovenian film actress and beauty queen .
Derek Goodwin ( 26 February 1920 -- 14 May 2008 ) was a British ornithologist who wrote a series of what The Times called `` definitive works '' on estrildid finches , crows and pigeons .
Arsenie Boca ( 29 September 1910 -- 28 November 1989 ) was a Romanian Orthodox monk , theologian and artist .
Sanan Alizade ( Azerbaijani : Sənan Əlizadə ) ( 1943 -- 31 January 2008 ) was an Azerbaijani politician and first Mayor of Baku , capital of Azerbaijan Republic .
T. Kanakam ( c. 1927 -- 21 July 2015 ) was an Indian Telugu drama and film actress and singer between the 1940s and 1960s .
Fred Taral ( 1867 - -1925 ) was an American Hall of Fame jockey .
Willy Vandersteen ( 15 February 1913 -- 28 August 1990 ) was a Belgian creator of comic books .
Ely Devons ( 29 July 1913 -- 28 December 1967 ) , an economist and statistician , was born in Bangor , Gwynedd North Wales , lived most of his life in Manchester and died after a long illness at St Thomas Hospital in London .
Jamie Fielding ( 1960 - -1993 ) was an Australian pianist , composer , and experimental musician .
Anna Maria Bennett ( ca . 1750 -- 12 February 1808 ) was an English novelist .
Edward Burgh , 2nd Baron Borough of Gainsborough , ( c.1463 - -20 August 1528 ) de jure 4th Baron Strabolgi , was an English peer .
Antonio Rinaldeschi ( died 1501 ) was an Italian gambler and blasphemer , who gained notoriety for throwing dung at a painting of the Virgin Mary above the doorway of the church of Santa Maria degli Alberghi in Florence .
Melekber Hanimefendi ( Arabic : ملك بر هانم افندی‎ , Turkish : Melekper Hanımefendi , died October 1890 ) ( Melekber meaning `` angel wings '' ) was the second wife of Said Pasha , Wāli of Egypt and Sudan from 1854 until 1863 .
Walter Flight ( 21 January 1841 -- 4 November 1885 ) , was an English mineralogist who studied the chemical composition of meteorites .
Sir Fairfax Leighton Cartwright GCMG GCVO ( 20 July 1857 - 9 January 1928 ) was a British author and diplomat who became ambassador to the Austro - Hungarian empire before World War I.
General Sir James Freeth KCB KH ( 1786 -- 19 January 1867 ) was Quartermaster - General to the Forces .
Adolph Grant Wolf died on November 3 , 1947 , after winning the admiration of Puerto Rico 's legal profession for his accomplishments on the bench .
Henry Foley , S.J. ( 9 August 1811 -- 19 November 1891 ) was an English Jesuit Roman Catholic church historian .
James Losh ( 1763 - -1833 ) was an English lawyer , reformer and Unitarian in Newcastle upon Tyne .
Elizabeth Boutell , née Davenport ( early 1650s?--1715 ) , was a British actress .
Terence de Vere White ( 29 April 1912 -- 17 June 1994 ) was an Irish writer , lawyer and editor .
Joyce Ann Brown ( died 13 June 2015 ) was wrongfully convicted of robbery and murder in 1980 and spent almost a decade in prison before her conviction was overturned .
Victor Adler ( 24 June 1852 -- 11 November 1918 ) was an Austrian politician , a leader of the labour movement and founder of the Social Democratic Workers ' Party ( SDAP ) .
William Greenhill ( 1591 - -1671 ) was an English nonconformist clergyman , independent minister , and member of the Westminster Assembly .
Samuel Osiński ( died 1649 ) of Radwan coat of arms was a high - ranking noble ( szlachcic ) in the Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth .
Saint Felix of Rhuys ( died 1038 ) was a Breton Benedictine hermit and abbot .
Charles Alfred Holland ( 1872 - -1940 ) , who went by Charles A. Holland , was a University of Southern California football captain , a businessman and a Los Angeles , California , City Council member between 1929 and 1931 .
Vernon Duke ( 10 October ( O.S. 27 September ) 1903 -- 16 January 1969 ) was an American composer / songwriter , who also wrote under his original name , Vladimir Dukelsky .
George Heslop ( 1 July 1940 -- 17 September 2006 ) was an English footballer .
Mahmoud Mabsout ( Arabic : محمود مبسوط‎ ) , also known by the character Fehmen ( Arabic : فهمان‎ ) ( 1941 -- 25 July 2011 ) was a Lebanese actor .
Kamala Sohonie ( 1912 - -1998 ) was an Indian biochemist .
Blessed Francesco Pianzola ( 5 October 1881 - 4 June 1943 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic priest who established the Missionary Sisters of the Immaculata , Queen of Peace .
Manuel Alejandro Aponte Gómez ( 10 December 1974 -- 9 April 2014 ) , commonly referred to by his alias `` El Bravo '' ( `` The Fierce One '' ) , was a Mexican professional hitman and high - ranking leader of the Sinaloa Cartel , a drug trafficking organization .
Carlo Mauri ( 25 March 1930 -- 31 May 1982 ) was an Italian mountaineer and explorer .
María Alejandra Ana Da Passano ( 26 July 1947 -- 30 June 2014 ) , better known as Alejandra Da Passano , was an Argentine actress of film , stage and television .
Percy Hughes ( 1872 - -1952 ) was a philosopher and teacher , and a leading figure in the Philosophy , Education , and Psychology department at Lehigh University .
Alex Bain ( born 22 January 1936 ; died 2014 ) was a professional footballer , who played for teams in both Scotland and England .
Frederick Thomas Elworthy ( 1830 - -1907 ) was an English philologist and antiquary .
Princequillo ( 1940 - -1964 ) was a Thoroughbred racehorse conceived in France and born in Ireland .
Thomas Girdlestone ( Holt , Norfolk , 1758 -- 25 June 1822 ) was an English physician and writer .
Mehmed Saqizli ( Turkish : Sakızlı Mehmed Paşa , literally , Mehmed Pasha of Chios ) ( died 1649 ) , ( r.1631 - 49 ) was Dey and Pasha of Tripolis .
Benjamin Batson ( 1942 - -1996 ) was an American mathematician and historian who studied 20th century Thai history .
Dr. Lawrence Lual Lual Akuei ( 1940 - 2011 ) was a Sudanese politician born in Mathiang - Agor village of Ajak area into a family of spiritual leader Lual Akuei Lual of Pakuein Paan - Deng sub - clan of Agaal - Liil section .
Ruggero Settimo ( 19 May 1778 -- 12 May 1863 ) was an Italian politician , diplomat , and patriotic activist from Sicily .
Charles Dutton , 7th Baron Sherborne ( 13 May 1911 -- 25 December 1983 ) was a British peer .
Dekha Ibrahim Abdi ( Somali : Deeka Ibraahiim Cabdi , Arabic : دخا إبراهيم عبدي‎ ) ( 1964 - 14 July 2011 ) was an ethnic Somali peace activist based in Mombasa , Kenya .
Henry William Greville ( 1801 - -1872 ) was an English aristocrat and diarist .
John Andrew Buchanan ( 1863 - -1935 ) was a judge and politician in Astoria in the U.S. state of Oregon , and an amateur poet who wrote the lyrics to the Oregon state song .
Rosa Mulholland ( also known as Lady Gilbert , 1841 -- 1921 ) was an Irish novelist , poet and playwright .
Luka Ćelović ( Serbian Cyrillic Лука Ћеловић ; 18 October 1854 in Pridvorci , near Trebinje -- 15 August 1929 in Belgrade ) was a Serbian wholesaler , merchant and rentier .
Thomas Dacre , 2nd Baron Dacre of Gilsland , KG ( 25 November 1467 -- 24 October 1525 ) was the son of Humphrey Dacre , 1st Baron Dacre of Gilsland and Mabel Parr ; great - aunt of queen consort Catherine Parr , the sixth and final wife of King Henry VIII of England .
George William Meadley ( 1774 - -1818 ) was an English merchant , known as a biographer .
Thomas Vere Hodgson ( 1864 - -1926 ) was a biologist aboard H.M.S. Discovery during the Discovery Expedition of 1901 - -1904 , known by the nickname Muggins .
Christian Kramp ( 8 July 1760 -- 13 May 1826 ) was a French mathematician , who worked primarily with factorials .
Walter Aston , 3rd Lord Aston of Forfar ( 1633 -- 20 November 1714 ) was the eldest son of Walter Aston , 2nd Lord Aston of Forfar , and his wife Lady Mary Weston , daughter of Richard Weston , 1st Earl of Portland .
William Henry Singleton ( August 10 , 1843 -- September 7 , 1938 ) was an American slave from North Carolina who became a Union soldier during the American Civil War .
Isaac Hodgson ( 15 November 1828 -- 24 November 1867 ) commonly known as `` Ikey '' or `` Ike '' , was an English first - class cricketer , who played nine games for Yorkshire as a pre - county club between 1852 and 1862 , and 21 for Yorkshire in the County Championship between 1863 and 1866 .
Suzanne Haïk - Vantoura ( née Vantoura ) ( 13 July 1912 -- 22 October 2000 ) was an organist , music teacher , composer and music theorist .
Viktor Mineyev ( 19 June 1937 -- 22 July 2002 ) is a former Soviet modern pentathlete and Olympic Champion .
Lillemor von Hanno ( née Bergljot Selmer ; 30 December 1900 -- 5 April 1984 ) was a Norwegian actress , novelist and playwright .
Major Edward Croft - Murray ( 1907 - 1980 ) was a British antiquarian , an expert on British art , and Keeper of the Department of Prints and Drawings at the British Museum from 1954 - 1973 .
İbrahim Hakkı Erzurumi ( 18 May 1703 - 22 June 1780 ) , a popular sufi saint of Turkey from Erzurum in eastern Anatolia - mystic , poet , author , astronomer , physicist , psychologist , sociologist and Islamic scholar .
Niclas , Graf von Abensberg ( 1441 -- 28 February 1485 ) was a knight and nobleman under the reign of Louis IX , Duke of Bavaria .
James Maitland , 9th Earl of Lauderdale ( 12 May 1784 -- 22 August 1860 ) , styled Viscount Maitland between 1789 and 1839 , was a British peer and Whig politician .
Blaise de Vigenère ( 5 April 1523 -- 19 February 1596 ) ( French pronunciation : ​(viʒnɛːʁ ) ) was a French diplomat , cryptographer , translator and alchemist .
Eric Cochran ( 18 June 1890 -- 12 April 1969 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Frederick James Gould ( 19 December 1855 -- 6 April 1938 ) was an English teacher , writer , and pioneer secular humanist .
James Stuart , 2nd Earl of Bute ( before 1696 -- 28 January 1723 ) was the son of James Stuart , 1st Earl of Bute and Agnes Mackenzie .
Derrick Wayne Frazier ( 28 April 1977 in Dallas , Texas - 31 August 2006 in Huntsville , Texas ) was an American convicted murderer .
Harriett Hesketh or Harriett Cowper ( 1733 -- 5 January 1807 ) is known for her correspondence with William Cowper .
Sir Gore Ouseley , 1st Baronet GCH ( 24 June 1770 -- 18 November 1844 ) , was a British entrepreneur , linguist and diplomat .
Marnix Gijsen 20 October 1899 - 29 September 1984 ) was a Belgian writer .
John Stark Ravenscroft ( 1772 - -1830 ) was the first Bishop of the Episcopal Diocese of North Carolina .
Zhufu Yan ( 主父偃 , died 126 or 127 BCE ) was one of the high - ranking court official and advisor to Emperor Wu of Han .
Sir Edward Hales , 2nd Baronet ( 1626 -- c. 1684 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1681 .
Dorothy , Lady Pakington ( née Coventry ) ( 1623 - -1679 ) was an English friend and supporter of learned clergymen , and a writer of religious works .
Frederik Ferdinand Friis ( 16 December 1793 - 18 March 1865 ) was a Danish architect , professor and Royal Building Inspector .
Badis ben Habus was the third Berber king of the Kingdom of Granada and the founder of Alhambra palace , ruled between 1038 and 1073 .
Alex Glasgow ( 14 October 1935 -- 14 May 2001 ) was a singer / songwriter from Low Fell , Gateshead , England .
Professor Jakes Gerwel ( 18 January 1946 -- 28 November 2012 ) was a South African academic and anti - apartheid activist .
Jacob Franquart ( 1582/3 -- 6 January 1651 ( buried ) ) was a Flemish painter , court architect , and an outstanding copper plate engraver .
Dr Alan William Greenwood CBE FRSE ( 1897 - -1981 ) was a Scottish zoologist and geneticist , who helped pave the way to creating Dolly the Sheep .
Alice Merrill Horne ( 1868 - -1948 ) was a Utah artist and politician .
Archduchess Maria Luisa of Austria , Princess of Tuscany ( full name : Maria Luisa Annunziata Anna Giovanna Giuseppa Antonietta Filomena Apollonia Tommasa ) ( 31 October 1845 -- 27 October 1917 ) was a Princess of Tuscany , and later Princess of Isenburg and Büdingen .
Empress Yujiulü ( 郁久閭皇后 , personal name unknown ) ( 525 - -540 ) , formally Empress Dao ( 悼皇后 , literally `` the untimely - dead empress '' ) , was an empress of the Chinese / Xianbei state Western Wei -- a branch successor state of Northern Wei .
Jacob Bronowski ( 18 January 1908 -- 22 August 1974 ) was a British mathematician , historian of science , theatre author , poet and inventor .
Chieh Yuan ( 15 March 1945 -- 16 November 1977 ) was an actor and martial artist .
Francis Holl ( 23 March 1815 -- 14 January 1884 ) , was an English engraver .
Sverre Wilberg ( 24 December 1929 -- 19 July 1996 ) was a Norwegian actor , perhaps best remembered as the clumsy police superintendent Hermansen , always going after Egon and the rest of Olsenbanden .
Margit Anna born Margit Sichermann ( 1913 - -1991 ) was a twentieth century Hungarian painter .
Ricardo dos Santos ( 23 May 1990 -- 20 January 2015 ) was a Brazilian surfer .
Philopoemen Constantinidi or Caracosta ( 1909 , Thessaloniki , Salonica Vilayet , Ottoman Empire -- 1992 , Paris , France ) was a Greek painter and engraver .
Jerome of Prague ( Jeroným Pražský in Czech , 1379 -- 30 May 1416 ) was a Czech church reformer and one of the chief followers of Jan Hus who was burned for heresy at the Council of Constance .
John Edward Parkinson ( 1955 - -2004 ) was Professor of Law at Bristol University and a key member of the Company Law Review Steering Group which worked towards the recent Companies Act 2006 .
Mabel O'Donnell ( 1890 - -1985 ) was an author of popular children 's literature , mostly basal readers that helped young readers build stamina and endurance .
George Baillie ( 16 March 1664 -- 6 August 1738 ) was a Scottish politician who served in the Parliament of Scotland and the Parliament of Great Britain .
George Murnu ( Aromanian : Ioryi al Murnu ; 1 January 1868 , Veria , Salonica Vilayet , Ottoman Empire , now in Greece -- 17 November 1957 , Bucharest ) was a Romanian university professor , archaeologist , historian , translator , and poet of Aromanian origin .
Nard Jones ( 1904 - -1972 ) was an American writer , best known for his novels .
Frederic Westcott ( died 1861 ) was an English botanist .
Robert McGowan Coventry or Robert McGown Coventry ( 1855 -- 1914 ) was a Scottish painter born in Glasgow .
Simon Oates ( 6 January 1932 -- 20 May 2009 ) was an English actor best known for his roles on television .
Francesco Baratta the elder ( c. 1590 - 1666 ) was an Italian sculptor of the Baroque period .
Jean Louis Joseph Lebeau ( 3 January 1794 -- 19 March 1865 ) was a Belgian liberal politician and statesman , the second Prime Minister .
Beryl Ingham ( 1901 -- 24 December 1960 ) was the wife and manager of singer / actor George Formby , as well as being a variety performer and champion clogdancer .
Bård Annar Poulsson ( 23 March 1911 -- 23 November 1996 ) was a Norwegian businessperson in the insurance industry .
Whitwell Elwin ( 26 February 1816 -- 1 January 1900 ) was an English clergyman , critic and editor of the Quarterly Review .
Brooks Crompton Wood ( 27 March 1870 -- 29 July 1946 ) was a British Conservative Party politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1924 to 1929 as the Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Bridgwater .
Toivo Reingoldt ( 15 March 1906 -- 28 September 1941 ) was a Finnish swimmer who won a European title in the 200 m breaststroke in 1931 .
Edward Moxon ( 12 December 1801 -- 3 June 1858 ) was a British poet and publisher , significant in Victorian literature .
Samuel Arthur Saunder ( 1852 -- December 8 , 1912 ) was a British mathematician and selenographer who taught at Wellington College , Berkshire .
Ercole Setti ( c.1530 - -1618 ) was an Italian engraver of the late - Renaissance period .
George Newenham Wright ( c. 1794 - -1877 ) was an Irish writer and Anglican clergyman .
Andrew McDermot ( 1790 - -12 October 1881 ) was a Hudson 's Bay Company ( HBC ) employee who became a prominent independent fur trade merchant and member of the Council of Assiniboia .
Thomas Llewellyn Jones ( 8 March 1872 -- 18 June 1946 ) was a company director and member of both the Queensland Legislative Council and Queensland Legislative Assembly .
Peter Breisiger ( also Briesger , Bryssiger , fl . 1516 - 1542 , dates of birth and death unknown ) was a German organ builder .
John Vaughan , 1st Earl of Carbery ( 1574 or 1575 -- 6 May 1634 ) was a Welsh courtier and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1601 and from 1621 to 1622 .
Zvi Sliternik ( Hebrew : צבי סליטרניק‎ ; born 16 May 1897 , died 1994 ) was an Israeli entomologist .
Marguerite Agnes Power ( 1815 - -1867 ) was a novelist , writer for periodicals , and editor throughout the majority of her life .
Harry Scott Newlands ( 1884 -- 1933 ) was the Ghana British Chief Commissioner from 1930 to 1933 and Governor of Barbados from January to March 1933 .
Hartwig of Uthlede ( died 3 November 1207 ) was a German nobleman who -- as Hartwig II --
Vattaparambil Sankaran Valiathan ( October 1919 -- 21 June 2006 ) , commonly referred to as Artist V. S. Valiathan was an Indian artist from Pandalam , who was known for his classical style of painting in the Raja Ravi Varma tradition .
Bertita Harding ( 11 November 1902 -- 31 December 1971 ) was a royal biographer with an easy and sometimes humorous style that made her a popular author .
Henry Lennard , 12th Baron Dacre ( 25 March 1570 -- 8 August 1616 ) was an English baron and politician .
Edwin Stead ( aka Edward Stead ) ( 1701 , Harrietsham , Kent -- 28 August 1735 , London ) was a noted patron of English cricket , particularly of Kent teams in the early years of major cricket .
John Alexander Dowie ( 25 May 1847 -- 9 March 1907 ) was a Scottish evangelist and faith healer who ministered in Australia and the United States .
Jacob Mountain died at Marchmont House , Lower Canada , 16 June 1825 and was buried under the chancel of the Holy Trinity Cathedral , which also contains a monument to his memory .
Yves Duval ( 21 March 1934 - 22 May 2009 ) was a Belgian comics author who mainly worked for Tintin magazine , but also wrote comics , stories , and articles for other magazines .
King Xiaocheng of Zhao ( Chinese : 趙孝成王 ; reigned 265 -- died 245 BCE ) was a king of the State of Zhao during the Warring States period of ancient Chinese .
James Evan Baillie ( 1781 - 14 June 1863 ) was a British West Indies merchant , landowner and Whig politician who sat in the House of Commons in two periods between 1813 and 1835 .
Gogumal Kishenchand Harisinghani pronunciation ( 14 April 1925 , Karachi -- 16 April 1997 , Baroda ) was Indian Test cricketer .
Michael Vadbolsky ( 1899 - -1990 ) was a painter , writer and researcher of chess history who contributed to the development of the Georgian Chess School .
Willem Claesz Vooght ( 1572 -- 1630 ) , was a mayor of Haarlem best known today for the portrait painted of him by the painter Frans Hals .
Johan Christian Viggo Ullmann ( 21 December 1848 -- 30 August 1910 ) was a Norwegian educator and politician of Venstre , the Norwegian social - liberal party .
Charles E. Roberts ( March 13 , 1843-March 1934 ) was an engineer , inventor and an important early client and patron of Frank Lloyd Wright .
Seán Caughey ( Irish : Seán Mac Eochaidh ) ( died 18 July 2010 ) was an Irish republican , and later a monarchist and activist .
Francis Harison ( died 1740 ) was a lawyer and politician in colonial New York .
Phillip Cottrell ( 5 June 1968 -- 11 December 2011 ) was a British - born journalist .
Maria Hack ( née Barton , 16 February 1777 -- 4 January 1844 ) was an English writer of educational books for children .
Harriet Grote ( 1792 - -1878 ) was an English biographer , and as wife to George Grote hostess to the English philosophical radicals of the earlier nineteenth century .
Selâmet I Giray ( 1568 - -1610 ) was a khan of the Crimean Khanate who reigned from 1608 to 1610 .
Haim Kantorovitch ( 1890 - -1936 ) was an American socialist teacher , writer , and Marxist theoretician .
Juan Victor Séjour Marcou et Ferrand ( 2 June 1817 -- 20 September 1874 ) was an American expatriate writer who worked in France .
Algy Millhouse ( 13 May 1887 -- 1 October 1948 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Henry Hampden Dutton ( 13 February 1879 -- 15 June 1932 ) , often referred to as Harry Dutton , was a South Australian pastoralist , remembered for in 1908 making the first automobile journey from Adelaide to Port Darwin .
Thomas F. Cooke ( ca.1863 - -1941 ) was an American banker and a City Council member in Los Angeles , California , between 1929 and 1931 .
Robert David MacDonald ( 27 August 1929 -- 19 May 2004 ) was a Scottish playwright , translator and theatre director .
Johannes Cardinalis von Bergreichenstein ( Jan Kardinál z Rejnštejna ) ( circa 1375 -- after 1428 ) was a Czech lawyer and diplomat .
Wong Nai Siong ( Chinese : 黄乃裳 ) ( 1849 - -1924 ) as a Chinese revolutionary leader and educator from Minqing county in Fuzhou , Fujian province , China .
Thomas Moundeford M.D. ( 1550 - -1630 ) was an English academic and physician , President of the London College of Physicians for three periods .
Friedrich Eibner ( 1826 - -1877 ) , a German painter of architectural subjects , was born at Hilpoltstein .
Lou Reiffel ( 5 November 1910 -- 16 November 1977 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Amanullah Sailaab Sapi(an alternative spelling for Safi ) ( Pashto : امان الله سېلاب ساپی/صافي ‎ , born 1933 - died 1979 ) was a renowned Afghan poet and writer .
James Sinclair , 14th Earl of Caithness FRS ( 16 August 1821 -- 28 March 1881 ) , styled Lord Berriedale from 1823 to 1855 , was a Scottish Liberal politician , scientist and inventor .
Sir Charles Umpherston Aitchison ( 1832 -- 1896 ) , was a Scottish born Lieutenant Governor of the Punjab , then a province of British India .
Robert Koch Woolf , formerly known as Robert Koch ( 1923 , in Temple , Texas -- 2004 , in Montecito , California ) , was an American interior decorator noted for the Hollywood homes he created with architect John Elgin Woolf .
William Badby ( died 1380 ) was a Carmelite and theological writer .
Barbara Wootton , Baroness Wootton of Abinger CH ( 14 April 1897 -- 11 July 1988 ) was a British sociologist and criminologist .
Olav Liestøl ( 24 February 1916 -- 3 April 2002 ) was a Norwegian glaciologist .
G. A. Vadivelu ( 12 June 1925 -- 13 January 2016 ) was a freedom fighter and a close associate of Mahatma Gandhi , Jayaprakash Narayan , Rajaji and Kamaraj .
Adam Stansfield ( 10 September 1978 -- 10 August 2010 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a striker .
Samia Sarwar ( 1970 -- 6 April 1999 ) was a Pakistani Pukhtun woman , who was shot dead in her lawyers ' office in Lahore in an `` honor killing . ''
Giovanni Giacomazzi ( 18 January 1928 , in San Martino di Lupari , Padova -- 12 December 1995 ) was an Italian football ( soccer ) player .
Maharaja Sir Mayurdwajsinhji Meghrajji III , KCIE ( 3 March 1923 -- 1 August 2010 ) was the last ruling Maharaja of Dhrangadhra Halvad .
Jens Christian Kofoed ( 6 April 1864 - 3 November 1941 ) was a Danish architect who adopted the Historicist style inspired by Italian architecture from the Middle Ages .
Kajetan Georg von Kaiser ( 5 January 1803 -- 28 August 1871 ) was a German chemistry professor , researcher and inventor .
Jack Trehey ( 28 May 1882 -- 5 December 1943 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Paulus Constantijn la Fargue , also Constantine Paul Lafargue , ( The Hague , 5 January 1729 - 10 June 1782 ) was a Dutch painter , etcher and draftsman .
Sacha Kolin ( 9 May 1911 ( Paris , France ) - 14 February 1981 ( New York City , United States ) ) was a French - born painter .
Henry Koplik ( October 28 , 1858 in New York - 1927 ) was an American physician .
Margaret Bastock ( c1920 - 1982 ) was a zoologist and geneticist .
Parson Jonathan Fisher ( 1768 - -1847 ) was the first Congregational minister from 1794 to 1837 in the small village of Blue Hill , Maine in the United States .
Pavle Solarić ( 7 August 1779 -- 18 January 1821 ) was a Serbian linguist , geographer , archaeologist , poet and man of letters .
Courtney Shropshire ( July 10 , 1877 -- 1965 ) , a prominent doctor in Birmingham , Alabama , was the founder and first president of Civitan International .
Edmond Malone ( 4 October 1741 -- 25 May 1812 ) was an Irish Shakespearean scholar and editor of the works of William Shakespeare .
Xiao He ( died 193 BC ) was a Chinese statesman of the early Western Han dynasty .
Giuseppe Musolino ( 24 September 1876 - 22 January 1956 ) , also known as the `` Brigante Musolino '' or the `` King of Aspromonte '' , was an Italian brigand and folk hero .
Norman DePoe ( 4 May 1917 - 13 March 1980 ) , was a star CBC reporter in Canada for eight years in the 1960s on national and international affairs .
Charles Moffat Howe ( 1851 - -1920 ) was a dentist and the Mayor of Passaic , New Jersey .
Paolo Baffi ( 5 August 1911 - - 4 August 1989 ) was an Italian academic , banker and economist .
James Logie Robertson ( 18 September 1846 -- June 1922 ) was a literary scholar , editor and author , who also wrote under the pen name Hugh Haliburton .
Thomas Guillaume St. Barbe Baker ( 1895 - 1966 ) was a pre - War British national socialist who had been an officer in World War I as a 2nd Lieutenant in the Royal Field Artillery and later as a Captain in the Royal Air Force .
Moctezuma I ( c. 1398 - -1469 ) , also known as Motecuhzoma Ilhuicamina , Huehuemotecuhzoma or Montezuma I ( Classical Nahuatl : Motēuczōma Ilhuicamīna ( moteːkʷˈsoːma ilwikaˈmiːna ) , Classical Nahuatl : Huēhuemotēuczōma ( weːwemoteːkʷˈsoːma ) ) , was the second Aztec emperor and fifth king of Tenochtitlan .
Martin Gwilt Jolley ( 1859 - 1916 ) was an English painter .
William Roger Paton , usually cited as W. R. Paton ( 2 September 1857 -- 21 April 1921 ) , was an author and translator of ancient Greek texts and poets , mostly known for his translation of the Greek anthology .
Pierre de Milard ( often referred to as Chevalier Milard , also spelled Chevalier Millard ; 1736 - -1778 ) was a former French Navy officer , who became a senior officer in the Royal Burmese Armed Forces .
Landgravine Magdalena Sibylla of Hesse - Darmstadt ( 28 April 1652 -- 11 August 1712 ) was regent of the Duchy of Württemberg from 1677 to 1693 , and was a prominent German composer of baroque hymns .
William Quarrier ( 29 September 1829 -- 16 October 1903 ) was a shoe retailer and philanthropist from Glasgow , Scotland .
Dr. Dhirendra Verma ( 17 May 1897 -- 23 April 1973 ) was a prominent Indian poet and writer .
Géza Vida ( or Gheza Vida , 28 February 1913 , Nagybánya - 11 May 1980 , Baia Mare ) was a Romanian - Hungarian sculptor from Maramureș .
Sir Francis Bryan ( about 1490 -- 2 February 1550 ) was an English courtier and diplomat during the reign of Henry VIII . He was Chief Gentleman of the Privy chamber and Lord Chief Justice of Ireland .
Ismail Djoemala ( also credited Rd Djoemala ; Perfected Spelling : Ismail Jumala ; 1915/1918 -- 10 June 1992 ) was an Indonesian actor active in the 1940s .
Wang Guoquan ( Chinese : 王国权 ) ( 1911 - 2004 ) was a Chinese diplomat .
Richard Geren , OC ( 1917 - -2002 ) , was an American geologist who was a key member of a team that defined high - grade iron ore deposits in the Knob Lake area of northeastern Quebec .
Sultan Bahu ( also spelled Bahoo ; ca 1630 - -1691 ) was a Sufi mystic , poet and scholar active mostly in the present - day Punjab province of Pakistan .
Pope Sylvester III or Silvester III ( c. 1000 -- 1062 or 1063 ) , born Giovanni dei Crescenzi--
Ibn Abd al - Zahir ( Muḥyī d - Dīn ibn ʿAbd aẓ - Ẓāhir محيي الدين بن عبد الظاهر , 1223 - -1293 ) was an Egyptian historian during the Mamluk period .
Donald Wyman ( 1904 -- 6 December 1993 ) was an American horticulturist , the head of horticulture at Harvard University 's Arnold Arboretum from 1935 to 1970 .
Hugh Farmer ( 20 January 1714 , -- 5 February 1787 ) was an English Dissenter and theologian .
Edwin Griffiths ( 1884 - -1950 ) was an English footballer who played for Stoke .
Murlidhar Devidas Amte , popularly known as Baba Amte ( 26 December 1914 -- 9 February 2008 ) was an Indian social worker and social activist known particularly for his work for the rehabilitation and empowerment of poor people suffering from leprosy .
Nissan Nativ ( Hebrew : ניסן נתיב ) ( originally Notowicz ; 5 . November 1922 -- 20 April 2008 ) was an influential Israeli director , actor and acting teacher .
Francesco Foschi ( 1710 - -1780 ) was an Italian painter best known for painting winter landscapes .
George Douglas , 13th Earl of Morton ( 1662 -- 4 January 1738 ) , styled The Honourable George Douglas between 1681 and 1730 , was a Scottish nobleman and politician .
Consuelo Zavala Castillo ( 1874 - 1956 ) was a Mexican feminist teacher , and founder of one of the first secular private schools in Mérida , Mexico .
Édouard Goubert ( 29 July 1894 to 14 August 1979 ) was former mayor and first chief minister of Puducherry between 1 July 1963 -- 11 September 1964 .
Jaime Batalha Reis ( 1847 - -1934 ) was a Portuguese agronomist and diplomat , born in Lisbon on 24 December 1847 .
Sir Thomas Herbert Maddock ( 18 May 1792 -- 15 January 1870 ) was a British civil servant in India and a Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1852 to 1857 .
Abraham Janssens I , Abraham Janssen I or Abraham Janssens van Nuyssen ( 1575 -- 1632 ) was a Flemish painter , who is known principally for his large religious and mythological works , which show the influence of Caravaggio .
Joaquín Madariaga ( 1799 in Corrientes -- 1848 ) was a soldier and Argentine politician .
Souleymane Kante or Solomana Kante ( 1922 - 1987 ) was an African writer and inventor of the N'Ko alphabet for the Manding languages of West Africa .
Andrew Michael Ramsay ( 9 January 1686 -- 6 May 1743 ) , commonly called the Chevalier Ramsay , was a Scottish - born writer who lived most of his adult life in France .
Peter Dacre ( 8 June 1925 - 16 March 2003 ) was a prominent journalist on the Sunday Express whose work included show business features .
Arnold M. Auerbach ( 23 May 1912 ; New York City , New York -- 19 October 1998 ; New York City , New York ) was an American comedy writer , especially for radio , television and newspapers .
Samuel Carpenter ( 4 November 1649 -- 10 April 1714 ) was a Deputy Governor of colonial Pennsylvania .
Benjamin Christensen ( 28 September 1879 -- 2 April 1959 ) was a Danish film director , screenwriter and an actor both in film and on the stage .
Elias Henry Hendren , known as Patsy Hendren ( 5 February 1889 in Turnham Green , Middlesex -- 4 October 1962 in Tooting Bec , London ) , was an English cricketer .
Madan Lal Madhu ( 1925 - -2014 ) was an Indian poet and translator , known for his translations of Russian classics in Hindi language .
Turibius of Mogrovejo ( or Toribio Alfonso de Mogrovejo or Toribio von Lima ) ( 16 November 1538 -- 23 March 1606 ) was a Spanish missionary Archbishop of Lima .
Wilhelm von Bibra ( 1442 - -1490 ) ( Eques auratus ) was a Papal Emissary .
Vice - Admiral Temple West ( 1714 -- 9 August 1757 ) was a British naval officer , best known for his role as second - in - command to Admiral John Byng in the Battle of Minorca ( 1756 ) .
Paul Carus ( 18 July 1852 -- 11 February 1919 ) was a German - American author , editor , a student of comparative religion and philosopher .
Sir Richard Gardiner , Knight , ( died 19 December 1489 ) was , in 1478 , Lord Mayor of London .
William Nugent Macnamara or M'Namara ( c.1776 -- 11 November 1856 ) was an Irish landowner and Member of Parliament .
Conrad Justinger , whose name was frequently omitted in later publications of the Bernese Chronicle , probably died childless in April 1438 .
Ni Tian ( Chinese : 倪田 ; 1855 - -1919 ) , born as Baotian , courtesy name Mogeng , sobriquet as Modaoren and Biyuehezhu , was a Chinese painter in Qing Dynasty and Republic Period .
Bernard Grün ( Stařeč , 11 February 1901 - London , 28 December 1972 ) was a Moravia - born British composer and conductor .
Thomas Colley Grattan ( 1792 -- 4 July 1864 ) , was an Irish miscellaneous writer .
William Larkins ( died 24 April 1800 ) was a member of the Royal Society elected 14 April 1796 He was formerly an accountant in Bengal for the British East India Company .
Athanasius IV of Salh was the Patriarch of Antioch , and head of the Syriac Orthodox Church from 986 until his death in 1002 .
Nejat Saydam ( 15 September 1929 -- 25 October 2000 ) was a Turkish film director , screenwriter , and actor from Istanbul .
Samuel Walker Houston ( 1864 - -1945 ) was an American pioneer in the field of education .
Pierre Abraham Lorillard ( 1742 -- 1776 ) was a tobacconist of New York City .
Frederick , Duke of Schleswig - Holstein - Sonderburg - Augustenburg ( 10 December 1652 -- 3 August 1692 in Edingen ) was a German nobleman .
Henry Canning ( born 8 July 1774 -- died 3 February 1841 , Hamburg , Germany ) was appointed HM Consul General in Hamburg ( including also consular responsibilities in respect of Bremen ) on 29 November 1823 .
Olav Torkelsson , also known as Olaf Thorkelsön ( d. 30 May 1535 , Voss , Bergenhus len ( now Hordaland ) , Norway ) , was the 31st and last Roman Catholic Bishop of Bergen , from 1523 to 1535 , and a member of the Riksråd ( National Council of Norway ) .
Gregorio Tarquini ( died 1145 ) was an Italian cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church .
Alfred Frank Evans ( 3 February 1887 -- 1 February 1964 ) was a British sailor who worked as a lookout on board the ill - fated RMS Titanic .
John de Clinton , 1st Baron Clinton ( died 1315 ) was an English peer .
Eugène Benderitter ( 17 November 1869 , Rouen -- 28 February 1940 , Amiens ) was a French entomologist who specialized in Coleoptera especially Scarabaeidae .
Doksim Mihailović ( Serbian : Доксим Михаиловић ; 20 February 1883 -- 24 October 1912 ) was a Macedonian Serb voivode ( military commander ) , originally a teacher , who joined the Serbian Chetnik Organization to fight in Ottoman Macedonia , and then the Balkan Wars ( in the army of the Kingdom of Serbia ) .
John Mason Neale ( 24 January 1818 -- 6 August 1866 ) was an Anglican priest , scholar and hymn - writer .
Peder Colbjørnsen ( 5 July 1683 -- 17 March 1738 ) was a Norwegian timber merchant and war hero .
Ruby Langford Ginibi ( 26 January 1934 -- 1 October 2011 ) was an acclaimed Bundjalung author , historian and lecturer on Aboriginal history , culture and politics .
Albert Rosen died in Dublin on 22 May 1997 , aged 73 , of lung cancer .
Moritz Henle ( 7 August 1850 -- 24 August 1925 ) was a prominent German composer of liturgical music and cantor of the Jewish reform movement .
Geoff Dyson ( 16 March 1923 - April 1989 ) was an English former professional footballer who played as an inside left .
Rafał Sznajder ( 13 October 1972 -- 13 April 2014 ) was a Polish fencer , who competed in the Atlanta 1996 , Sydney 2000 and Athens 2004 Olympic Games .
Mary Eva Kelly ( later O'Doherty ) ( 1826 - -1910 ) was an Irish - Australian poet and writer who was widely known as Eva of the Nation .
Fritz Dietrich ( 13 or 23 February 1905 -- 1945 ) was a German musicologist and composer .
Americus Backers ( died 1778 ) , sometimes described as the father of the English grand pianoforte style , brought the hammer striking action for keyboard instruments from his master Gottfried Silbermann 's workshop in Freiburg to England in the mid-18th century .
Gilbert Byron died shortly before his 88th birthday on June 25 , 1991 .
George Knapton ( 1698 - -1778 ) was an English portrait painter and the first portraitist for the Society of Dilettanti in the 1740s .
Hugh Lord McDonald ( March 25 , 1841 -- 1890 ) was a contractor and political figure in Prince Edward Island .
Alexander McKee ( ca . 1735 -- 15 January 1799 ) was an agent in the British Indian Department during the French and Indian War , the American Revolutionary War , and the Northwest Indian War .
Charles Creed ( 1909 -- 17 July 1966 ) was a British fashion designer .
Rowland Taylor ( sometimes spelled `` Tayler '' ) ( 6 October 1510 -- 9 February 1555 ) was an English Protestant martyr during the Marian Persecutions .
Berry Nieuwenhuys , ( 5 November 1911 -- 12 June 1984 ) was a South African footballer who played predominantly for Liverpool , which he was contracted to from 1933 to 1947 .
James Christopher Flynn ( 1852 -- 15 November 1922 ) was an Irish nationalist politician who served for 25 years as a member of the Irish Parliamentary Party in the House of Commons of what was then the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland .
Bernard Molitor ( 22 October 1755 -- 17 November 1833 ) was a Luxembourgish cabinet - maker .
Kate Carney ( 1869 -- 1950 ) was an English singer and comedian who played the music halls in London .
Sir Arthur William Buller ( 5 September 1808 -- 30 April 1869 ) was a British Liberal Party Member of Parliament , who in his early career served as head of a commission of inquiry into education reform in Lower Canada .
Hermann Georg Fiedler ( 1862 - -1945 ) , was a German scholar , who became Taylor Professor of the German Language and Literature at the University of Oxford ( 1907 - -37 ) .
Fritz Süffert ( 1891 - 1945 ) was a German entomologist who specialised in studies of butterflies .
Konstanze Vernon ( 2 January 1939 -- 21 January 2013 ) was a German ballet dancer , academic teacher and director of a ballet academy and a ballet company .
Luigi von Kunits ( 20 July 1870 -- 8 October 1931 ) , born Ludwig Paul Maria von Kunits , was an Austrian conductor , composer , violinist , and pedagogue .
Giovanni Bottesini ( 22 December 1821 -- 7 July 1889 ) , was an Italian Romantic composer , conductor , and a double bass virtuoso .
Sir Maitland Mackie , CBE , KStJ , DL , JP ( 16 February 1912 -- 18 June 1996 ) , often known as Mike Mackie , was a British Liberal Party politician , farming pioneer , educational innovator and Lord - Lieutenant of Aberdeenshire .
Robert Richbell ( 1605 - 1688 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 .
Oscytel died on 1 November 971 or on 31 October 971 at Thame , and was buried at Bedford .
Ralph de Cromwell , 1st Baron Cromwell ( died 27 August 1398 ) , Tattershall in Lincolnshire , was an English peer .
Luke Rivington ( May 1838 in London -- 30 May 1899 in London ) was an English Anglican and later Roman Catholic priest and controversial writer .
Hephzibah Menuhin ( 20 May 1920 -- 1 January 1981 ) was an American - Australian pianist , writer , and human rights campaigner .
Jakow Trachtenberg ( 17 June 1888 -- 1953 ) was a Russian mathematician who developed the mental calculation techniques called the Trachtenberg system .
Kristoffer Nilsen Svartbækken Grindalen ( 9 September 1804 -- 25 February 1876 ) was a Norwegian criminal , killer and thief .
Elizabeth Mortimer , Baroness Camoys ( 12 February 1371 -- 20 April 1417 ) was an English noblewoman , the granddaughter of Lionel of Antwerp , 1st Duke of Clarence , and great - granddaughter of King Edward III . Her first husband was Sir Henry Percy , known to history as ' Hotspur ' .
Frances Farley died in 2004 from Alzheimer 's Disease .
Asen Peshev ( Bulgarian : Асен Пешев ) ( 5 March 1908 - 28 June 1967 ) was а Bulgarian footballer .
Peter Aufschnaiter ( 2 November 1899 -- 12 October 1973 ) was an Austrian mountaineer , agricultural scientist , geographer , and cartographer .
Charles Frederick Whittlesey ( 1867 - -1941 ) was an American architect best known for his work in the American southwest , and for pioneering work in reinforced concrete in California .
Harry Littlewood ( 23 May 1921 -- 26 December 2003 ) was a British actor who has appeared in Z - Cars , Softly , Softly , The Saint , Never the Twain , Families , The Bill , Casualty , Bergerac and Howards ' Way .
( Mary ) Kathleen Baxter , née Young , ( 30 May 1901 , Bradford -- 25 October 1988 , Bromley ) was an English women 's rights activist .
Maria Dickons or Martha Frances Caroline Poole ( 1770s -- 4 May 1833 ) was an opera singer .
James Walter Miller ( 1890 - -1950 ) was an American citizen and an alleged asset of the San Francisco Office of the KGB from 1943 to 1945 .
Francis Hartwell Henslowe ( 1811 - 1878 ) , civil servant and composer .
Henry Shepherd Pearson ( c.1775 - 1840 ) was acting Governor of Penang from 1807 to 1808 .
James Deacon Hume ( 1774 -- 1842 ) was an English official , an economic writer and advocate of free trade .
Kalicharan Brahma ( Bodo : कालिचरन ब्रह्मा 1862 -- 1938 ) , originally Kalicharan Mech , was a 20th - century social and religious reformer of Bodo society .
Marko Miljanov Popović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Марко Миљанов Поповић , pronounced ( mâːrkɔ mǐʎanɔʋ pɔ̌pɔʋit͡ɕ ) ; 25 April 1833 -- 2 February 1901 ) was a Montenegrin general , clan chief and writer .
Eliezer Zussman - Sofer ( 1828 - -1902 ) was a Hungarian rabbi and head of a yeshivah .
Diane Nyland Proctor ( 20 January 1944 -- 6 October 2014 ) was a Canadian actress , director and choreographer .
Sexhelm of Lindisfarne ( died 947 ) was Bishop of Lindisfarne for six months in 947 .
Marvin Comisky ( 1918 - -2010 ) was a major figure in the Philadelphia legal community for decades .
Louise Guthrie ( October 10 , 1879 -- February 20 , 1966 ) was a South African botanist and botanical artist .
Wazo of Liège ( c. 985 -- 1048 ) was bishop of Liège from 1041 to 1048 , and a significant educator and theologian .
Bernard III , Lord of Lippe ( c. 1194 -- c. 1265 ) was a German nobleman .
William Henry Crossland ( Huddersfield , West Riding of Yorkshire , England , 1835 -- 14 November 1908 , London , ( stroke ) ) was a 19th - century architect and a pupil of George Gilbert Scott .
Hernando Williams ( c. 1955 -- 25 March 1995 ) was a convicted murderer , executed by the State of Illinois .
Augustin Pyramus de Candolle also spelled Augustin Pyrame de Candolle ( 4 February 1778 -- 9 September 1841 ) was a Swiss botanist .
Antonio Russolo ( 1877 - 1942 ) was an Italian Futurist composer , brother of the more famous Futurist composer and theorist Luigi Russolo .
Vintage Crop ( 1 March 1987 -- 14 July 2014 ) was a British - bred Irish - trained Thoroughbred racehorse best known for becoming the first overseas runner to win Australia 's premier race the Melbourne Cup .
James Watson Kernohan , M.D. ( 1896 - -1981 ) was an Irish - American pathologist born October 1 , 1896 in County Antrim , Ireland .
Anne Macvicar Grant often styled Mrs Anne Grant of Laggan ( 21 February 1755 -- 7 November 1838 ) is a Scottish poet and author best known for her collection of mostly biographical poems Memoirs of an American Lady as well as her earlier work Letters from the Mountains
Patrick Callaghan ( 12 August 1879 -- 26 February 1959 ) was a Scottish football player , who played for Hibernian and represented Scotland once .
Lex McLean ( born Alexander McLean Cameron , 1908 - -23 March 1975 ) was a Scottish comedian .
John Macoun ( 17 April 1831 -- 18 June 1920 ) was an Irish - born Canadian naturalist .
Monsieur Chouchani ( January 9 1895 - -January 26 1968 ) , or `` Shushani , '' is the nickname of an otherwise anonymous and enigmatic Jewish teacher who taught a small number of distinguished students in post - World War II Europe and elsewhere , including Emmanuel Levinas and Elie Wiesel .
George Bariț ( 4 June 1812 -- 2 May 1893 ) , often rendered as George Barițiu , was a Romanian historian , philologist , playwright , politician , businessman and journalist , the founder of the Romanian language press in Transylvania .
Roland Gerber ( 20 May 1953 -- 24 February 2015 ) was a German football coach and a former player .
Lee Chark - tim , GBM ( Chinese : 李澤添 , 23 December 1934 -- 22 May 2007 ) was the president of the Hong Kong Federation of Trade Unions ( HKFTU ) , the largest trade union and pro - Beijing organ in Hong Kong from 1988 to 2000 .
Richard D'Oyly Carte ( 3 May 1844 -- 3 April 1901 ) was an English talent agent , theatrical impresario , composer and hotelier during the latter half of the Victorian era .
Abdul Wahid bin Zaid Abul Fadl ( ' Abdul Wāḥid bin Zaid Abul Faḍl ; died 793 ) was an early day Sufi Saint , a successor to Hasan al - Basri , second link in the Sufi Silsilah of Chishti Order , and the Master of Fudhail Bin Iyadh .
Frans Michel Penning ( 12 September 1894 -- 6 December 1953 ) was a Dutch experimental physicist .
Álvaro Gonçalves da Maia ( 1380 - -1449 ) was a Portuguese noblemen , Ambassador of Aragon .
Frank Sancet ( August 24 , 1907 - March 1985 ) was a college baseball coach for the Arizona Wildcats baseball team .
Thomas Powel ( 1845 -- 16 May 1922 ) was a Welsh Celtic scholar , who was Professor of Celtic at University College , Cardiff from 1884 to 1918 .
Henry Chamberlain Russell , CMG , FRS , ( 17 March 1836 -- 22 February 1907 ) was an Australian astronomer and meteorologist .
Felix Godin , a pseudonym of Henry Albert Brown ( c1864 - 1925 ) , was an English composer of light music , best known for his elegiac Valse Septembre , a light waltz written in 1909 .
Anna Maria Elvia ( 20 February 1713 - 8 May 1784 ) , was a Swedish feminist writer .
Nancy Ford Cones ( 1869 - -1962 ) was an early photographer from Loveland , Ohio , where she documented country life .
Elias Friedman OCD ( 1916 - -1999 ) , was a Carmelite priest .
Arnold Berliner ( Gut Mittelneuland bei Neisse , 26 December 1862 -- Berlin , 22 March 1942 ) was a German physicist .
Go Hui - dong ( 1886 - -1965 ) , also known by the pen name Chun - gok , born in Seoul , was the first Korean painter to adopt Western styles .
Maybanke Anderson also known as Maybanke Wolstenholme ( 17 February 1845 -- 15 April 1927 ) was a Sydney reformer involved in women 's suffrage and federation .
Hélio Gueiros ( 12 December 1925 -- 15 April 2011 ) was a Brazilian politician who served as the Governor of Pará from 1987 to 1991 .
Louis Charles de Montigny ( 1805 - -1868 ) was a French diplomat who was active in Asia during the 19th century .
Gabriel Franchère ( 1786 - -1863 ) was a French Canadian author and explorer of the Pacific Northwest .
Tiberius Claudius Marinus Pacatianus ( died c. 248 ) was a usurper in the Danube area of the Roman Empire during the time of Philip the Arab .
Mehdi Rahimi ( 1921 - 16 February 1979 ) was an Iranian military general .
Frank Skeffington Carroll ( c. 1837 - -1887 ) was a salesman , mapmaker , journalist , editor , and , briefly , politician in the colony of South Australia .
Ian Donald ( December 1910 -- 19 June 1987 ) was a Scottish physician who pioneered the use of diagnostic ultrasound in medicine .
Mathew Carey Lea ( August 16 , 1823 -- March 15 , 1897 ) was a Philadelphia - born American chemist and lawyer .
Kang Ryang - uk ( 강량욱 , 1904 - -1983 ) , also spelled Kang Lyanguk , was a North Korean Protestant Minister and Chairman of the Christian Federation of Korea during the 1950s .
Piotr Drzewiecki ( 29 May 1865 , Warsaw - 8 December 1943 , Berlin ) was the President of Warsaw in the 20th century .
Richard Heighway ( 1832 - 1917 ? ) was an illustrator , noted and exhibited for his black and white designs of Aesop 's fables .
Ram Dutt Joshi ( 16 November 1916 -- 26 December 1976 ) was an Indian Bishop of the United Methodist Church , elected in 1968 .
Rodolfo Oroz ( 8 July 1895 -- 13 April 1997 ) was a Chilean writer , professor , and philologist .
Phil Coe ( 1839 - -1871 ) , was a soldier , and Old West gambler and businessman from Texas .
Samo Resnik ( 1962 , Maribor -- 9 April 2011 , Ljubljana ) was a Slovenian journalist , essayist , political activist , writer and poet .
Mary Ann Magnin ( 1850 - 1943 ) was a Dutch - born American businesswoman .
Zurab Popkhadze ( Georgian : ზურაბ ფოფხაძე , Russian : Зураб Тамазович Попхадзе ) ( 2 June 1972 -- 15 January 2013 ) was a Georgian professional footballer .
Raphael Ravenscroft ( 4 June 1954 -- 19 October 2014 ) was a British musician , composer and author .
Elizabeth Grimston ( also Grymeston or Grimeston ) ( c. 1563- c. 1603 ) was an English poet .
Pieter de Zeelander ( nickname Kaper ) ( Haarlem , ca 1620 -- Rome , after 1650 ) was a Dutch painter who specialized in seascapes .
Mike Disfarmer ( 1884 - 1959 ) was an American photographer whose portraits of everyday people in rural Arkansas became regarded as art some years after his death .
Andreas Meyer - Hanno ( 18 February 1932 -- 7 September 2006 ) was a German theater and opera director .
George N. Saegmuller ( 1847 - 1934 ) was a German - born American inventor of many astronomical instruments and other mechanical devices .
Robert Lock Graham Irving ( 17 February 1877 -- 10 April 1969 ) , was an English schoolmaster , writer and mountaineer .
Cuthbert Wilfrid Francis Noyce ( 31 December 1917 -- 24 July 1962 ) ( usually known as Wilfrid Noyce ( often misspelt as ' Wilfred ' ) , some sources give third forename as Frank ) was an English mountaineer and author .
Elizabeth Younger whose married name was Elizabeth Finch ( 2 September 1699 -- 24 November 1762 ) , was an actress and dancer .
Henry Nicholas Paint ( 10 April 1830 -- 29 September 1921 ) was a Canadian politician , shipowner and merchant .
Fernand Legros ( French : ( ləɡʁo ) ; 26 January 1931 -- 7 April 1983 ) was an art dealer who , together with his lover Real Lessard , sold the art forgeries of Elmyr de Hory .
Helen Mabel Trevor ( 20 December 1831 -- 3 April 1900 ) was a Northern Irish landscape and genre painter .
Jōchō ( 定朝 ; died 1057 AD ) , also known as Jōchō Busshi , was a Japanese sculptor of the Heian period .
Frank Parker Crosse MC ( 24 October 1897 -- 15 March 1979 ) was a British soldier and Church of England clergyman who became Dean of Grahamstown in South Africa , and was styled The Very Revd Frank Crosse .
Chilakamarti Lakshmi Narasimham ( 26 September 1867 -- 17 June 1946 ) was an Indian playwright , novelist and author of short stories , who wrote in the Telugu language .
Thomas Bevill Peacock ( 21 December 1812 -- 31 May 1882 ) was a cardiologist in London remembered for founding the London Chest Hospital .
Ratip Aşir Acudoğlu ( also known as Ratip Aşir Acudoğu ) ( 1898 - -17 January 1957 ) was a Turkish sculptor .
Henry Cockayne Cust M.A. ( d. 19 May 1861 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1813 - 1861
Gerdeka Hartlevsdotter , or Hartlefsdotter , also called Gerdica ( 1370 - 1438 ) , was a Swedish Bridgettine nun .
Peter Carson ( 3 October 1938 -- 9 January 2013 ) was an English publisher , editor and translator of Russian literature .
Samuel Israel Mulder ( born Amsterdam 20 June 1792 ; died there 29 December 1862 ) was a Dutch - Jewish educationalist .
Maurice E. Kressly ( 1892 - -1963 ) was an American architect practicing in Pennsylvania and central Florida in the middle years of the twentieth century .
Axel Johann Einar Lönnberg ( 24 December 1865 -- 21 November 1942 ) was a Swedish zoologist and conservationist .
Gordon Woodbury ( 1863 - -1924 ) was the United States Assistant Secretary of the Navy from 1920 to 1921 .
He Zhen , also known as Zhou Cheng , Chang Qing , Xue Yu ( 1541 -- 1606 ) was a Chinese artist during the Ming Dynasty , who specialised in carving personal seals .
Ilia Xhokaxhi ( born August 28 , 1948 in Tirana ; died 2007 ) was an Albanian painter , scenographer , and costume designer .
John Almon ( 17 December 1737 -- 12 December 1805 ) was an English journalist and writer on political subjects , notable for his efforts to secure the right to publish reports on the debates in Parliament .
Maria Beatrice of Savoy ( Maria Beatrice Vittoria Giuseppina ; 6 December 1792 -- 15 September 1840 ) was a Princess of Savoy and Duchess of Modena by marriage .
Christian Hoecken ( born in Upper Brabant ; died on the Missouri River , 19 June 1851 ) was a Jesuit missionary of Belgian origin who worked in the United States among the first nations .
Isla Stewart ( 25 August 1856 -- 6 March 1910 ) was an English hospital matron of St Bartholomew 's Hospital in London and a founding member of the Royal British Nurses Association .
John Kyrle ( 22 May 1637 -- 7 November 1724 ) , known as `` the Man of Ross '' , was an English philanthropist , remembered for his time in Ross - on - Wye in Herefordshire .
Dhondup Gyal ( 1953 - -1985 ) is considered the first modern Tibetan poet breaking through traditional Tibetan formalist elements .
Gianni Musy ( 3 August 1931 -- 7 October 2011 ) was an Italian actor and voice actor .
Celina González Zamora ( 16 March 1929 , Jovellanos , Matanzas -- 4 February 2015 ) was a Cuban singer - songwriter , who specialized in `` música campesina '' , traditional music of the Cuban countryside .
Carin Malmlöf - Forssling ( born 1916 , d. 2005 ) was a Swedish organist , choir director and composer .
John Calver ( ca . 1695 -- 12 April 1751 ) was an English clockmaker based in Woodbridge , Suffolk .
Rev. Dr. Hermann Kohlmeyer ( 1814 -- 1883 ) was the rabbi of Congregation Shangarai Chasset in New Orleans , Louisiana .
Sir Richard Lyster ( ca . 1480 -- 14 March 1554 ) was an English judge and Chief Justice of the King 's Bench .
Mary Reynolds ( 10 October 1889 -- 29 August 1974 ) was an Irish politician , farmer and grocer from County Leitrim .
Abdallah bin Alawi was the Sultan ( ? Shirazi ) of and on Anjouan island ( in the Comoros ) from 1816 to 1832 , and then again from 1833 to his death in 1836 .
Kleber Claux ( 22 March 1893-June 1971 ) was a leading anarchist of the early twentieth century and a founder of the first nudist colony in Australia .
Bassel Fleihan ( 10 September 1963 -- 18 April 2005 ; Arabic : باسل فليحان‎ ) was a Lebanese legislator and minister of economy and trade .
Franz Ullrich continued to live in Annweiler am Trifels until his death on the 21 December 1891 .
William Bleloch ( 9 February 1906 Johannesburg -- 20 June 1991 ) was a South African metallurgist noted for developing smelting techniques for the processing of chrome ores .
Juan de Dicastillo ( b. of Spanish parents at Naples , 28 December 1584 ; d. at Ingolstadt , 6 March 1653 ) was a Spanish Jesuit theologian .
Stephen Catterson Smith ( 12 March 1806 -- 30 May 1872 ) was an English - Irish portrait - painter and president of the Royal Hibernian Academy .
Adrian Love ( born 3 August 1944 in York -- 10 March 1999 ) was a British radio presenter , remembered for his Love In The Afternoon show on Radio Two .
Princess Henriette of Liechtenstein ( German : Henriette Maria Norberta , Prinzessin von und zu Liechtenstein ; 6 June 1843 -- 24 December 1931 ) was a Princess of Liechtenstein and member of the Princely House of Liechtenstein .
Saul Tepper ( December 20 , 1899 -- January 1987 ) was an American illustrator and later a popular songwriter .
Thomas Thetcher ( 1737 ? -- 1764 ) , also known simply as The Hampshire Grenadier , was a grenadier in the North Regiment of the Hants Militia .
Arundel Wrighte ( 1804 - -1887 ) was a colonist , first Postmaster of Launceston in Van Diemen 's Land and founder of Box Hill , Victoria .
Charles Allen Clarke ( 1863 - -1935 ) , most widely known as C. Allen Clarke , was an English working - class humorist , novelist , journalist and social investigator from Lancashire .
Roscoe Sarles ( 4 January 1892 -- 17 September 1922 ) was an American racecar driver active in the formative years of auto racing .
Frank Szécsi de Felsőlendva ( Széchy ; died 28 September 1396 ) was a Hungarian nobleman from the influential House of Szécsi .
Guo Shengtong ( 郭聖通 ; died AD 52 ) was an empress during the Eastern Han dynasty .
Lillian Hall - Davis ( 23 June 1898 -- 25 October 1933 ) was an English actress during the silent film era , featured in major roles in English film and a number of German , French and Italian films .
Robert H. Scanlan ( 1914 - 2001 ) was a civil and aeronautical engineer who came to be widely recognized as a leader in the analysis of wind effects on large structures .
Wingfield Cromwell , 2nd Earl of Ardglass , DCL , ( 12 September 1624 -- 3 October 1668 ) was an English nobleman , son of Thomas Cromwell , 1st Earl of Ardglass and Elizabeth Meverell .
Bill Shine , born Wilfred William Dennis Shine , ( 20 October 1911 -- 24 July 1997 ) was a British theatre , film and television actor .
Thomson Hankey ( 1805 -- 13 January 1893 ) was a British merchant , a banker and a Liberal Party politician .
Aubrey Wyatt Tilby , known as A. Wyatt Tilby ( 1 April 1880 -- 1 September 1948 ) was an author , journalist and traveller .
Shamai Davidson ( Hebrew : שמאי דוידסון‎ ; 1926 - -1986 ) was an Israeli professor , psychiatrist and psychoanalyst , who spent 30 years working with Holocaust survivors , trying to understand the nature of their experience .
Vincenzo Ugolini ( ca . 1580 -- 6 May 1638 ) was an Italian composer of the early Baroque era and of the Roman School .
Nicholas Farnham ( or Nicholas of Farnham ; died 1257 ) was a medieval Bishop of Durham .
George Brann ( 23 April 1865 -- 14 June 1954 ) was an English amateur cricketer and footballer who had a long career with Sussex County Cricket Club at the end of the 19th century , and played three matches for the England national football team .
David Funck ( 1648 -- 1699 ? ) was a Czech or German music composer , educator , and performer on several instruments , including violas da gamba , violin , guitar , and clavichord .
Thomas Caulfield Irwin ( 4 May 1823 - 20 February 1892 ) was an Irish poet , writer , and classical scholar .
Samuel Llewelyn Kenrick ( 1847 -- 29 May 1933 ) was a Welsh solicitor who became the founder of the Football Association of Wales and organised the first Welsh international football match against Scotland in 1876 .
Robert Shiels ( also Shiells or Shields ) ( died 1753 ) was an English literary compiler .
Hans Rosenthal ( 2 April 1925 -- 10 February 1987 ) was a radio editor , director , and one of the most popular German radio and television hosts of the 1970s and 1980s .
Queena Stovall ( 20 December 1887 -- 27 June 1980 ) was an American folk artist sometimes called `` The Grandma Moses of Virginia . ''
Aretas Akers - Douglas , 2nd Viscount Chilston GCMG PC ( 17 February 1876 - 25 July 1947 ) , was a British diplomat .
William Strutt RBA , FZS ( 3 July 1825 -- 3 January 1915 ) was an English artist .
Carlo Yvon ( 29 April 1798 in Milan -- 23 December 1854 in Milan ) was an Italian composer , virtuoso oboist and English horn player , and music educator .
Todor Krastev ( Bulgarian : Тодор Кръстев ; 1 June 1945 -- 9 May 2001 ) was a Bulgarian footballer .
Bahram Afzali ( Persian : بهرام افضلی‎‎ ; 1938 - 25 February 1984 ) was the Commander of Iranian Navy from 1980 to 1983 .
Ernst Eduard Taubert ( 25 September 1838 , Regenwalde -- 14 July 1934 ) was a Pomeranian composer , music critic , and music educator .
István Kossa ( 31 March 1904 -- 9 April 1965 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Finance twice : between 1949 - -1950 and between 1956 - 1957 .
Jan Ligthart ( 11 January 1859 - 16 February 1916 ) was a Dutch teacher and philosopher .
Arturo Peyrot ( 1908 - -1993 ) was an Italian artist ; painter and writer .
Tonino Accolla ( 6 April 1949 -- 14 July 2013 ) was an Italian voice actor and actor .
Norman Easedale Crump FRSS ( 10 January 1896 -- 22 January 1964 ) , was a British financial and economic authority and Liberal Party politician .
Marianne - Caroline Hamilton ( 1777 -- 29 July 1861 ) was an Irish artist and memoirist .
Irvine Loudon ( 1 August 1924 -- 7 January 2015 ) was a British doctor , medical historian and artist , and an expert on childbirth fever and maternal mortality .
Fernando Díaz ( floruit 1071 - -1106 ) was a Spanish nobleman and military leader in the Kingdom of León , the most powerful Asturian magnate of the period .
Sir Robert Geffrey ( Robert Geffrye ) ( 1613 - -1703 ) was an English merchant and Lord Mayor of London .
Pandit Ram Kishore Shukla ( Pronounced ( ˈraːm kɪʃoːr ʃʊklaː ) ; Rām Kiśōr Śukla ) ( 4 September 1923 -- 11 December 2003 ) was an Indian politician and an activist for Indian independence .
William Beattie Nesbitt ( May 23 , 1866 -- 1913 ) was an Ontario physician , manufacturer and political figure .
John Cragg ( 1767 -- 17 July 1854 ) was an English ironmaster who ran a foundry in Liverpool , Merseyside , England .
Johann Andreas Schnabl ( 1838 - 1912 ) was born a Pole of German descent , and an entomologist specializing in Diptera .
Henri Van Kerckhove ( 6 September 1926 -- 4 November 1999 ) was a Belgian road cyclist who won a bronze medal at the 1946 World Championships .
Geoffrey Horrocks ( 1932/33 Leicester- 12 September 2012 ) was a British mathematician working on vector bundles , who introduced the Horrocks construction used in the ADHM construction , and the Horrocks--
Rachel , Lady Redgrave ( 28 May 1910 -- 24 May 2003 ) , known primarily by her birth name Rachel Kempson , was an English actress .
Wills Hill , 1st Marquess of Downshire PC ( 30 May 1718 -- 7 October 1793 ) , known as the Viscount Hillsborough from 1742 to 1751 and as the Earl of Hillsborough from 1751 to 1789 , was a British politician of the Georgian era .
Frédéric Cerfberr ( 27 October 1786 in Strasburg -- 18 September 1842 at sea on a voyage from New York to France ) was a French diplomat and a Jew .
Kara Murat Pasha , or Kara Dev Murat Pasha ( Turkish , lit . Black Giant Murat Pasha ; died 1655 ) , was an Ottoman statesman and military officer .
Tarun Bose ( 14 September 1928 -- 8 March 1972 ) was an Indian film actor , active in Bollywood during the 1960s and 1970s .
Saelred of Essex ( also known as Swebert and Selered ) reigned as King of Essex from c. 709 to 746 .
Willem Surenhuis ( Surenhuys , Surenhusius ) ( c.1664 in Rottum - 1729 ) was a Dutch Christian scholar of Hebrew , known for his Latin translation of the Mishnah , the first of the complete work .
Lado Ketskhoveli ( 1877 - -1903 ) was a writer and revolutionary who was one of the first people to introduce Joseph Stalin to Marxism .
Denis Fernand Py ( 1887 - -1949 ) was a French medal artist and engraver that created highly stylized medals with religious themes during his career .
Karen Kotte ( died 1590 ) was a Danish merchant .
Cesar Castellani ( died 2 August 1905 ) was an architect .
Otto - Ernst Ottenbacher ( 18 November 1888 -- 7 January 1975 ) was a highly decorated Generalleutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II who commanded several corps .
Wobogo ( died 1904 ) was the Mogho Naba ( ruler ) of Ouagadougou from 1890 to 1897 , at the time of the French colonial conquest of Upper Volta .
Joseph Ahearne L.R.C.P. , L.R.C.S. , ( 1852 - -1926 ) was a Surgeon - Major for the Queensland colony 's defense force and later to Australian Defense Force .
Anita M. Smith ( full name Anita Miller Smith , October 20 , 1893 -- 1968 ) was an impressionist and regionalist painter most closely associated with Woodstock , New York .
Ambrose Cobbs ( 1603 - abt . 1655 ) was an early Virginia colonist and planter who established the long lasting social and political Cobbs dynasty in the southern states .
Elsa Gramcko ( 9 April 1925 , Puerto Cabello -- 1994 , Caracas ) was a Venezuelan abstract sculptor and painter .
Niu Jingyi ( 钮经义 , 1920 - -1995 ) was a Chinese biochemist .
Moti Abba Jifar II was King of the Gibe Kingdom of Jimma ( r. 1878 - -1932 ) .
Cadwaladr , Cadwallader , or Cadwalader ( Welsh : Cadwaladr ap Cadwallon ) was king of Gwynedd from around AD 655 to 682 .
William Roby ( 1766 - -1830 ) was an English Congregational minister .
Silvio Ranieri ( 1882 -- 1956 ) was an Italian Mandolin virutuoso .
F. Wayne Valley ( 1914 - -1986 ) was an American businessman , philanthropist and football player .
Sir Poynings More , 1st Baronet ( 1606 - -1649 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1624 and 1640 .
Osorio Martínez ( Latin : Osorius Martini ) ( bef . 1108 -- March 1160 ) was a magnate from the Province of León in the Empire of Alfonso VII . He served the emperor militarily throughout his long career , which peaked in 1138 - -41 .
Emrys Hughes ( 10 July 1894 -- 18 October 1969 ) was a British Labour politician , best known for being the biographer and son - in - law of Keir Hardie , the Scottish Labour politician .
Nicholas Bond ( 1540 - -1608 ) was an English churchman and academic , President of Magdalen College , Oxford , from 1590 .
Richard FitzAlan , 10th Earl of Arundel and 8th Earl of Surrey ( c.1306/1313 -- 24 January 1376 ) was an English nobleman and medieval military leader and distinguished admiral .
Sir Thomas Ridell ( died 1652 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at times between 1621 to 1629 .
Willem van der Zaan ( 29 June 1621 -- 17 March 1669 ) was a Dutch Admiral .
Homer Kelley ( 1907 -- 1983 ) was the American author of The Golfing Machine , one of the most comprehensive descriptions of the golf swing .
Xavier Marcel Boulestin ( 1878 -- 20 September 1943 ) was a French chef , restaurateur , and the author of cookery books that popularised French cuisine in the English - speaking world .
George Henry Livens ( 1886 - -1950 ) was a British mathematician best known for his work on electromagnetics , elasticity and thermodynamics .
Gese Wechel ( born in Hamburg , died in Lübeck 1645 ) , was the managing director of the Swedish Post Office , Postverket from 1637 until 1642 .
Bruce Conde ( aka Bruce Alsono Bourbon de Conde , aka Alfonso Yorba ) ( 5 December 1913 -- 19 July 1992 ) was a US Army officer , stamp collector , royal imposter , and a general for Royalist forces during the North Yemen Civil War .
John Brittleton ( 5 May 1906 -- 1982 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Aston Villa .
George Augustine Taylor ( 1 August 1872 -- 20 January 1928 ) was an Australian artist , journalist , and inventor .
Sam McCluskie ( 11 August 1932 - -15 September 1995 ) was a British Labour Party politician and trade unionist .
Rodrigo de Triano ( foaled 27 May 1989 -- 5 August 2014 ) was an English Thoroughbred Champion racehorse .
Alistair Ferguson Ritchie ( 1890 - -1954 ) was a crossword compiler , under the pseudonym Afrit .
Vilhelm Bjerke - Petersen ( December 24 , 1909 -- September 13 , 1957 ) was a Danish painter , writer and art theorist .
Jörg Berger ( 13 October 1944 -- 23 June 2010 ) was a German football manager and player , who last managed Arminia Bielefeld .
