Carl Cohn Haste ( 7 December 1874 -- 4 June 1939 ) was a Danish pianist , organist and composer .
Alwin - Broder Albrecht ( 18 September 1903 -- 1 May 1945 ) was a German naval officer who was one of Adolf Hitler 's adjutants during World War II .
Alexander Crichton of Brunstane , ( died before Dec. 1558 ) , was a Scottish Protestant laird who advocated the murder of Cardinal David Beaton and supported the plan for the marriage of Mary , Queen of Scots and Edward VI of England .
Peter Waterman ( 8 December 1934 -- 16 January 1986 ) was an English boxer and a British and European welterweight champion .
Kelallur Nilakantha Somayaji ( 1444 - -1544 ) ( also referred to as Kelallur Comatiri ) was a major mathematician and astronomer of the Kerala school of astronomy and mathematics .
Peter Gijsbert van Anrooij , better known as Peter van Anrooy ( 13 October 1879 -- 31 December 1954 ) , was a Dutch composer and conductor of classical music .
Saba Raleigh ( 1866 - -1923 ) , born Isabel Ellissen , was an English actress .
Albert Arnz ( 24 January 1832 -- 9 September 1914 ) was a German landscape painter of the Düsseldorf school .
Antonio De Vita ( 10 February 1932 -- 14 January 1998 ) , best known as Tony De Vita , was an Italian composer , conductor , arranger and pianist .
Tiberius Julius Pharsanzes , also known as Pharsanzes ( Greek : Τιβέριος Ἰούλιος Φαρσανζης , flourished 3rd century -- died 254 ) was a prince and Roman Client King of the Bosporan Kingdom .
Bronisława Janowska or Bronisława Anna Waleria Rychter - Janowska ( 13 July 1868 -- 29 September 1953 ) was a Polish realist painter and publisher associated with the Kraków - based Young Poland movement .
Stephen Murray - Smith AM ( 9 September 1922 -- 31 July 1988 ) was an Australian writer , editor and educator .
Charles William Kelsey ( 1877 - -1975 ) was a Canadian artist best known for his stained glass work .
Arnold Pick ( 20 July 1851 -- 4 April 1924 ) was a Jewish Czech neurologist and psychiatrist .
Louisa Ruth Herbert ( 1831 -- 1921 ) was a well - known Victorian - era English stage actress and model for the artist Dante Gabriel Rossetti .
John Asgill ( 25 March 1659 -- 10 November 1738 ) was an eccentric English writer and politician .
Sidkeong Namgyal ( Sikkimese : སྲིད་སཀྱོང་རྣམ་རྒྱལ་ ; Wylie : srid skyong rnam rgyal ) ( 1819 - -1874 ) was king of Sikkim from 1863 to 1874 .
Sir Alexander Reid , 2nd Baronet ( died 5 March 1750 ) was a Scottish laird and politician from Aberdeenshire .
Weldon Champneys ( 1839 - 1892 ) was an English clergyman and rower who twice won Silver Goblets at Henley Royal Regatta .
Peter Rochegune Munch ( in Danish usually referred to as P. Munch ) ( 1870 - -1948 ) was a leading Danish historian and politician .
Thomas Tymme ( or Timme ) ( died 1620 ) was an English clergyman , translator and author .
Lady Catharine Long ( née Walpole ; 1797 -- 30 August 1867 ) was an English novelist and religious writer of the 19th century .
George Edgcumbe , 1st Earl of Mount Edgcumbe , PC ( 3 March 1720 -- 4 February 1795 ) was a British peer , naval officer and politician .
Şükrü Âli Ögel ( 1886 - -1973 ) was a Turkish military officer and the first director of the former Turkish governmental intelligence agency Milli Emniyet Hizmeti ( MAH ) ( National Security Service ) , the predecessor of Milli İstihbarat Teşkilatı ( MİT ) today .
Abu Said Uthman III ( Abu Said Uthman ibn Abi l - Abbas ibn Abi Salim ) ( died 1420 ) was Marinid ruler of Morocco from 19 March 1398 to 1420 , the last effective ruler of that dynasty .
Josiah Parkes ( 1793 - -1871 ) was an English civil engineer , inventor of a deep drainage system .
William Barley ( 1565?--1614 ) was an English bookseller and publisher .
Fet - Mats ( `` Fat Mats '' ) ( real name : Mats Israelsson ) ( died 1677 ) was a `` petrified man '' found in 1719 .
Sir James Kirkpatrick , 8th Baronet ( 22 March 1841 -- 10 November 1899 ) was the 8th Kirkpatrick Baronet of Closeburn , Dumfriesshire .
John Lillywhite ( born 10 November 1826 at Hove , Sussex ; died 27 October 1874 at St Pancras , London ) was an English cricketer and umpire during the game 's roundarm era .
Rafael Gutiérrez Girardot ( Sogamoso , Colombia , 5 May 1928 -- Bonn , Germany , 26 May 2005 ) was a expatriate Colombian philosopher , professor , translator and publisher .
Nawab Sadiq Hussain Qureshi ( July 25 , 1927 -- 24 June 2000 ) was a Pakistani politician who served as both Governor and Chief Minister of Punjab under Zulfikar Ali Bhutto in the 1970s .
Archibald Douglas , 2nd Earl of Forfar , 3rd Earl of Ormond ( 25 May 1692 -- 8 December 1715 ) was a Scottish peer .
Walter Hart ( or Walter Lyhert ; died 24 May 1472 ) was a medieval Bishop of Norwich .
Isaac Hellmuth ( December 14 , 1819 -- 28 May 1901 ) , second Anglican Bishop of the Diocese of Huron , was the founder of Huron University College and the University of Western Ontario , one of Canada 's leading universities .
Bartolomeo Sanvito ( 1435 - -1518 ) was a scribe from Padua in Italy , but trained in Rome .
George John Bennett ( 1800 - -1879 ) was for nearly 40 years a Shakespearian actor on the London stage , notably Covent Garden and Drury Lane .
Ezekiel Baker ( 1758 - -1836 ) was a master gunsmith from Whitechapel , London , who became known for his design of the Baker rifle in 1800 .
Alexandre - Louis Leloir ( 14 March 1843 -- 28 January 1884 ) was a French painter specializing in genre and history paintings .
Colonel Sackville Tufton ( 11 June 1646 -- 30 March 1721 ) was the son of John Tufton , 2nd Earl of Thanet and his second wife Margaret Sackville .
Axel Heiberg ( 16 March 1848 -- 4 September 1932 ) was a Norwegian diplomat , financier and patron , born in Kristiania .
Lanning Roper ( 4 February 1912 -- 22 March 1983 ) was an American landscape architect and writer who studied and lived in England .
Charles Radclyffe ( 3 September 1693 -- 8 December 1746 ) titular 5th Earl of Derwentwater , who claimed the title Fifth Earl of Derwentwater .
Yulian Bromley ( Russian : Юлиа́н Влади́мирович Бромле́й , 21 February 1921 - 4 June 1990 ) was a Soviet Russian anthropologist who gained an international recognition .
Hermann Grab ( 6 May 1903 -- 2 August 1949 ) was a Bohemian German - language writer .
The Most Reverend Michael Courtney ( 5 February 1945 -- 29 December 2003 ) was the Apostolic Nuncio to Burundi and Titular Archbishop of Eanach Dúin Michael Aidan Courtney was born in Summerhill , Nenagh , County Tipperary .
Jean Baptiste Senaillé ( 23 November 1687 -- 15 October 1730 ) was a French born Baroque composer and violin virtuoso .
Louis V , Duke of Bavaria , called the Brandenburger ( May 1315 -- 18 September 1361 ) was Duke of Bavaria and as Louis I also Margrave of Brandenburg and Count of Tyrol .
Supangmung ( reigned 1663 - -1670 ) , also known as Chakradhwaj Singha ( Assamese : স্বৰ্গদেউ চক্ৰধ্বজ সিংহ ) , was an important Ahom king under whom the Ahom kingdom took back Guwahati from the Mughals following the reverses at the hands of Mir Jumla and the Treaty of Ghilajharighat .

Steve Gittins ( 16 August 1963 -- 20 February 2013 ) was a darts player from England .
Reginfrid ( or Ragnfrid ) ( died 814 ) was a co - King of Denmark from 812 , when Hemming I died , to 813 , when he and his brothers were ousted by the sons of a previous king , Gudfred .
Ramon A. Estella ( 1911 -- 1991 ) was a pre - war Philippine movie director and actor .
Daniel Cawdry ( Cawdrey ) ( 1588 - -1664 ) was an English clergyman , member of the Westminster Assembly , and ejected minister of 1662 .
Edmund Falconer ( c.1814 -- 29 September 1879 ) , born Edmund O'Rourke , he was an Irish poet , actor , theatre manager , songwriter and playwright , known for his keen wit and outstanding acting skills .
Alfred John King BSc , ( 14 February 1859 -- 16 March 1920 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician .
Johann Jakob Merlo ( 25 October 1810 -- 27 October 1890 ) was a German historian , antiquarian and poet .
Helen Thornton Geer ( January 7 , 1903 in New Castle , Pennsylvania -- March 1983 in New Jersey ) was a prominent author , professor , and librarian .
Charles Jurine ( 1751 - -1819 ) was a Swiss zoologist who , inspired by a letter by Lazzaro Spallanzani to the Geneva Natural History Society , set about showing that bats used their ears to navigate .
Horace Bell ( December 11 , 1830 -- June 29 , 1918 ) , was active in the American era of 19th century California , especially in the Los Angeles region .
Henry Reginall Underhill , Baron Underhill CBE ( 8 May 1914 -- 12 March 1993 ) , also known as Reg Underhill , was a British party worker and Labour politician .
Domenico Malipiero ( 1428 - -1515 ) was a naval captain from a patrician Venetian family who passed his youth in maritime commerce on his family 's behalf and became a Venetian senator in 1465 .
Henrik Starcke ( 16 April 1899 -- 5 June 1973 ) was a Danish sculptor who created fanciful creatures based on his interest in ancient art .
Lydia Campbell ( November 1 , 1818 -- April 1905 ) was an early diarist in Labrador of English and Inuit descent .
Malcolm Norris ( 1900 - -1967 ) was an influential Canadian Métis leader of the twentieth century and celebrated Aboriginal activist .
Seyyed Ahmad Musavi Hindi ( سید احمد مسوی ہندی ; born circa 1790 , died 1869 ) was a Twelver Shia Muslim scholar .
George Monoux ( born in or before 1465 ; died 1544 ) , born in Walthamstow , Essex , England , was Lord Mayor of London and a local benefactor in Walthamstow .
Gjerasim Qiriazi ( 1858 - -1894 ) was an Albanian Protestant preacher and educator .
Mark James Monk ( 1858 - 1929 ) was an cathedral organist , who served at Truro Cathedral and composer .
Forggus mac Cellaig ( or Fergus mac Cellaig ) ( died 756 ) was a King of Connacht from the Uí Briúin branch of the Connachta .
Rao Dalpat Bundela ( died 14 June 1707 ) was a Rajput king of Datia - Orchha .
Joan Vilar i Costa ( 1889 - -1962 ) was an ecclesiastical writer .
John Stewart , 1st Earl of Lennox ( b. bef . 1430 , d. 8 Jul/11 Sep 1495 ) was known as Lord Darnley and later as the Earl of Lennox .
George Charles Haité ( 8 June 1855 -- 31 March 1924 ) was an English designer , painter , illustrator and writer .
Robert Seton , 1st Earl of Winton ( 1553 -- 22 March 1603 ) was one of the Scottish peers who supported Mary , Queen of Scots .
Charles de l'Aubespine , marquis de Châteauneuf ( 22 February 1580 -- 26 September 1653 ) was a French diplomat and government official .
Annemie Fontana ( 14 December 1925 -- 25 October 2002 ) , born Jacqueline Annemarie Fontana , was a Swiss sculptor and painter .
Reynaldo Dante ( 1920 - -1975 , also known as Roy de Silva ) was a Filipino actor .

Toby Caulfeild , 3rd Baron Caulfeild of Charlemont ( 1621 - -1642 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician .

Joachim von Bertrab survived the war but died near Boitzenburg on 18 July 1922 .
Sir William Dormer ( before 1514 -- 17 May 1575 ) was a Tudor knight , captain and politician .

Antonín Fivébr ( 22 November 1888 -- 26 February 1973 ) was a Czech footballer and manager of clubs such as Valencia , Spartak Moscow , and Brescia .
Murali Kuttan ( Malayalam : മുരളി കുട്ടന്‍ ) ( 1953 ? -- 19 December 2010 ) was an Indian track and field athlete who represented the country as a sprinter on several occasions .
Frederick of Pettorano ( c. 1212/3 -- after 1240 ) was the eldest illegitimate son of Frederick II , king of Sicily and Germany .
Rabbi Eliezer Papo ( 1785 - -1828 ) was the rabbi of the community of Silistra in Bulgaria ( then part of the Ottoman Empire ) .
James Priddey , RBSA , PPRBSA , FRSA , ( April 19 , 1916 -- December 1980 ) was an English painter , printmaker , illustrator and member of the Royal Birmingham Society of Artists .
Damian Dalassenos ( Greek : Δαμιανός Δαλασσηνός ; ca . 940 -- 19 July 998 ) was a Byzantine aristocrat and the first known member of the Dalassenos noble family .
Karl Josef Becker S.J. ( 18 April 1928 -- 10 February 2015 ) was a German Catholic theologian and consultor for the Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith since 15 September 1977 .
Frederick Cecil Banes - Walker ( 19 June 1888 -- 9 May 1915 ) was an English first - class cricketer who played five matches for Somerset County Cricket Club .
Kapitanlieutenant Erich Giese ( 22 June 1887 -- 5 June 1917 ) was a German naval officer killed action during World War I. Giese was killed in Action of 5 June 1917 against Royal Navy warships aboard the torpedo boat S20 .
Ludovik Mifsud Tommasi ( 1796 - 1879 ) , was a priest and educator , and also author of short poems and short prayers .
Smoky Dawson AM MBE ( 19 March 1913 -- 13 February 2008 ) born as Herbert `` Herb '' Henry Brown , was an Australian country music performer , radio star , entertainer , and icon .
Jane Soames ( 1900 - 1988 ) , also known as Jane Soames Nickerson , was a British - born author , translator , and historian .
Philip Mayne ( 22 November 1899 -- 9 April 2007 ) is thought to have been the last surviving British officer of the First World War .
Sir Richard Clough ( c. 1530 - -1570 ) , known by his Welsh contemporaries as Rhisiart Clwch , was a merchant from Denbigh , north - east Wales , and an agent of Queen Elizabeth I of England .
Safar Iranpak ( 23 December 1947 -- 30 January 2009 ) was an Iranian football striker who played for Persepolis and the Iran national football team .
Yaltah Menuhin ( 7 October 1921 -- 9 June 2001 ) was an American - born British pianist , artist and poet .
Elodie Lawton Mijatović ( also spelled Mijatovics and Mijatovich , 1825 - 13 December 1908 ) was a British author who lived in Boston in the 1850s , where she was an advocate of the abolitionist movement .
Henry Crook ( born 1802 at Bingham , Nottinghamshire ; died 17 August 1886 at Bingham ) was an English cricketer who was associated with Nottingham Cricket Club and made his first - class debut in 1827 .
Sir Humphrey May ( 1573 -- 9 June 1630 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1605 and 1629 .
Albert Lybrock ( 1827 - -1886 ) was a German - born architect in the United States .
The Most Reverend Cornelius Denvir D.D. ( 1791 - -1865 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic Prelate , mathematician , natural philosopher ( physicist ) and former Lord Bishop of Down and Connor .
Edwin Pemberton ( 20 June 1908 -- 4 November 1989 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Irwin Foster Hilliard ( February 2 , 1863 -- November / December 1948 ) was an Ontario lawyer and political figure .
Augustus , Duke of Saxe - Gotha - Altenburg ( full name : Emil Leopold August ) ( 23 November 1772 -- 17 May 1822 ) , was a Duke of Saxe - Gotha - Altenburg , and the author of one of the first modern novels to treat of same - sex love .
Vera Misevich ( Ukrainian : Віра Місевич ; 10 April 1945 -- 4 March 1995 ) was an equestrian from Ukraine and Olympic champion .
Mary Anne à Beckett ( 29 April 1815 -- 11 December 1863 ) was an English composer , primarily known for opera .
Lieutenant - Colonel Norman Coates M.C. ( 27 April 1890 -- 21 March 1966 ) was a British army officer , School Head Master , and briefly a Conservative politician .
Joe Paton ( 21 August 1878 -- 21 August 1952 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Miles W. Casteel ( December 30 , 1895 -- March 1977 ) was an American football coach .
Karl Wilhelm Scheibler ( Polish : Karol Scheibler , 1 September 1820 -- 13 April 1881 ) was a German - born Polish industrialist , businessman and textile manufacturer .
Adnan Ersöz ( 1917 , Sarıyer - 13 October 1991 , Istanbul ) was a retired Turkish general , serving as Army General 1973 to 1977 .
Giuseppe Barattolo ( 1882 - 1949 ) was an Italian lawyer , politician and film producer .
Frederick Grant Gleason ( born 17 December 1848 in Middletown , Connecticut - died Chicago , 6 December 1903 ) was an American composer , and director of the Chicago Conservatory from 1900 - 1903 .
Reginald Somerset Ward ( 28 January 1881 - 9 July 1962 ) was an English Anglican priest , author and spiritual director .
Ruby Levick ( 1871 or 1872 - -1940 ) was a Welsh sculptor and medallist who had many of her works exhibited at the Royal Academy .
William Byrd ( /bɜːrd/ ; birth date variously given as c.1539/40 or 1543 -- 4 July 1623 , by the Julian calendar , 14 July 1623 , by the Gregorian calendar ) was an English composer of the Renaissance .
Dora Elizabeth Burchill SRN , RM , TC , OAM ( 4 January 1904 -- 3 December 2003 ) was an Australian nurse , philanthropist and author .
Efrén Rebolledo ( 1877 - 1929 ) was a Mexican poet and lawyer .
Maha Chakkraphat died one month into the siege in January 1569 .
Judaeus Bohemus Abraham ( died 1533 ) was a Czech / Polish tax collector , banker and royal factor .
Hans Christian Ulrik Midelfart ( 22 July 1772 -- 1 December 1823 ) was a Norwegian Lutheran minister who served as a representative at the Norwegian Constitutional Assembly in 1814 .
Alberto Santos - Dumont ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( awˈbɛʁtu ˈsɐ̃tuz duˈmõ ) ; 20 July 1873 -- 23 July 1932 ) was a Brazilian aviation pioneer .
Thomas Howard , 14th Earl of Suffolk , 7th Earl of Berkshire ( 11 June 1721 -- 23 February 1783 ) was a British peer , styled Hon . Thomas Howard until 1779 .
Fabio Cristofari ( died 1689 ) was an Italian Baroque painter and mosaicist active in Rome .
Mary Edith Durham ( 8 December 1863 -- 15 November 1944 ) was a British traveller , artist and writer who became famous for her anthropological accounts of life in Albania in the early 20th century .
Johann Dubez ( 1828 -- 27 October 1891 ) was an Austrian virtuoso on several instruments mandolin , guitar , harp , and zither as well as a composer .
Napoleon Manuel Kheil ( 19 October 1849 , Prague , Bohemia -- 1 November 1923 Prague , Czechoslovakia ) was a Czech zoologist and entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera and Orthoptera .
William Goring ( 5 December 1811 -- 9 May 1849 ) was an English cricketer who played first class cricket for Sussex between 1833 and 1835 .
Pierre Joseph Édouard Deperthes ( Édouard Deperthes ) ( 31 July 1833 - -23 July 1898 ) was a French architect .
Ernestine of Sayn - Wittgenstein ( Ernestine Salentine ; 23 April 1626 -- 13 October 1661 ) , was a German noblewoman member of the House of Sponheim , Sovereign Countess of Sayn - Wittgenstein - Sayn - Hachenburg and by marriage Countess of Manderscheid - Blankenheim .
Pedro de Artajona or Pedro de París ( b. ? - d. 13 June , 1193 , Pamplona ) was a Spanish noble of the House of Artajona in the service of the Kingdom of Navarre .
Louis Kentner ( 19 July 1905 -- 23 September 1987 ) was a Hungarian , later British , pianist who excelled in the works of Chopin and Liszt , as well as the Hungarian repertoire .
Emmy Wehlen ( 1887 - -1977 ) was a German - born Edwardian musical comedy and silent film actress who vanished from the public eye while in her early thirties .
Andres Molinary ( 1847 - -1915 ) was an artist , art teacher , restorer and photographer who painted for most of his career in New Orleans , Louisiana .
Herbert Heslip ( 1913 in Ballinaskeagh , near Banbridge , County Down - 1992 ) was a Northern Irish politician with the Ulster Unionist Party ( UUP ) .
Henry Garrett Newland ( 1804 - -1860 ) was an English cleric and author , a supporter of the Tractarian movement .
Albert Porte ( 19 January 1906 -- 1986 ) was an Americo - Liberian political journalist and dissident who was the editor of the Crozerville Observer .
Major General Sir Harry Barron KCMG CVO ( 11 August 1847 -- 27 March 1921 ) was Governor of Tasmania from 1909 to 1913 , and Governor of Western Australia from 1913 to 1917 .
Gennaro Greco ( 1663 - -1714 ) , also known as `` Il Mascacotta '' , was an Italian veduta painter .
Lola Almudevar ( London , 28 June 1978 -- La Paz , 25 November 2007 ) was a British journalist and news reporter .
Alfred Görnemann ( 1 September 1877 -- 11 October 1903 ) was a German cyclist who had his best achievements in motor - paced racing .
Dr. Gerhardus Petrus Christiaan de Kock ( 14 February 1926 , Cape Town -- 7 August 1989 , Pretoria ) was the sixth Governor of the South African Reserve Bank .
Soviet Star ( 20 April 1984 -- 7 October 2014 ) was an American - bred French - trained Thoroughbred racehorse and sire .
Marmaduke Stalkartt ( 1750 - 24 September 1805 ) was an English naval architect .
Arthur Bliss Lane ( 16 June 1894 -- 12 August 1956 ) was a United States diplomat who served in Latin America and Europe .
Thomas Foran ( died 18 March 1951 ) was an Irish Labour Party politician and trade union official .
Albert Franz Doppler ( 16 October 1821 -- 27 July 1883 ) , was a flute virtuoso and a composer best known for his flute music .
Captain Arthur Jaques ( 7 March 1888 -- 27 September 1915 ) was an English cricketer .
Yoryi Morel ( born Jorge Octavio Morel Tavares ) ( 1906 - -1979 ) was a painter from the Dominican Republic .
James Douglas , 4th Earl of Morton ( c. 1516 -- 2 June 1581 , aged 65 ) was the last of the four regents of Scotland during the minority of King James VI .
Victor Perlo ( 1912 - -1999 ) was a Marxist economist , government functionary , and a longtime member of the governing National Committee of the Communist Party USA .
William of Nassyngton ( died 1354 ) was an English clerical administrator and translator from Nassington in Northamptonshire .
James Woods Gyle ( died 1935 ) was an Independent Unionist politician in Northern Ireland , member of the Parliament of Northern Ireland .
Sextus Julius Frontinus ( c. 40 -- 103 AD ) was one of the most distinguished Roman senators of the late 1st century AD .
Luke Greenwood ( 13 July 1834 -- 1 November 1909 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played 48 matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club from 1861 to 1874 .
Enrico Alberto d'Albertis ( 23 March 1846 - 3 March 1932 ) was an Italian navigator , writer , philologist , ethnologist and philanthropist .
Don Juan Cano de Saavedra ( ca . 1502 - -1572 ) was a Spanish conquistador from Cáceres in Extremadura .
Indu Prakash Singh ( I. P. Singh ; 23 July 1931 -- 16 August 2002 ) was an Indian philosopher , economist , politician , scholar , author and former diplomat with the Indian Foreign Service .
Colonel John Lowther du Plat Taylor CB VD ( 1829 -- 5 March 1904 ) was the founder of the Army Post Office Corps and the Post Office Rifles .
Neville Kennard ( 1900 - 30 December 1963 ) was a twentieth century variety entertainer from England , most active in the 1920s , 1930s and 1940s .
Sir Charles Whetham ( 1812 - 4 September 1885 ) was a businessman and politician who served as Lord Mayor of London in 1878 - 1879 .
Einar Hildrum ( 10 January 1902 -- 31 January 1991 ) was a Norwegian horticulturalist .
Sydney Chedgzoy ( 17 February 1911 -- 1983 ) was an English professional association footballer who played as a winger for a number of Football League and non - league clubs in the 1930s .
Helvi Juvonen ( 5 November 1919 , Iisalmi , Northern Savonia - 1 October 1959 ) was a Finnish writer and recipient of the Eino Leino Prize in 1957 .
Ashwini Kumar Dutta ( Bengali : অশ্বিনীকুমার দত্ত ) ( 25 January 1856 -- 7 November 1923 ) was a Bengali educationist , philanthropist , social reformer and patriot .
Alfred William Wilcock ( 1887 -- 1953 ) was an cathedral organist , who served in Derby Cathedral and Exeter Cathedral .
Rose Marie McCoy died at her home in Champaign , Illinois , on 20 January 2015 at the age of 92 .
Primo Feliciano Velázquez Rodríguez ( 6 June 1860 -- 19 June 1953 ) was a Mexican journalist , attorney and historian who specialized in regional history .
John Ovens ( 1788 -- 7 December 1825 ) was an Irish - born soldier , civil engineer and explorer of Australia .
Rose Knox , née Markward , aka Mrs Charles B. Knox ( November 18 , 1857 -- 1950 ) was an American businesswoman , who ran the Knox Gelatin Factory in Johnstown , New York , USA , after her husband died .
Archibald Scott Couper ( 31 March 1831 -- 11 March 1892 ) was a Scottish chemist who proposed an early theory of chemical structure and bonding .
Bernardo Daddi ( c. 1280 -- 1348 ) was an early Italian Renaissance painter and apprentice of Giotto .
Villayil Raman Gopala Pillai ( 1915 - 1981 ) , better known as V. R. Gopala Pillai , was a Singaporean novelist writing in Malayalam under the nom de plume G.P. Njekkad , after his natal village in Kerala .
Ed Balducci ( 1906 -- 1988 ) is often named as the creator of the `` Balducci levitation '' , which has been popularized by magician David Blaine .
Margaret McLean ( née Arnot ) ( 7 April 1845 -- 14 February 1923 ) was a Scottish Australian temperance and women 's rights advocate .
Yiorgos Theotokas ( Greek : Γιώργος Θεοτοκάς ) , formally Georgios Theotokas ( Γεώργιος Θεοτοκάς ; 27 April 1906 -- 30 October 1966 ) , was a Greek novelist .
Kamila Skolimowska ( 4 November 1982 -- 18 February 2009 ) was a Polish hammer thrower .
Jerzy Browkin ( 5 November 1934 -- 23 November 2015 ) was a Polish mathematician , studying mainly algebraic number theory .
Ferik İbrahim Pasha ( 1815 , Istanbul - 1891 , Üsküdar ) was a Turkish painter ; one of the first to produce Western - style oil paintings .
Alexandre Dubuque , also Alexander and Dubuc ( Russian : Алекса́ндр Ива́нович Дюбю́к ; Aleksandr Ivanovich Diubiuk ; 3 March ( O.S. 20 February ) 1812 -- 8 January 1898 ( O.S. 27 December 1897 ) ) , was a 19th - century Russian pianist , composer and teacher of French descent .
Alfonso Marconi ( 1865 -- 1936 ) was an Italian businessman and collector of stringed instruments , most famous for assisting his younger brother Guglielmo Marconi in his pioneering work on long - distance radio transmission
Nong Van Den , later known as Kim Đồng , ( 1929 - -1943 ) , was a Nung ethnic minority boy who fought with the Vietnamese resistance against the French .
Walter Barefoote ( also Barefoot , fl . 1655 -- d. 1688 ) was colonist and deputy governor of the Province of New Hampshire .
Sir Thomas Dyke , 1st Baronet ( c. 1650 - 31 October 1706 ) was an English Tory politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1685 and 1698 .
Ganesh Vasudeo Joshi ( Marathi : गणेश वासुदेव जोशी ) ( 20 July 1828 - 25 July 1880 ) was a lawyer , social reformer , and political activist .
Benjamin Nottingham Webster ( 3 September 1797 - 3 July 1882 ) was an English actor - manager and dramatist .
Paulus Svendsen ( 17 April 1904 -- 1989 ) was a Norwegian historian of literature and ideas .
Tomasz Szadek ( 1550 -- 1612 ) was a Polish composer , singer , and cleric of the late Renaissance .
George Stacey Gibson FLS ( 20 July 1818 -- 11 April 1883 ) , was a British banker , botanist and philanthropist .
Lady Jane Grey ( 1536/1537 -- 12 February 1554 ) , also known as Lady Jane Dudley or the Nine Day Queen , was an English noblewoman and de facto monarch of England from 10 July until 19 July 1553 .
Jules Barthoux or Jules Couyat - Barthoux ( 1881 - 1965 ) was a French geologist and archaeologist born in 1881 .
Kate Denin ( 1837 Philadelphia -- 5 February 1907 New York City ) was a 19th - century United States stage actress .
Claude Victor de Boissieu ( 28 November 1784 - 23 November 1868 ) was a French artist and local politician .
Yisrael Alter , ( Polish : Izrael Alter , Hebrew : ישראל אלתר ; October 1895 -- 20 February 1977 ) , also known as the Beis Yisroel after the works he authored , was the fifth Rebbe of the Hasidic dynasty of Ger , a position he held from 1948 until 1977 .
Babu Parmanand ( 10 August 1932 -- 24 April 2008 , Jammu ) was an Indian politician and the governor of Haryana from 19 June 1999 to 2 July 2004 .
David Dolben ( 1581 - -1633 ) was a Welsh bishop of Bangor .
Tomás de Suría ( 1761 - -1844 ) was a Spanish artist and explorer .
Katerina Gogou ( Greek : Κατερίνα Γώγου ; 1 June 1940 -- 3 October 1993 ) was a Greek poet , author and actress .
Ellen Francis Mason ( June 24 , 1846 -- 1930 ) was a New England author , civic leader , trustee , and philanthropist .
John Augustus Atkinson ( 1775 - -1833 ) was an English artist , engraver and watercolourist .
Avraham Givelber ( Hebrew : אברהם גיבלבר‎ , born 23 March 1910 , died 2 August 2002 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment between 1974 and 1977 .
Rashad al - Shawwa ( Arabic : رشاد الشوا‎ ) ( 1909 - 28 September 1988 ) was the Palestinian mayor of Gaza for eleven years from 1971 to 1982 .
Franz Woepcke ( May 6 , 1826 , -- March 25 , 1864 ) was an historian , Orientalist and mathematician .
Moriz Seeler ( 1 March 1896 -- after 15 August 1942 ) was a German poet , writer , film producer , and man of the theatre .
Axel Klinckowström ( 1867 - -1936 ) was a Swedish baron , zoologist , Arctic and Antarctic explorer , fictional writer and memoirist .
William Bence Jones ( 1812 - -22 June 1882 ) was an Anglo - Irish agriculturist .
Thomas Lupset ( c.1495 - -1530 ) was an English churchman and humanist scholar .
Rev Thomas Streatfeild MA , FSA ( 5 January 1777 -- 17 May 1848 ) was a renowned antiquarian and churchman in the early 19th century descended from the historic Streatfeild family .
Minoru Kawabata ( 22 May 1911 -- 29 June 2001 ) Japanese artist , whose works comprise Abstract Expressionist , Color field paintings .
Sir Benjamin Tichborne , 1st Baronet ( c. 1540 - 1629 ) was an English landowner , courtier and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1588 and 1593 .
Maria Withoos ( 1663 - -after 1699 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter and the daughter of Mathias Withoos and sister of the painters Alida , Johannes , Frans and Pieter .
Sir Vandeleur Molyneux Grayburn ( 28 July 1881 -- 21 August 1943 ) was the chief manager of the Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation from 1930 to 1943 .
Goran Gogić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Горан Гогић , 24 April 1986 -- 3 July 2015 ) was a Serbian footballer .
Cecil Dick ( Degadoga , 1915 - -1992 ) was a well - known Cherokee artist often referred to as `` the Father of Cherokee Traditional Art '' .
Taya Zinkin ( 1918 - 2003 ) was a prominent English journalist and author .
Richard Shelley ( d. in Marshalsea prison , London , probably in February or March , 1586 ) was an English recusant who presented to Elizabeth I of England , or her Parliament , a petition drawn up to request greater religious tolerance for Roman Catholics .
Bindu of Bukhara was Bukhar Khudah ( king of Bukhara ) from an unknown date to 681 .
Mademoiselle Mars retired following 1841 and died in Paris on 20 March 1847 .
Henry Banister ( c. 1538 - -1628 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1614 and in 1625 .
André Bourgeois ( 4 March 1928 -- 18 October 2015 ) was a Belgian politician who was the Minister of Agriculture between 1992 and 1995 .
Richard Tufton , 5th Earl of Thanet ( 30 May 1640 or 1641 -- 8 March 1684 ) , styled The Honourable Richard Tufton until 1680 , was an English nobleman .
Sándor Simonyi - Semadam ( 23 March 1864 -- 4 June 1946 ) was a Hungarian politician who served as prime minister for a few months in 1920 .
Michael Montague , Baron Montague of Oxford , CBE ( 10 March 1932 -- 5 November 1999 ) was a British businessman and politician .
Hermann Boerner , also written `` Börner '' ( 11 July 1906 -- 3 June 1982 ) was a German mathematician who worked on variation calculus , complex analysis , and group representation theory .
Heron Carvic ( 21 January 1913 -- 9 February 1980 ) was a British actor and writer who provided the voice for Gandalf in the BBC Radio version of The Hobbit , and played Caiaphas the High Priest every time the play cycle The Man Born to be King was broadcast .
Albert Lindegger or Lindi ( 14 September 1904 -- 14 October 1991 ) was a Swiss painter and illustrator , best known as a political satirist .
David Richard Seaborne Davies ( 26 June 1904 -- 26 October 1984 ) was a Welsh law teacher who served briefly as a Liberal Party Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
Georges Scelle ( 19 March 1878 Avranches ( Manche ) - 8 January 1961 ) was an international jurist and member of the United Nations International Law Commission .
James Henry Dalziel , 1st Baron Dalziel of Kirkcaldy PC ( 24 April 1868 -- 15 July 1935 ) , known as Sir Henry Dalziel , Bt , between 1918 and 1921 , was a British newspaper proprietor , Liberal politician and supporter of David Lloyd George .
Sir Thomas Peirson Frank ( 1881 - -1951 ) was a British civil engineer and surveyor .
Laurence Oliphant , 1st Lord Oliphant ( c. 1434 -- 1498 ) was a Scottish peer .
High Chaparral ( 1 March 1999 -- 21 December 2014 ) was an Irish Thoroughbred racehorse and sire .
Donald Hamilton Fraser RA ( 30 July 1929 , London -- 2 September 2009 ) , is famed for his abstract landscape paintings .
Alexandru Moghioroș ( Hungarian : Mogyorós Sándor ; 1911 - -1969 ) was a Romanian communist activist and politician .
Zhu Yuyue ( Chinese : 朱聿𨮁 ; pinyin : Zhū Yùyuè ; died 1647 ) , the Prince of Tang ( 唐王 ) reigned as the Shaowu Emperor ( 紹武 ) of the Southern Ming dynasty from 1646 - 1647 .
Henry Pierce Bone ( 6 Nov. 1779 -- 21 Oct. 1855 ) was an English enamel painter .
Alf Moore ( 3 August 1872 -- 15 July 1950 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Charles William Frederick Field ( December 1879 -- 1949 ) , known as Oakey Field , was an English professional footballer who played as an inside left or outside left for Sheffield United and Small Heath ( later renamed Birmingham ) in the Football League .
Josef Hilgers ( 9 September 1858 Kückhoven , - 25 January 1918 , the Emmerich Bonifatiushaus , the academic centre for the diocese of Fulda ) was a German Jesuit who wrote on theological and ascetical matters .
Chen Shuda ( died 635 ) , courtesy name Zicong , formally Duke Zhong of Jiang , was an imperial prince of the Chen dynasty , who , after the destruction of Chen , served as an official under the Sui and Tang dynasties , becoming a chancellor during the reigns of the Tang emperors Gaozu and Taizong .
Pat Upton ( 1 September 1944 -- 22 February 1999 ) was an Irish Labour Party politician and veterinarian .
Sir Mark Sykes , 1st Baronet ( 9 May 1711 - 14 September 1783 ) was a priest in the Church of England , Rector of Roos in the East Riding of Yorkshire .
John Arthur Ruskin Munro ( 1864 - -1944 ) was the Rector of Lincoln College , Oxford .
Aju ( or Achu ) ( 1227 - -1287 ) was a general and chancellor of the Mongol Empire and the Yuan Dynasty .
John Callagher ( 3 April 1898 -- 25 January 1980 ) was a Scottish professional footballer who played at centre half for various clubs in the 1920s .
Ebba d'Aubert , née Bergström ( 1819 - -1860 ) was a Swedish concert pianist .
Robert Carr Brackenbury ( 28 May 1752 -- 11 August 1818 ) was born in 1752 at Panton House , near Wragby , Lincolnshire .
Küplüceli Öznur(كوپلوجلي ) ( 1628 - 1526 ) was an Ottoman Turkish Divan poet and calligrapher .
Arthur Edmund Grimshaw ( 1868 - -1913 ) was an artist , composer , organist and conductor .
Joseph LaFlesche , also known as E - sta - mah - za or Iron Eye ( 1822 - -1888 ) , was the last recognized head chief of the Omaha tribe of Native Americans who was selected according to the traditional tribal rituals .
Frank Sydney Greenop ( 12 March 1913 -- 15 June 1975 ) was an Australian journalist , editor , linguist , poet and author .
Captain Robert St Leger Fowler MC ( 7 April 1891 -- 13 June 1925 ) was an Irish cricketer , regarded as the best Irish cricketer not to have represented Ireland itself .
Cornelis de Vries ( 16 August 1740 , Koog aan de Zaan -- 21 November 1812 , Haarlem ) , was a Mennonite minister .
Nathaniel Bowman ( 1608 - -1682 ) was the first Bowman immigrant to be among the earliest settlers of the Massachusetts Bay colony .
Major General John Walter Graham Tulloch CB ( 2 November 1861 -- 9 May 1934 ) was a British soldier and diplomat who served with the Indian Army and other British army forces in Africa and Asia .
Fathi Eljahmi ( Arabic : فتحي الجهمي‎ ) ( 4 April 1941 -- 21 May 2009 ) was Libya 's `` most prominent democratic dissident '' for three decades up until his death , and received significant international attention .
Fletcher Steele ( June 7 , 1885 - July 16 , 1971 ) was an American landscape architect credited with designing and creating over 700 gardens from 1915 to the time of his death .
Brenda Pye ( 29 November 1907 -- 26 April 2005 ) , also known by her earlier married name of Brenda Landon or her maiden name of Brenda Capron , was an English portrait painter and landscape artist .
Colonel Eberhard Finckh ( 7 November 1899 - 30 August 1944 ) was a German army officer who was a colonel on the general staff of the German army , a longtime opponent of nazism and a member of the German resistance to Adolf Hitler 's regime .
Louis Chéron ( 2 September 1660 - 26 May 1725 ) was a French painter , illustrator and art tutor .
Ioannis Kefalogiannis ( Greek : Ιωάννης Κεφαλογιάννης ; 6 December 1933 -- 20 January 2012 ) was a Greek politician who served as a Member of Parliament from 1958 to 1964 , and again from 1974 to 2004 .
Guy Coburn Robson ( 1888 - 1945 ) was a British zoologist , specializing in Mollusca , who first named and described Mesonychoteuthis hamiltoni , the Colossal Squid .
Berthe Meijer ( 21 April 1938 -- 10 July 2012 ) was a Holocaust survivor and author .
Herman Rosenthal ( October 6 , 1843 -- 1917 ) was an American author , editor , and librarian .
Marguerite Jacquelin ( 1850s -- 1 February 1941 ) was a French flower painter .
Sherard Osborn Cowper - Coles ( 8 October 1866 - 9 September 1936 ) was a British metallurgist , and inventor of the sherardising process of galvanization .
Anthony Bushby Bacon ( also known as Anthony Bushby or Anthony Smith or , occasionally , Anthony Bacon II ; and , as a child , William Addison ) ( 1772 - 11 August 1827 ) was a British industrialist turned landed gentleman .
Amalia of Solms - Braunfels ( 31 August 1602 , Braunfels -- 8 September 1675 ) , was a regent of Orange - Nassau .
Alfred E. Treibs ( 1899 -- 1983 ) was a German organic chemist who is credited with founding the area of organic geochemistry .
George Annand ( c.1798 -- 9 January 1856 ) was a politician in colonial Victoria ( Australia ) , a member of the Victorian Legislative Council .
Elizabeth of Doberschütz , ( or Dobschütz ) née von Strantz ( died : 17 December 1591 in Stettin , Pomerania ) ( modern Szczecin ) was beheaded as a witch on the Hay Market in Stettin and burned on the outskirts of the city
Richard Bulkeley , 3rd Viscount Bulkeley ( c. 1658 -- 9 August 1704 ) was a Welsh politician and peer .
Robert de Ho ( c. 1140 - 1210 ) was a twelfth century writer of Anglo - Norman literature known for Enseignements Trebor .
Horace Hodges ( 1865 - -1951 ) was a British film actor and writer .
Mihal Zallari ( 1896 - -1976 ) was an Albanian historian , politician , journalist and poet .
William de Warenne , 5th Earl of Surrey ( died 27 May 1240 ) was the son of Hamelin de Warenne and Isabel , daughter of William de Warenne , 3rd Earl of Surrey .
Johann Koehnken ( born September 14 , 1819 - 1897 ) was an American organ builder in Cincinnati , Ohio who worked under Matthias Schwab ( 1808 - 1862 ) and with Gallus Grimm ( 1827 - 1897 ) .
Alan Deyermond FBA ( 24 February 1932 -- 19 September 2009 ) was a British professor of Medieval Spanish Literature and Hispanist .
Patrick Bashford ( 1929 - 2011 ) was a Polish - born professor of classical guitar at the Royal College of Music , Vogue model , and familiar face of the 1950s & 60s .
Hans Hamilton ( ca . 1758 -- December 1822 ) was an Anglo - Irish Member of Parliament .
Susanna Drury , later Susanna Warter ( c. 1698 -- c. 1770 ) was an Irish painter .
Johannes de Bosch ( 1713 - -1785 ) was a Dutch painter , engraver and draughtsman .
George Parker , 4th Earl of Macclesfield PC ( 24 February 1755 -- 20 March 1842 ) , styled Viscount Parker between 1764 and 1795 , was a British peer and politician .
Axel Maurer ( 12 April 1866 -- 1925 ) was a Norwegian stagewriter , editor and theatre director .
Blessed Thomas Percy , 7th Earl of Northumberland , 1st Baron Percy , KG ( 1528 -- 22 August 1572 ) , led the Rising of the North and was executed for treason .
Munangabum ( ? - 1846 ) was an influential clan head of the Liarga balug and Spiritual Leader or neyerneyemeet of the Dja Dja Wurrung people in central Victoria , Australia .
Margaret Ann Courtney ( 1834 - -1920 ) was an author resident in Penzance , Cornwall , UK in the late 19th century .
Fei Yimin ( 1908 - -1988 ) was the managing director of the pro - Beijing Tai Kung Pao .
Frederick Bogue Noyes ( 1872 - -1961 ) was an American dentist .
Albert Kingsbury ( 23 December 1863 -- 28 July 1943 ) was an American engineer , inventor and entrepreneur .
Henry Pitkin ( 2 January 1811 -- 18 September 1846 ) was a silversmith and watchmaker of Hartford , Connecticut .
Louis - Charles - Auguste Hébert ( 31 Dec 1763 - 3 Oct 1836 ) was a missionary of Paris Foreign Missions Society and was the Vicar Apostolic of Madurai and Coromandel Coast from 8 July 1836 until his death on 3 Oct 1836 .
Frank Hammond ( died 2004 ) was an author of Christian related books , particularly on deliverance ministry .
William McCombie ( 1805 -- 1 February 1880 ) , was a Scottish cattle breeder and agriculturist ; he was also known as `` the grazier king '' or the `` king of graziers '' .
Antoine François Desrues ( 1744 - -1777 ) was a French poisoner .
William Lugg ( 4 June 1852 -- 5 December 1939 ) was an English actor and singer of the late Victorian and Edwardian eras .
Valerio De Los Benidos ( 1905 - -1975 ) was a Cuban activist who was involved in preaching to his local community .
Wayne Cochran ( born 1939 , Thomaston , Georgia , United States ) is an American soul singer , known for his outlandish outfits and white pompadour hairstyle , inspired by Johnny and Edgar Winter .
John Christian Bullitt ( 1824 - -1902 ) was a prominent lawyer and civic figure in the city of Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
Roblan Frank Armitage ( 5 September 1924 -- 4 January 2016 ) was an Australian - born American painter and muralist , known for painting the backgrounds of several classic animated Disney films , designing areas of and painting murals for Walt Disney World and Tokyo DisneySea , and his biomedical visualization artwork .
Povl Christensen ( 2 June 1909 -- 9 July 1977 ) was a Danish painter and illustrator who in the early 1930s joined the artists ' colony in northwestern Zealand known as the Odsherred Painters .
James Cecil , 3rd Earl of Salisbury , KG PC ( 1648 -- June 1683 ) , known as Viscount Cranborne from 1660 to 1668 , was an English nobleman .
Datta Naik ( 12 December 1927 -- 30 December 1987 ) , also credited as N. Dutta , is a Hindi film music director .
Rudolf Franz Lehnert ( * 13 July 1878 -- † 16 . January 1948 ) was a photographer .
Juan López Hita ( 5 September 1944 -- 11 June 2014 ) was a Spanish professional footballer who played most of his career in Sevilla FC .
Richard Worsam Meade II ( 1807 -- 16 April 1870 ) ( also called Richard Worsam Meade , Sr . , in relation to his son , Rear Admiral Richard Worsam Meade III ) was an officer in the United States Navy .
Maria Aletta Hulshoff , pen - name `` Mietje '' , ( 30 July 1781 in Amsterdam -- 10 February 1846 in Amsterdam ) was a Dutch Patriot , feminist and pamphleteer .
Thérèse de Couagne ( 19 January 1697 -- 26 February 1764 ) was a knowledgeable business woman who played an active role in the New France economy .
Adrian Cowell ( 2 February 1934 -- 11 October 2011 ) was a British filmmaker , born in Tongshan , China .
Harold Gould Henderson ( 1889 - -1974 ) was an American academic , art historian and Japanologist .
Solomon Ngobeni ( died 14 November 1989 ) was the last person to be executed by the government of South Africa .
Torfinn Bentzen ( 1912 - -1986 ) was a Norwegian jurist and sports official .
Elizabeth Amadas ( née Bryce ) ( died 1532 ) was a lady at the royal court of King Henry VIII of England who was accused of treason , and who claimed to have been the target of the King 's advances .
Walter Rautenstrauch ( 1880 - 1951 ) was an American mechanical and consulting engineer , and Professor at Columbia University 's Department of Industrial Engineering in the 1930s .
Jennifer Willems ( 13 August 1947 -- 13 November 2015 ) was a Dutch actress , well known in film and television , particularly for her role in the children 's television series De film van ome Willem ( 1974 - 1989 ) .
Martin Lev ( 31 March 1959 -- 11 March 1992 ) was an English child actor .
Harry Biss ( 9 Aug 1919 , New York -- 17 May 1997 , Long Beach , New York ) was an America jazz pianist who flourished from 1944 to 1952 .
Princess Elise of Hohenlohe - Langenburg ( German : Prinzessin Elise Victoria Feodora Sophie Adelheid zu Hohenlohe - Langenburg ; 4 September 1864 - 18 March 1929 ) was Princess Reuss Younger Line as the wife of Heinrich XXVII .
General Sir Edward Selby Smyth , KCMG ( 31 March 1819 -- 22 September 1896 ) was a British General .
John K. Smith ( died 1845 ) was the founder of SmithKline as in GlaxoSmithKline , the leading pharmaceutical business .
Fakhr al - Din Ali , better known as Sâhib Ata or Sâhip Ata , held a number of high offices at the court of the Sultanate of Rum from the 1250s until his death in 1288 .
Emperor Wu of Northern Zhou ( ( 北)周武帝 ) ( 543 - -578 ) , personal name Yuwen Yong ( 宇文邕 ) , nickname Miluotu ( 禰羅突 ) , was an emperor of the Xianbei dynasty Northern Zhou .
Pedro Patiño Ixtolinque ( also San Pedro Ecatzingo ) ( 1774 - -1835 ) was a mixed - race Mexican sculptor .
Lionel Woodville ( c. 1446 -- 23 June 1484 ) was a Bishop of Salisbury in England .
Valentine Cary ( also spelled Carey or Carew ) ( died 1626 ) was an English clergyman , who became bishop of Exeter .
Laurence Bradshaw ( 1899 - -1978 ) was an English sculptor , printmaker and artist .
Dorothy Scharf ( 1942 - -2004 ) was a reclusive art collector who left 51 valuable paintings to the Courtauld Institute in her will .
Shāh Ashraf Hotak , ( Pashto , Dari : ‌ شاہ أشرف ہوتک ) , also known as Shāh Ashraf Ghiljī ( Pashto : شاه اشرف غلجي‎ ) ( died 1730 ) , son of Abdul Aziz Hotak , was the fourth ruler of the Hotak dynasty .
Edmond Polchlopek ( 20 July 1934 -- 21 September 2004 ) was a French road racing cyclist and a bicycle designer .
Sam Fonteyn ( born Samuel Soden , c. 1925 - -1991 ) was an English composer - pianist whose most significant output was for the Boosey & Hawkes Music Library , for which he composed and recorded countless works .
Kshullak Ganeshprasad Varni ( Hindi:पूज्य 105 श्री गणेश प्रसाद वर्णी , Gujarati : શ્રી ૧૦૫ ક્ષુલ્લક ગણેશપ્રસાદ વર્ણી Kannada:ಶ್ರೀ ೧೦೫ ಕ್ಷುಲ್ಲಕ ಗಣೆಶಪ್ರಸಾದ ವರ್ಣೀ ) ( 1874 -- 5 December 1961 ) was one of the foundational figures of the modern Indian Digambara intellectual tradition during early 20th century .
Kay Callard ( 10 November 1923 -- 7 March 2008 ) was a Canadian film and television actress who spent most of her career in Britain .
Milivoje Živanović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Миливоје Живановић ; 2 April 1900 -- 15 November 1976 ) was a renowned Serbian film and stage actor .
Gunnar Aagaard Andersen ( 14 July 1919 , Ordrup -- 29 June 1982 , Munkerup ) was a Danish sculptor , painter , designer and architect whose work belongs to the Concrete art movement .
Richard Sears McCulloh ( 18 March 1818 -- 1894 ) was an American civil engineer and professor of mechanics and thermodynamics at the Washington and Lee University , Lexington , Virginia .
Johann Wilhelm Theodor Ludwig von Blandowski , known in English as William Blandowski ( 21 January 1822 -- 18 December 1878 ) , was a German zoologist and mining engineer .
George Winokur ( February 10 , 1925 - October 12 , 1996 ) was an American psychiatrist known for seminal contributions to diagnostic criteria and to the classification and genetics of mood disorder .
Jorge Glusberg ( 23 September 1932 -- 2 February 2012 ) was an Argentine author , publisher , curator and professor .
Ambroise - Marie Carré OP ( 25 July 1908 -- 15 January 2004 ) was a Catholic priest , author and member of the Académie française .
Antônio Fernandes , also known as Antoninho ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( ɐ̃toˈnĩɲu ) ) ( 13 August 1921 -- 16 December 1973 ) , was a Brazilian professional football player and manager .
Sir John Blackwood McEwen ( 13 April 1868 -- 14 June 1948 ) was a Scottish classical composer and educator .
Major - General Hugh Andrew Young ( April 3 , 1898 - -1982 ) was Commissioner of the Northwest Territories from November 14 , 1950 to November 15 , 1953 .
Undecimus Stratton ( 1868 - 12 July 1929 ) was the manager of Daimler 's London depot and supplier of automobiles to British , Spanish and German royalty .
Ronald Keith Chatto ( 1924 -- 22 October 1992 ) was an Australian comic book artist and writer .
Herman Derek Bryan OBE ( 16 December 1910 -- 17 September 2003 ) was a consular official , diplomat , sinologist , lecturer , writer , translator and editor .
Guillermo Uribe Holguín ( sometimes spelled Uribe - Holguín ) ( 17 March 1880 -- 26 June 1971 ) was a Colombian composer and violinist and one of the most important Colombian cultural figures of his generation .
John Bateman , 2nd Viscount Bateman ( April 1721 -- 2 March 1802 ) was a British politician .
Griffith Ogden Ellis ( 1869 - 1948 ) was born to a prominent family of Urbana , Ohio .
Prof Malcolm McGregor Cooper FRSE BLitt ( 17 August 1910 -- 1 September 1989 ) was a New - Zealand - born agriculturalist and author .
Daniel Whitby ( 1638 - -1726 ) was a controversial English theologian and biblical commentator .
Xue Song ( 薛嵩 ) ( died 773 ) , formally the Prince of Pingyang ( 平陽王 ) , was a general of the Chinese rebel state Yan , who later submitted to and became a general of Tang Dynasty , from which Yan had rebelled .
Susanne Sophie Catharina Gustava Kielland ( née Blom , 6 March 1800 -- 28 February 1889 ) was a Norwegian author and missionary pioneer .
Miguel Samper Agudelo ( 24 October 1825 -- 16 March 1899 ) was a Colombian lawyer , politician , and writer .
Einar Westye Egeberg , Jr. ( 24 February 1883 -- 1946 ) was a Norwegian businessperson .
Paul Schiemann ( Latvian : Pauls Šīmanis ; 17 March 1876 -- 23 June 1944 ) was a Baltic German journalist , editor and politician who was known for his commitment to minority rights .
Georges Bégué or George P. Begue ( 22 November 1911 -- 18 December 1993 ) was a French engineer and agent in the Special Operations Executive .
Thomas Wyndham , 1st Baron Wyndham PC ( 27 December 1681 -- 14 November 1745 ) , was an Irish lawyer and politician .
Juan Violá ( 1883 - -1919 ) was a Cuban baseball player in the Cuban League , Negro leagues and the minor leagues .
Tan Quanbo ( 譚全播 ) ( 834?-918 ? ) was a ruler of Qian Prefecture ( 虔州 , in modern Ganzhou , Jiangxi ) from 913 to 918 , early in the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period .
Clash of Clans is a freemium mobile MMO strategy video game developed and published by Supercell .

Rondo of Swords , known in Japan as Rondo of Deception ( 偽りの輪舞曲 Itsuwari no Rondo ) , is a strategy role - playing video game developed by Success and published by Atlus for the Nintendo DS . The game was released in Japan on August 9 , 2007 , and in North America on April 15 , 2008 .
Zmacs was written for the MIT Lisp machine and runs on its descendants ( Symbolics Genera , LMI Lambda , TI Explorer ) .
Emergency Mayhem is a racing action video game developed by Supersonic Software and published by Codemasters exclusively for the Wii .
WWE SmackDown ! vs. Raw ( often shortened to WWE SvR or SVR 2005 and known as Exciting Pro Wrestling 6 : SmackDown ! vs. Raw in Japan ) , is a professional wrestling video game released on the PlayStation 2 console by THQ and developed by Yuke 's .
Leaderboard is a series of golf simulation video games that was developed by Bruce Carver and Roger Carver , and published by Access Software .
Hyper Duel is a horizontal scrolling shooter video game developed by Technosoft .
The Apple A4 is a 32-bit package on package ( PoP ) system - on - a - chip ( SoC ) designed by Apple Inc. and manufactured by Samsung .

Norton Personal Firewall , developed by Symantec , is a discontinued personal firewall with ad blocking , program control and privacy protection capabilities .

MySQL was owned and sponsored by a single for - profit firm , the Swedish company MySQL AB , now owned by Oracle Corporation .

Bravman is the 17th president of Bucknell University who came to Bucknell after a 35-year career at Stanford University , where he served as the Freeman - Thornton Vice Provost for Undergraduate Education , Dean of the Freshman - Sophomore College , and Bing Centennial Professor of Materials Science and Engineering at Stanford University .

Betts Award , the proceeds from which were used to establish the Thornburgh Family Lecture Series on Disability Law and Policy at the University of Pittsburgh .

Dorothy Burr Thompson ( 19 August 1900 -- 10 May 2001 ) was a classical archaeologist and art historian at Bryn Mawr College and a leading authority on Hellenistic terracotta figurines .
Geoffrey Blodgett ( October 13 , 1931 -- November 15 , 2001 ) was Robert S. Danforth Professor of History at Oberlin College , located in Oberlin , Ohio .

Richard North Patterson graduated in 1968 from Ohio Wesleyan University and has been awarded that school 's Distinguished Achievement Citation and his national fraternity 's Alumni Achievement Award .
Torun Dewan is professor of political science at the London School of Economics .

Nick Margerrison went to the University of Essex where he studied English Literature .

Atilio Boron received a PhD from Harvard University .
Denis Smalley studied at the University of Canterbury and Victoria University in his native New Zealand , and later at the Paris Conservatoire with Olivier Messiaen , with the Groupe de Recherches Musicales ( GRM ) , and at the University of York .
Krzysztof Meyer ( born 11 August 1943 ) is a Polish composer , pianist and music scholar , formerly Dean of the Department of Music Theory ( 1972 - -1975 ) at the State College of Music ( now Academy of Music in Kraków ) , and president of the Union of Polish Composers ( 1985 - -1989 ) .
Barry Bergdoll is Meyer Schapiro Professor of art history in the Department of Art History and Archaeology at Columbia University and curator in the Department of Architecture and Design at the Museum of Modern Art , New York , where from 2007 to 2013 he served as Philip Johnson Chief Curator of Architecture and Design .
The senior Ensign later became chairman of the board of directors of Mandalay Resort Group , John Ensign attended the University of Nevada , Las Vegas , becoming a member of the Sigma Chi fraternity .
G. David Gearhart ( born June 9 , 1952 ) was the fifth chancellor of the University of Arkansas .
David Langford was born and grew up in Newport , Monmouthshire , Wales before studying for a degree in Physics at Brasenose College , Oxford , where he first became involved in science fiction fandom .
Martha Somerman gained a Bachelor of Arts ( BA ) from New York University , Master of Science ( MS ) from Hunter College , Doctor of Dental Surgery ( DDS ) from New York University , and a PhD from the University of Rochester .
Peter Taylor - Gooby OBE is a Professor of Social Policy at the University of Kent who is internationally noted for his work on new social risks , an area of study he helped create and develop .
Charnvit Kasetsiri obtained his Ph.D. in Southeast Asian History from Cornell University in 1972 , under the supervision of O. W. Wolters and David K. Wyatt .
Russell T. McCutcheon is a Canadian scholar with a Ph.D. in religious studies from the University of Toronto in 1995 .
David Jessel was born in Abingdon and educated at the Dragon School , an independent school in Oxford , and at Eton College , to which he won a scholarship in 1959 .
Peter Woolcott earned his Bachelor of Law and Bachelor of Arts degrees from the Australian National University and a Master of Arts degree from The Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy .
Sonia Livingstone holds a BSc degree in psychology from University College London and obtained her PhD in Psychology from the University of Oxford .
Patrick C. Kennell ( born February 18 , 1960 ) is Director of the Center for Intensive English Studies ( CIES ) at Florida State University in Tallahassee , Florida .
His bothers were Eric Gunasekera and Donald Gunasekera , the former was headmaster of Wesley College , Colombo The Sir Frank Gunasekera Trophy is awarded annually at the annual cricket match between Royal College Colombo and Wesley College , Colombo , played since 1893 .
Igor Ternov graduated from Faculty of Physics of Moscow State University ( MSU ) in 1951 , where he spent his entire career .
Brigitte Peucker ( born 13 April 1948 , in Berlin , Germany ) is the Elias Leavenworth Professor of German Languages and Literatures and Professor of Film Studies at Yale University .
Mitchell J. Nathan is Full Professor of Educational Psychology , Chair of the Learning Science program in the School of Education at the University of Wisconsin-- Madison , and a researcher at the Wisconsin Center for Education Research .

Tan Chung taught at Jawaharlal Nehru University ( JNU ) and the University of Delhi for many years .
William Twining is the Emeritus Quain Professor of Jurisprudence at University College London .
Barbara Wilding , CBE , QPM is the former Chief Constable of South Wales Police , the first woman to hold the post .
Joseph Wickham Roe ( 1871 - 1960 ) was an American engineer and Professor of Industrial Engineering at the New York University , known for his seminal work on machine tools and machine tool builders history .
Pippa Norris ( born July 10 , 1953 ) is the McGuire Lecturer in Comparative Politics at the Kennedy School of Government , Harvard University , Australian Laureate Fellow and Professor of Government and International Relations at the University of Sydney , and Director of the Electoral Integrity Project .
W. Bruce Croft is a distinguished professor of computer science at the University of Massachusetts Amherst whose work focuses on information retrieval .
Ronald C. Kennedy , PhD was a virus immunologist at Texas Tech University .
Roman Inderst ( born 13 April 1970 ) is a German economist who holds the chair for finance and economics at the Goethe University Frankfurt .
Hans Oeschger ( 2 April 1927 , Ottenbach -- 25 December 1998 , Bern ) was the founder of the Division of Climate and Environmental Physics at the Physics Institute of the University of Bern in 1963 and director until his retirement in 1992 .
Richard C. Dorf ( born December 27 , 1933 , in the Bronx , New York City ) is a Professor Emeritus of Management and Electrical and Computer Engineering at the University of California , Davis .
Ravida Din is a Canadian film producer who formerly served with the National Film Board of Canada ( NFB ) as a producer , executive producer , then as its Director General of English - language production , from February 11 , 2013 to February 26 , 2014 .
Philip V. Holberton ( born 1942 ) is an American business executive , entrepreneur and professor of Leadership at Brandeis University .
Francis Jay Underhill was an author , amateur musician , and American bond broker with two firms , Fisk & Robinson and later with J. & W. Seligman & Co. , that played a leading role in the financing and construction of the Panama Canal .
Ricardo Semler ( born 1959 in São Paulo ) is the CEO and majority owner of Semco Partners , a Brazilian company best known for its radical form of industrial democracy and corporate re - engineering .
Billy Goldberg ( born 1966 ) is a New York City emergency medicine physician at the NYU School of Medicine ( Bellevue Hospital and New York University ( NYU ) Medical Center ) , where he is also an Assistant Professor and an Assistant Director in the Department of Emergency Medicine .
In 1923 , Charlotte Bühler went to teach at the University of Vienna , where in 1929 she was promoted to the position of associate professor .
Robert Sommer is an internationally known Environmental Psychologist and currently holds the position of Distinguished Professor of Psychology Emeritus at the University of California , Davis .
Andrea Sella ( born February 1961 ) is a chemist and broadcaster based at University College London where he is a Professor of Inorganic Chemistry .
Katya Adler ( born 1972 ) is a British journalist , who having worked for the BBC since 1998 is now its Europe Editor .
Judith C. Russell ( born 1944 ) is the current Dean of University Libraries at the University of Florida .
Michael Slote is UST Professor of Ethics at the University of Miami and is author of From Morality to Virtue ( 1992 ) and Morals From Motives ( 2001 ) .
Elizabeth A. Craig is a Steenbock Professor of Microbial Science and Chair of the Biochemistry Department at the University of Wisconsin - Madison .
Robert W. Parry ( October 1 , 1917 - December 1 , 2006 ) was a professor of chemistry at the University of Michigan and the University of Utah .
Anke Ehlers FBA FMedSci ( born 11 January 1957 ) is a German psychologist who works at the University of Oxford as Wellcome Trust Principal Research Fellow and Professor of Experimental Psychopathology .
Richard Ernest Kronauer is the Gordon McKay Professor of Mechanical Engineering , emeritus , at Harvard University .
Scott J. Shapiro is the Charles F. Southmayd Professor of Law and Philosophy at Yale Law School and the Director of Yale 's Center for Law and Philosophy .

Enrique Máximo García ( Murcia , 1954 - -2008 ) was a Spanish musicologist and associated teacher at the Art History Department of the University of Murcia .
Salem Hanna Khamis ( November 22 , 1919 -- June 16 , 2005 ) was a Palestinian economic statistician for the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization who helped formalise the Geary - Khamis method of computing purchasing power parity of currencies .
Klaus Darga retired as a chess professional and became a computer programmer for IBM .

D. , is a computational biologist and bioinformatician , and a chair professor under the title ' Regents - Georgia Research Alliance Eminent Scholar ' in the Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology and the Institute of Bioinformatics at the University of Georgia , USA .

Geoffrey Bruun ( 20 October 1898 -- 13 July 1988 ) was a historian and biographer who taught at New York University from 1927 until 1941 .
John A. Jane , Sr . ( September 21 , 1931 -- September 18 , 2015 ) was an American neurosurgeon , and Professor of Neurosurgery at the University of Virginia .

Diane Davis ( born 1963 ) is a post - structuralist rhetorician and professor of Rhetoric and Writing , English , and Communication Studies at the University of Texas at Austin .
Mikhail Lukin ( Russian : Михаи́л Дми́триевич Луки́н ; born October 10 , 1971 ) is a Russian - American theoretical and experimental physicist and a professor at Harvard University .

Carl Kasell ( /ˈkæsəl/ ; born April 2 , 1934 ) is an American radio personality , most widely known as a newscaster for National Public Radio and as the former official judge and scorekeeper of the weekly news quiz show Wait Wait ...

InPhonic was founded by David A. Steinberg who resigned in 2007 due to poor debt management and decreasing revenues .

The Manufacture de films pour cinématographes , often known as the Star Film Company , was a French film production company run by the illusionist and film director Georges Méliès .

Christian Jungersen ( born 10 July 1962 in Copenhagen ) is a Danish novelist whose works have been translated into 18 languages .
Maria Assumpció Soler i Font ( Girona , 22 April 1913 -- Girona , 24 March 2004 ) was a Catalan writer and journalist .

Peter Frenkel ( born 13 May 1939 in Eckartsberga ) is an East German athlete who was one of the best 20 km race walkers in the world in the late 1960s and early 1970s .
George Crabbe ( /kræb/ ; 24 December 1754 -- 3 February 1832 ) was an English poet , surgeon , and clergyman .

Álvaro Cassuto ( born 1938 ) is a Portuguese composer and conductor .

João de Castro ( 7 February 1500 -- 6 June 1548 ) was a Portuguese nobleman and fourth viceroy of Portuguese India .

Jean II Restout ( 26 March 1692 -- 1 January 1768 ) was a French painter , whose late baroque classicism rendered his altarpieces , such as the Death of Saint Scholastica an `` isolated achievement '' that ran counter to his rococo contemporaries .

Colonel Valentín Galarza Morante ( 1882 in El Puerto de Santa María -- 1951 in Madrid ) was a Spanish officer and right wing politician .
Grey Cooper ( c. 1726 -- 30 July 1801 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1765 and 1790 and was Secretary to the Treasury under various administrations .

The 92nd ( Loyals ) Light Anti - Aircraft Regiment , Royal Artillery was a British Army mobile light anti - aircraft regiment of the Royal Artillery that was raised and active during the Second World War .

The Royal Regiment of Scotland is the senior and only Scottish line infantry regiment of the British Army Infantry .

The South - West Africa Territorial Force ( SWATF ) was an auxiliary arm of the South African Defence Force and comprised the armed forces of South - West Africa ( now Namibia ) from 1977 to 1989 .
Wing Commander Humphrey de Verd Leigh OBE , DFC , AFC ( 1897 - -1980 ) was a Royal Air Force officer .
James Carson Breckinridge ( September 13 , 1877 -- March 2 , 1942 ) was a lieutenant general of the United States Marine Corps .
The London Regiment is an infantry regiment in the British Army , part of the Army Reserve .
The Yorkshire Regiment ( 14th/15th , 19th and 33rd/76th Foot ) ( abbreviated YORKS ) is an infantry regiment of the British Army , created by the amalgamation of three historic regiments in 2006 .
Theodore C. Almquist ( --April 22 , 2010)was a Brigadier General in the United States Air Force .
Sir Edward Spragge ( name also written as Spragg or Sprague ) ( circa 1620 -- 21 August 1673 ) was an Irish admiral of the Royal Navy .
Emil Berner ( 4 December 1921 -- 13 June 2008 ) was a highly decorated Unteroffizier of the Reserves in the Luftwaffe during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
General Bernard Adolph Schriever ( September 14 , 1910 -- June 20 , 2005 ) , also known as Bennie Schriever , was a United States Air Force general .
Hong Sa - ik ( 4 March 1889 -- 26 September 1946 ) was a lieutenant general in the Imperial Japanese Army , and the top - ranking ethnic Korean in Japan to be charged with war crimes relating to the conduct of the Empire of Japan in World War II .
Princess Viktoria of Prussia ( Friederike Amalia Wilhelmine Viktoria ) ( 12 April 1866 -- 13 November 1929 ) was the second daughter of Frederick III , German Emperor and his wife Victoria , Princess Royal , a daughter of Queen Victoria .
Thanphuying Suthawan Sathirathai ( Thai : สุธาวัลย์ เสถียรไทย ; rtgs : Suthawan Sathianthai ) is the only daughter of Busba Kitiyakara ( younger sister of Queen Sirikit ) .
Knud , Hereditary Prince of Denmark ( Knud Christian Frederik Michael ; 27 July 1900 -- 14 June 1976 ) , was the second son and youngest child of Christian X and Alexandrine of Mecklenburg - Schwerin .
Dweezil Zappa was born in Los Angeles , California , the son of musician Frank Zappa and Gail Zappa , who worked in business .
Francisco Goya was born in Fuendetodos , Aragón , Spain , on 30 March 1746 to José Benito de Goya y Franque and Gracia de Lucientes y Salvador .
William of Septimania ( 29 November 826 -- 850 ) was the son of Bernard and Dhuoda .
Julie Delpy was born in Paris to Albert Delpy , a theater director , and Marie Pillet , an actress in feature films and the avant - garde theater .
In Greek mythology , Polybotes ( Greek : Πολυβώτης ) was one of the Giants , the offspring of Gaia ( Earth ) , and Uranus ( Sky ) .
Magnus Fiennes was born in Suffolk , England in 1965 , a son of photographer Mark Fiennes and novelist Jennifer Lash ( both deceased ) .
Take Charge Indy 's dam , Take Charge Lady , was a top - class racemare whosse wins included the Ashland Stakes and successive runnings of the Spinster Stakes .
The Gouët ( Ar Goued in the breton language ) is a French river , located in the department of Côtes - d'Armor , in the region of Brittany , which drains into the English Channel .
The Des Moines River is a tributary of the Mississippi River , approximately 525 miles ( 845 km ) long to its farther headwaters , in the upper Midwestern United States .
The Neosho River is a tributary of the Arkansas River in eastern Kansas and northeastern Oklahoma in the United States .
The Spokane River is a tributary of the Columbia River , approximately 111 miles ( 179 km ) long , in northern Idaho and eastern Washington in the United States .
The Kat River ( Afrikaans : Katrivier ) is a tributary of the Great Fish River , that drains the southern slopes of the Winterberg in the Eastern Cape Province , South Africa .
More specifically the Mosetse River discharges to Sua Pan , draining parts of eastern Botswana .
The Rolava ( German : Rohlau ) is a left tributary of the Eger river ( Czech : Ohře ) in the northwest of the Czech Republic .
The Iriri River ( Portuguese : Rio Iriri ) is a large tributary of the Xingu River in Brazil , in the state of Pará .
L'Anguille River ( pronounced `` lan - GWEEL '' `` LANG - gill '' or locally as `` LANE - GEE '' ) is a tributary of the St. Francis River , approximately 110 mi ( 175 km ) long , in northeastern Arkansas in the United States .
The Georgina River is the north - westernmost of the three major rivers of the Channel Country in Central West Queensland that flow in extremely wet years into Lake Eyre .
D.C. Follies is a syndicated sitcom which aired from 1987 - -1989 and was set in a Washington , D.C. bar , where bartender Fred Willard would welcome puppet caricatures of that day 's politicians and celebrities .
Teardrops on My Drum is an autobiographical novel of Jack Robinson 's boyhood in Liverpool , UK , in the 1930s ( ISBN 0 - 85449 - 261 - 5 , Gay Men 's Press , 1998 ) .
In Orange received a Golden Film after it had sold 100,000 cinema tickets in the Netherlands .
Box 2000 was regularly lampooned ( in a similar manner to many other STV programmes such as Late Call ) by the BBC Scotland comedy sketch show Scotch and Wry , where it took on the name Box 2001 , and instead had bizarre charities which generally poked fun at genuine ones shown on the real broadcasts .
The Golden Palace begins where The Golden Girls had ended , in the quartet 's now - sold Miami house .
Monsoon Wedding is a 2001 film directed by Mira Nair and written by Sabrina Dhawan , which depicts romantic entanglements during a traditional Punjabi Hindu wedding in Delhi .
Liza of Lambeth ( 1897 ) was W. Somerset Maugham 's first novel , which he wrote while working as a doctor at a hospital in Lambeth , then a working class district of London .
The Penguins of Doom is set in the fictitious city of Conwell , Massachusetts , which is described in the book as a suburb of Boston .
Freebie and the Bean is a 1974 action - comedy film about two off - beat police detectives who wreak havoc in San Francisco attempting to bring down a local organized crime boss .
Overheard 2 is a 2011 Hong Kong crime thriller film produced by Derek Yee , written and directed by Alan Mak and Felix Chong and starring Louis Koo , Lau Ching - wan and Daniel Wu .

Shelley Looney ( born January 21 , 1972 in Brownstown , Michigan and raised in Trenton , Michigan ) is an American ice hockey player .
Calvin Grant Shofner ( April 7 , 1932 -- October 10 , 2013 ) , known professionally as Cal Smith , was an American country musician , most famous for his 1974 hit `` Country Bumpkin . ''
Otto Kruger ( September 6 , 1885 -- September 6 , 1974 ) was an American actor , originally a Broadway matinee idol , who established a niche as a charming villain in films , such as Hitchcock 's Saboteur .
Domiziano Arcangeli ( born June 10 , 1968 ) is an Italian and American actor , producer , and writer .

Julian Deda is Albanian comedian and actor .
Mara Carlyle ( born 1974 or 1975 ) is an English singer - songwriter and arranger who also plays the musical saw and the ukulele .
Nathan Furst ( born July 4 , 1978 ) is an American television and film composer .
Paul Tripp ( February 20 , 1911 - August 29 , 2002 ) was a children 's musician , author , songwriter , and television and film actor .
Johnny Long , otherwise known as `` j0hnny '' or `` j0hnnyhax '' , is a renowned computer security expert , author , and public speaker in the United States .
George David Birkhoff ( March 21 , 1884 -- November 12 , 1944 ) was an American mathematician , best known for what is now called the ergodic theorem .
Samuel Dinsmoor ( July 1 , 1766 -- March 15 , 1835 ) was an American teacher , lawyer , banker and politician from New Hampshire .
Peter Betts is an American former figure skater .
Luigi Rosselli is an Italian born architect who practices in Australia .
Ron Husband ( February 8 , 1950 ) is an American character animator known for his work at Walt Disney Feature Animation , where he has worked since 1975 .
Eleanor O'Meara is a former Canadian figure skater who competed in single skating and pair skating with Ralph McCreath , with whom was the 1941 national and North American champion .

Warren Delano Robbins ( September 3 , 1885 -- April 7 , 1935 ) was an American diplomat and first cousin of President Franklin D. Roosevelt .
Goran Gocić is a Serbian freelance journalist , editor , author and filmmaker , whose work has been published or broadcast by many media organizations worldwide .
Adrian Lucas is an English conductor and organist .
Jonathan Cavendish is an independent film producer .
Charles Fenno Hoffman ( February 7 , 1806 -- June 7 , 1884 ) was an American author , poet and editor associated with the Knickerbocker Group in New York .
Katia Cardenal ( born June 19 , 1963 , in Managua , Nicaragua ) is a Nicaraguan singer / songwriter , and a part of the nueva trova movement .
Jennifer Lerner is an experimental social psychologist known for her research in emotion and decision theory .
David Ari Leon ( born December 12 , 1967 ) is an American composer , musician and music supervisor .
Mestre João Faras , better known simply as Mestre João ( ' Master John `` ) , was an astrologer , astronomer , physician and surgeon of King Manuel I of Portugal who accompanied Pedro Álvares Cabral in the discovery of Brazil in 1500 , and wrote a famous letter identifying the Southern Cross constellation .
David Hersey ( born November 30 , 1939 ) is a lighting designer who has designed the lighting for over 250 plays , musicals , operas , and ballets .
Thomas Hardeman , Jr. ( January 12 , 1825 -- March 6 , 1891 ) was an American politician , lawyer and soldier .
Anthony Shorten ( born 12 June 1969 ) is an Australian Liberal National politician who was the Member of Parliament for Algester from 2012 to 2015 , having defeated Karen Struthers at the 2012 state election .
Enrique Hidalgo is an accomplished musician and multi - instrumentalist ( guitar , venezuelan cuatro , piano , harp and percussion ) .
The so - called Byzantine Master of the Crucifix of Pisa was an anonymous Italian painter active in Pisa in the first half of the thirteenth century .
Shaun Sipos ( born October 30 , 1981 ) is a Canadian actor , known for playing Jack on ABC series Complete Savages and David Breck on The CW series Melrose Place .
T. Allen Lawson ( born August 3 , 1963 ) is an American artist recognized for his landscape paintings of Wyoming and Maine subjects , and is perhaps best known for having painted the White House Christmas card in 2008 .
William Henry Sheppard ( 1865 - -1927 ) was one of the earliest African Americans to become a missionary for the Presbyterian Church .
Randall S. Kiper , more known as Kyper , is a rapper , D.J. and actor based in Baton Rouge , Louisiana .

Pete Muller is an American photographer and multimedia reporter based in Nairobi , Kenya .
Ed Tracy is a British television writer and television director who collaborated with the comedian Kayvan Novak to create all of the Fonejacker and Facejacker television shows .
Stewart N. Gordon ( born Jan. 2 , 1945 ) is an American born historian , teacher , lecturer , writer , and consultant .
Laurie Geltman ( born in Baltimore and raised in Boston ) , is an American rock singer / songwriter .
Ronit Roy is an Indian film and television actor , known for his portrayal of K D Pathak , Rishabh Bajaj , Mihir Virani , Neil Khanna and Aparajit Deb .
Huo Guang ( Chinese : 霍光 ; died 68 BC ) , courtesy name Zimeng ( 子孟 ) , was a Western Han politician who was a rare example in Chinese history of a powerful official who deposed an emperor for the good of the state rather than to usurp the throne .
Ivan Doig ( June 27 , 1939 -- April 9 , 2015 ) was an American author and novelist , widely known for his seventeen fiction and non - fiction books set mostly in his native Montana , celebrating the landscape and people of the post - war American West .
Brigitte Raue is a retired German rower who won a bronze and a silver medal in the quad sculls at the European championships of 1957 and 1958 , respectively .
Winthrop Sargent ( May 1 , 1753 -- June 3 , 1820 ) was a United States patriot , politician , and writer ; and a member of the Federalist party .
Drew Milne is a contemporary British poet and academic .
Robert M. Blizzard was a pediatric endocrinologist and a founding member of the Lawson Wilkins Pediatric Endocrine Society .
Shlomi Dolev ( Hebrew : שלומי דולב‎ ) is an Israeli computer scientist best known for his contribution to self - stabilization .
Laura Poantă ( born March 10 , 1971 , Agnita , Sibiu County ) is a Romanian physician , medical scientist , author , translator , and painter .
Narayanan , known by his stage name Sirpy ( Tamil : சிற்பி ; born 25 May 1962 ) is an Indian film score and soundtrack composer .
Wilbur Mack ( July 29 , 1873 - March 13 , 1964 ) was an American film actor and early vaudeville performer from the 1920s through the 1960s .
Shayan Munshi is an Indian model turned actor who made his debut in the 2003 Bollywood film Jhankaar Beats and has performed in award - winning films such as Bong Connection and Carnival .
Dahlov Ipcar ( née Zorach ) ( born November 12 , 1917 ) is an American painter , illustrator and author .
