Leo Nosworthy ( born c.1930 ) was an Australian rugby league player from the 1950s who became a premiership winning coach of the Balmain Tigers rugby league team .
Paul Bogart ( November 21 , 1919 -- April 15 , 2012 ) was an American television and film director .
M. Afzal Hossain ( born November 30 , 1952 ) is a professor and Bangladeshi scientist in the field of agriculture and biochemistry .
Devon Halfnight LeFlufy ( born 26 March 1984 in Vancouver , Canada ) is a Canadian fashion designer based in Antwerp , Belgium .
Thomas Augustine Geary ( Timothy Geary ) ( 1775 -- November 1801 ) was an Irish composer , pianist and organist , with a precocious talent particularly in vocal and piano writing .
Judith K. Zilczer was an American art historian and museum curator .
John Houseman ( born Jacques Haussmann ; September 22 , 1902 -- October 31 , 1988 ) was a Romanian - born British - American actor and producer who became known for his highly publicized collaboration with director Orson Welles from their days in the Federal Theatre Project through to the production of Citizen Kane .
Jouni Helminen is a Finnish professional ten - pin bowler .
Armanis F. Knotts ( c. 1860-October 3 , 1937 ) , also called A.F. Knotts , was an American politician and lawyer .

Alberto María Fonrouge ( March 6 , 1913 -- March 28 , 2012 ) was an Argentine politician and lawyer , co - founder of the Popular Conservative Party and Senator from 1973 to 1976 .
Earl Muetterties ( 1927 - -1984 ) , was an American inorganic chemist born in Illinois , who is known for his experimental work with boranes , homogeneous catalysis , heterogeneous catalysis , fluxional processes in organometallic complexes and apicophilicity .
Ariane Lopez - Huici ( born August 5 , 1945 ) is a photographer living between New York and Paris .

Yuki Itoda ( born 1982 in Japan ) is a Japanese artist .

Karl Linn ( March 11 , 1923 -- February 3 , 2005 ) was a landscape architect , psychologist , educator , and community activist , best known for inspiring and guiding the creation of `` neighborhood commons '' on vacant lots in East Coast inner cities during the 1960s through 1980s .
Seymore Butts ( born Adam Glasser ; March 18 , 1964 ) is an American pornographic film director , producer , and occasional star who has produced hundreds of films in the gonzo genre of pornography ( faux reality - based adult material ) .

Frank Leaves for the Orient is a television series produced by Comedy Central , which aired for 6 episodes over the summer of 1999 .
Executive Stress is a British sitcom that aired on ITV from 1986 to 1988 .
Genie in the House is a British sitcom broadcast on Nickelodeon UK about a widowed father ( Philip ) with two teenage daughters ( Emma and Sophie ) who find a dusty old golden lamp while exploring the loft of their new home .
KOMO news anchors Dan Lewis , Kathi Goertzen , and several KOMO TV reporters have made appearances on Northwest Afternoon over the years .
Kittie Party is a Hindi television serial that aired on Zee TV .
Time for Sunday School was a Canadian children 's religious television series which aired on CBC Television from 1962 to 1966 .
Party Monsters Cabo is a reality TV show airing on E!.
Miodowe lata is a popular Polish television sitcom , produced by Polsat from 1998 to 2003 .
You 're the Worst is an American single - camera comedy - drama series created by Stephen Falk , originally for FX , and currently FXX .
Buenos días , Isabel is a Venezuelan telenovela produced by Venevisión in 1980 .
The genre of police / crime dramas was well established on British television by 1980 ; however the BBC 's Juliet Bravo , along with London Weekend Television 's The Gentle Touch , which started a few months earlier , dealt with female officers as lead characters having to fight both crime and the prejudice of male colleagues .
Talent Jackpot was an American game show broadcast on the DuMont Television Network from July 13 to August 23 , 1949 .
Nature 's Great Events is a wildlife documentary series made for BBC television , first shown in the UK on BBC One and BBC HD in February 2009 .
Kings of Comedy was a reality television series broadcast made by Endemol for Channel 4 .
Real Sports with Bryant Gumbel is a monthly sports newsmagazine on HBO that debuted on April 2 , 1995 .
Agyrta is a Neotropical genus of moth in the family Arctiidae .
Wiborgia is an African genus of the family Fabaceae .
Elytrostachys is a genus of bamboo ( tribe Bambuseae of the family Poaceae ) , found in the rainforests from Honduras to Venezuela .
Amplibuteo is an extinct genus of birds of prey , belonging the family Accipitridae .
Sporobolomyces is a fungal genus of uncertain familial placement in the order Sporidiobolales .
The Texas map turtle ( Graptemys versa ) is a species of emydid turtle endemic to the southern United States .
The Mozambique spitting cobra ( Naja mossambica ) is a species of spitting cobra native to Africa .
Eickwortapis is an extinct monotypic genus of sweat bee in the Halictidae subfamily Halictinae and containing the single species Eickwortapis dominicana .
The Mupli beetle , Luprops tristis , is a plant detritus eating Darkling beetle found in parts of India .
The Lyopsettinae are a subfamily of fish in the Pleuronectidae family consisting of one genus , Lyopsetta .
Cynoscion is a genus of fish in the drum family , Sciaenidae .
Utabaenetes is a genus of insect in family Rhaphidophoridae containing the species Utabaenetes tanneri .
Nylandtia is a small genus of two species of shrub , in the family Polygalaceae .
Ibisia is a genus of ' ibis flies ' belonging to the family Athericidae , a small family very similar to Rhagionidae ( ' Snipe Flies ' ) .
Hedera , commonly called ivy ( plural ivies ) , is a genus of 12 - -15 species of evergreen climbing or ground - creeping woody plants in the family Araliaceae , native to western , central and southern Europe , Macaronesia , northwestern Africa and across central - southern Asia east to Japan and Taiwan .
Aquilonites is a pericyclacean goniatitid belonging to the Family Intoceratidae , suborder Goniatitina , that lived during the very early Carboniferous of what is now Russia .
Ertzia is a monospecific genus in the family Lepidostromataceae ( the only family within the fungal order Lepidostromatales ) .
The Erg agama ( Trapelus tournevillei ) is a species of lizard in the Agamidae family .
The Nyika climbing mouse ( Dendromus nyikae ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
The Sierra newt , with scientific name Taricha sierrae , is a newt found west of the Sierra Nevada , from Shasta county to Tulare County , in California , Western North America .
The Atlantic bamboo rat ( Kannabateomys amblyonyx ) , or southern bamboo rat , is a spiny rat species from South America , found in humid tropical forests in Argentina , Brazil and Paraguay .
The Ethiopian woolly bat ( Kerivoula eriophora ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
The American chestnut moth ( Ectoedemia castaneae ) was a species of moth in the family Nepticulidae .
The Marcapata Valley caecilian , Epicrionops peruvianus , is a species of caecilian in the Rhinatrematidae family endemic to Peru .
Elachistocleis pearsei was until recently considered to form monotypic genus Relictivomer , but in molecular phylogeny Elachistocleis pearsei is nested within other Elachistocleis , leading to resurrection of name Elachistocleis pearsei .
Lyriothemis is a genus of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae , found in southeastern Asia .
Bathyacmaea is a genus of deep - sea limpet , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pectinodontidae .
Coptopterella scutellata is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Coptopterella .
The Glanville fritillary ( Melitaea cinxia ) is a butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
Vivianiaceae is a family of flowering plants placed in the order Geraniales .
Malesherbia is a genus of flowering plants consisting of about 27 species in the Passifloraceae .
Aureolaria plants are hemiparasitic , which is a character that in part describes the Orobanchaceae .
Limatula , the file shells or file clams , is a genus of marine bivalve molluscs in the family Limidae .

Aboriella is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Urticaceae , native to the eastern Himalaya , in the Abor Hills .
The Vietnamese crocodile newt or Vietnamese knobby newt , Tylototriton vietnamensis , is a species of newt in the Salamandridae family .
Halictophagidae are an insect family of the order Strepsiptera .
Rasahus is a Neotropical genus of assassin bugs ( Reduviidae ) ; 26 species have been described .
Patelloida is a genus of sea snails or true limpets , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Lottiidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Centroplacaceae is a family of flowering plants in the order Malpighiales and is recognized by the APG III system of classification .
Rayjacksonia is a genus of North American flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae .
Sersalisia is a genus of trees in Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1810 .
Dinocolpodes emeishanicus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Dinocolpodes .
Nannolytoceratidae is a taxonomic family of ammonoid cephalopods belonging to the suborder Lytoceratina .
The Aztec fruit - eating bat ( Artibeus aztecus ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Wettinia is a palm genus , consisting of flowering plants in the Arecaceae family .
The Colombian bonneted bat ( Eumops trumbulli ) , is a bat species from South America .
Richmond 's squirrel ( Sciurus richmondi ) is a tree squirrel in the genus Sciurus endemic to Nicaragua .
Vesey - Fitzgerald 's burrowing skink ( Janetaescincus veseyfitzgeraldi ) is a species of lizard in the skink family , Scincidae .
Scurria is a genus of sea snails , the true limpets , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Lottiidae .
Aphysotes tubericollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Aphysotes .
The Chinese pond heron ( Ardeola bacchus ) is an East Asian freshwater bird of the heron family , ( Ardeidae ) .
The Diprotodontia ( /ˌdaɪˌproʊtoʊˈdɒnʃiə/ ; Greek : διπρωτός diprotos , meaning `` two front '' and οδοντος odontos meaning `` teeth '' ) are a large order of about 125 marsupial mammals including the kangaroos , wallabies , possums , koala , wombats , and many others .
The Athi elephant - snout fish ( Mormyrus tenuirostris ) is a species of fish in the Mormyridae family .
Grifola is a genus of fungi in the family Meripilaceae , which includes some edible fungi such as Grifola frondosa , commonly known as hen - of - the - woods ( or Maitake in Japan ) ; not to be confused with Laetiporus sulphureus , known among English speakers as chicken of the woods .
Bifericeras is a Lower Jurassic ammonite belonging to the family Eoderoceratidae , and sometimes placed in the subfamily Xipherceratinae .
The Inca dove ( Columbina inca ) is a small New World dove .
Small - spotted lizard , ( Mesalina guttulata ) is a species of lizard .
The Sauro lizardfish ( Synodus lacertinus ) is a type of lizardfish that lives mainly in the Eastern Pacific .
The Hagerman horse ( Equus simplicidens ) , also called the Hagerman zebra or the American zebra , was a North American species of equid from the Pliocene epoch and the Pleistocene epoch .
The Indonesian coelacanth ( Latimeria menadoensis , Indonesian : raja laut ) is one of two living species of coelacanth , identifiable by its brown color .
Neogalissus pelidnos is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Neogalissus .
Thryophilus is a genus of wrens in the Troglodytidae ( wren ) family .
Candidatus Accumulibacter is an unclassified group of Betaproteobacteria that currently contains only a single member , Candidatus Accumulibacter Phosphatis .
Argyropeza is a genus of small deep - sea sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Procerithiidae .
Johan 's spiny mouse ( Acomys johannis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Zehala is a genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae .
Erhard 's wall lizard ( Podarcis erhardii ) is a species of lacertid lizard endemic to Southeast Europe .
The Galapagos bullhead shark , Heterodontus quoyi , is a bullhead shark of the family Heterodontidae .
The sole species , Chaltenobatrachus grandisonae , used to be included Atelognathus , which is considered the sister taxon of Chaltenobatrachus .
Phomatosphaeropsis is a genus of fungi in the family Botryosphaeriaceae containing the single species Phomatosphaeropsis pinicola .
Triosteum , commonly known as horse - gentian or , less commonly , feverwort , is a genus of flowering plants in the Caprifoliaceae family .
Todarodinae is a squid subfamily in the family Ommastrephidae .
Hypoderaeum conoideum is a species of digenetic trematode in the family Echinostomatidae .
Kuhl 's lorikeet ( Vini kuhlii ) , also called Rimatara lorikeet , Rimitara lorikeet , Kuhl 's lory , or Kura , is a species of lorikeet in the family Psittaculidae .
The Australian lace - lid ( Nyctimystes dayi ) is a tree frog and is the only species in its genus that occurs in Australia .
The Rimatara reed warbler ( Acrocephalus rimitarae ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Acrocephalidae family .
Cadorna 's pipistrelle ( Hypsugo cadornae ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .

Hutchins ' tree frog , Hypsiboas hutchinsi , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia and possibly Brazil and Peru .

The Sulawesian puddle frog or Celebes Oriental frog ( Occidozyga celebensis ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .

Cope 's climbing salamander ( Bolitoglossa morio ) is a species of salamander in the Plethodontidae family .
The Antarctic fur seal ( Arctocephalus gazella ) is one of eight seals in the genus Arctocephalus , and one of nine fur seals in the subfamily Arctocephalinae .
Eremiaphilidae is a small family of the order Mantodea ( mantises ) .

Rhexia ( deer grass , meadow beauty ) is a genus of plants in the Melastomataceae family .
The Tenerife giant rat ( Canariomys bravoi ) is an extinct species of rodent endemic to the island of Tenerife , the largest of the Canary Islands , Spain .
The Ward 's red - backed vole ( Eothenomys wardi ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Costabieta is a minor genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
The Thalia 's shrew ( Crocidura thalia ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
More specifically , Thunnus is one of five genera which make up the Thunnini tribe -- a tribe that is collectively known as the tunas .

Aglaostola tereticollis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Aglaostola .
The Orthocerataceae is one of two superfamilies in the Orthocerida presented in the Treatise , the other being the Pseudorthocerataceae .
Originally assigned to the Stegosauria by de Lapparent , Lusitanosaurus is today considered a basal member of the Thyreophora , perhaps belonging to the Scelidosauridae .
Progeryonidae is a small family of crabs in the order Decapoda .

Hirtomurex is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the subfamily Coralliophilinae , the coral snails , within the family Muricidae , the murex snails and rock snails .
Konglungenoceras is a discorid from the lower Silurian of Europe ( Norway ) included in the Cyrtogomphoceratidae that lacks the septal foramina grasping bullettes at the adapical end of the connecting rings .
Bifidobacteriales is an order of bacteria , in the subclass of Actinobacteridae .

Pempteurys sericans is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Pempteurys .

Myrcianthes is a genus of flowering plants in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1856 .

Polyommatinae , the blues , are a subfamily of gossamer - winged butterflies ( Lycaenidae ) .

The Caribbean lanternshark , Etmopterus hillianus , is a shark of the family Etmopteridae found in the eastern and western Atlantic at depths between 180 and 720 m. Its length is up to 50 cm . Reproduction is ovoviviparous .
Within the asterids , Apiales belongs to an unranked group called the campanulids , and within the campanulids , it belongs to a clade known in phylogenetic nomenclature as Apiidae .

The Allotrioceratidae is a family of Middle Ordovician fossils , established by Rousseau Flower , 1955 , originally including Allotrioceras and Mirabilocras , assigned inferentially to the Endocerida and known only from structures interpreted as siphuncles .
Permotanyderus is an extinct genus of protodipteran insect of the Permotanyderidae family , first described by Edgar F. Riek in Australia in 1953 and which contains a single species P. ableptus .
Rhagamys is an extinct genus of rodents in the subfamily Murinae , the Old World mice and rats .
Zalophus is a genus of the family Otariidae ( sea lions and fur seals ) of order Carnivora .
In the 19th century , the Mesozoa were a wastebasket taxon for multicellular organisms which lacked the invaginating gastrula which was thought to define the Metazoa .

Euclea , from the Greek eukleia meaning `` glory and fame '' , denotes a group of flowering plants in the Ebenaceae or ebony family .

The Wanieso lizardfish ( Saurida wanieso ) is a species of lizardfish that lives in the Atlantic , Pacific and Indian Oceans .

The Sulu bleeding - heart ( Gallicolumba menagei ) is a species of bird in the pigeon and dove family , Columbidae .
Cerradomys maracajuensis , also known as the Maracaju Oryzomys , is a rodent species from South America .
The Papallacta tree frog , Hyloscirtus psarolaimus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia and Ecuador .
Mechow 's mole - rat ( Fukomys mechowii ) is a species of rodent in the family Bathyergidae .
The Pteronarcyidae , also known as giant stoneflies or salmonflies , are a family of the order Plecoptera .
The Linduan rousette ( Rousettus linduensis ) is a species of megabat in the Rousettus genus of the family Pteropodidae .
Claoxylon is a flowering plant genus in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae , comprising dioecious subshrubs to small trees .
Citrus × meyeri , the Meyer lemon , is a citrus fruit native to China thought to be a cross between a true lemon and either a mandarin or common orange .
The Biak threespot crow ( Euploea tripunctata ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
Brown doves are members of the genus Phapitreron in the pigeon family .
The Admiralty flying fox ( Pteropus admiralitatum ) is a species of fruit bat in the family Pteropodidae , the megabats .
Bulweria is a genus of seabirds in the family Procellariidae named after English naturalist James Bulwer .
Acheronodon is a genus of herbivorous arboreal mammal which belongs to the family Microcosmodontidae and which was endemic to North America during the Early Paleocene subepoch ( 66 - -56.8 mya ) and in existence for approximately 9.2 million years .
Allaiocerus metallicus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Allaiocerus .
The Kuatun horned toad or Kuatun spadefoot toad ( Xenophrys kuatunensis ) is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .

Clinostigma is a genus of flowering plant in the Arecaceae ( palm ) family , native to various islands in the western Pacific .
Apiomerus is a genus of conspicuous , brightly colored assassin bugs belonging to the family Reduviidae .
The Somalian slender mongoose ( Galerella ochracea ) is a mongoose endemic to Somalia .
Agonandra is a genus of plants in the family Opiliaceae described as a genus in 1862 .
Kluyveromyces is a genus of ascomycetous yeasts in the family Saccharomycetaceae .
Cintaroa aptera is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Cintaroa .
Anoplocephala is a genus of tapeworms in the family Anoplocephalidae named in 1848 by Blanchard .
Vittarioideae is a subfamily of the Pteridaceae family of ferns , in the order Polypodiales , class Polypodiopsida .
Geoffroy 's cat ( Leopardus geoffroyi ) is a wild cat native to the southern and central regions of South America .
Syntelia is a genus of middle - sized beetles , the only genus in the family Synteliidae .
Hypostrymon is a Nearctic and Neotropical genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae .
The Slender snake eel ( Scolecenchelys macroptera , also known as the Narrow worm eel ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Insulivitrina is genus of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Vitrinidae , the glass snails .
River stingrays or freshwater stingrays are Neotropical freshwater fishes of the Potamotrygonidae family in the order Myliobatiformes , one of the four orders of batoids , cartilaginous fishes related to sharks .
The Zanzibar barb ( Barbus zanzibaricus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Some modern taxonomic authorities do not recognize Leptonia as a genus in its own right , but only as a subgenus of Entoloma .
Cuphocarpus is an obsolete genus of flowering plants in the family Araliaceae .
Rebbachisaurinae is a subfamily within the family Rebbachisauridae , defined to include Rebbachisaurus garasbae and exclude Limaysaurus tessonei .
The Mograbin diadem snake ( Spalerosophis dolichospilus ) is a species of snake in the Colubridae family .
Kneria is a genus of small fish in the family Kneriidae .
Larocheopsis is a genus of small to minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Larocheidae .
Chanaresuchus was originally classified in the family Proterochampsidae , although it has been placed in the family Rhadinosuchidae in more recent studies ( both families belong to the larger group Proterochampsia ) .
Penguins ( order Sphenisciformes , family Spheniscidae ) are a group of aquatic , flightless birds living almost exclusively in the Southern Hemisphere , especially in Antarctica .
The genus Cathartes includes medium - sized to large carrion - feeding birds in the New World vulture ( Cathartidae ) family .
Geogenanthus is a genus of plants with 3 species in the family Commelinaceae ( the spiderwort and dayflower family ) .
Guatemalteca virgen is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae .
Viriclanis is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species , Viriclanis kingstoni , which is known from Tanzania .
The Mount Tucuche tree frog ( Flectonotus fitzgeraldi ) is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
The Wahai tree frog ( Litoria vagabunda ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , endemic to Indonesia .
The Hodgson 's redstart ( Phoenicurus hodgsoni ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Callionymus decoratus , the Decorated dragonet , is a species of dragonet endemic to the waters around the Hawaiian Islands where it occurs at depths of from 1 to 134 metres ( 3.3 to 439.6 ft ) .
The Saint Croix ground lizard ( Ameiva polops ) is a member of the Teiidae family of lizards .

Episcia is a genus of 10 species belonging to the flowering plant family Gesneriaceae .
Teak ( /tik/ ) ( Tectona grandis ) is a tropical hardwood species placed in the family Lamiaceae .
Desmarest 's spiny pocket mouse ( Heteromys desmarestianus ) is a species of rodent in the family Heteromyidae .
The Scioto pigtoe , scientific name Pleurobema bournianum , was a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
The Rota white - eye or Rota bridled white - eye ( Zosterops rotensis ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Holdridge 's toad ( Incilius holdridgei , formerly Bufo holdridgei ) is a species of toad endemic to Costa Rica .
The Kalakad gliding frog or Langbian flying frog ( Rhacophorus calcadensis ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to the southern Western Ghats in Kerala and Tamil Nadu states , India .
The Ethiopian wolf ( Canis simensis ) is a canid native to the Ethiopian Highlands .
The New Caledonian long - eared bat ( Nyctophilus nebulosus ) is a species of bat endemic to New Caledonia , but is only been recorded from Mount Koghis , near Nouméa .
The Charta tree frog , Hyloscirtus denticulentus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Colombia .
Schultz 's round - eared bat ( Lophostoma schulzi ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Zabidius novemaculeatus , the Ninespine Batfish or the Short - Finned Batfish , is a species of batfish native to coral reefs around Indonesia , Papua New Guinea and Australia at depths of from 10 to 40 metres ( 33 to 131 ft ) .
Highfin shiner ( Notropis altipinnis ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Notropis .
Xinjiangovenator was originally placed as Maniraptora incertae sedis and as possibly closely related to Bagaraatan .
Lybius is a genus of African barbets from the family Lybiidae ( formerly included in the Capitonidae and sometimes in the Ramphastidae ) .
Bannereus anomalus is a species of shrimp of the family Alpheidae , in the monotypic genus Bannerus .
Milla , the Mexican star , is a genus of monocotyledonous plants in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Brodiaeoideae .
Lygodactylus blanci , commonly called Blanc 's dwarf gecko , is a species of gecko native to central Madagascar .
Macheirocera grandis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Macheirocera of the family Ulidiidae .
The Chuuk flying fox or Ruck flying fox ( Pteropus insularis ) is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae .
The Kenyan big - eared free - tailed bat ( Tadarida lobata ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
Gomontiaceae is a family of green algae in the order Ulotrichales .
Schizobasis is a genus of bulbous flowering plants in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae ( also treated as the family Hyacinthaceae ) .
Allen 's woodrat ( Hodomys alleni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae found only in Mexico .
Kenodactylus audouini is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Kenodactylus .
The Bornean shrew ( Crocidura foetida ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The European eel ( Anguilla anguilla ) is a species of eel , a snake - like , catadromous fish .
Athoracophorus is a genus of air - breathing , land slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Athoracophoridae .
Virgularia is a genus of sea pen in the family Virgulariidae .
The Day 's round herring ( Dayella malabarica ) is a relative of the herring that is endemic to southwestern India .
The East Caucasian tur or Daghestan tur ( Capra caucasica cylindricornis ) is a mountain - dwelling caprine found only in the eastern half of the Greater Caucasus Mountains .
Catatrama is a fungal genus in the family Amanitaceae , order Agaricales .
Percolestus blackburni is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Percolestus .
Lissocampus bannwarthi ( Duncker , 1915 ) Lissocampus caudalis Waite & Hale , 1921 ( smooth pipefish ) Lissocampus fatiloquus ( Whitley , 1943 ) ( prophet 's pipefish ) Lissocampus filum ( Günther , 1870 ) ( shortsnout pipefish ) Lissocampus runa ( Whitley , 1931 ) ( javelin pipefish )
The Sardinian brook salamander or Sardinian mountain newt ( Euproctus platycephalus ) is a species of salamander in the Salamandridae family found only in Sardinia , Italy .
The smelt or European smelt ( Osmerus eperlanus ) is a species of fish in the Osmeridae family .
Mahathala is a small genus of hairstreak butterfly in the family Lycaenidae .
Olrog 's chaco mouse ( Andalgalomys olrogi ) is a species of South American rodent in the family Cricetidae , endemic to Argentina .
Stempfferia uniformis , the Ikoyi Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
The Hutan shrew ( Crocidura hutanis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Doridoxidae is the only family in the superfamily Doridoxoidea , within the clade Pseudoeuctenidiacea (= Doridoxida ) .
The Pelew flying fox ( Pteropus pelewensis ) is a species of megabat in the Pteropus genus found in the Pelew Islands .
Louisiana pancake batfish , Halieutichthys intermedius , belongs to the Ogcocephalidae family of batfish .
Batocerini is a tribe of longhorn beetles of the Lamiinae subfamily .
The Sulawesi naked - backed fruit bat ( Dobsonia exoleta ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
The African bullhead ( Lophiobagrus cyclurus ) is a species of claroteid catfish endemic to Lake Tanganyika at the border of Burundi , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Tanzania , and Zambia .
Alston 's brown mouse , also called Alston 's singing mouse , short - tailed singing mouse , or singing mouse ( Scotinomys teguina ) , is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Humboldtiana is a genus of American air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Humboldtianidae .
The name Atlas bear ( Ursus arctos crowtheri ) has been applied to an extinct population or populations of the brown bear in Africa .
Yersinella is a genus of ' katydids crickets ' belonging to the family Tettigoniidae subfamily Tettigoniinae .
The Shuicheng salamander ( Pseudohynobius shuichengensis ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to China .
Cornisepta is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Nikolaus 's mouse ( Megadendromus nikolausi ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Nuttalliella namaqua is a tick found in southern Africa from Tanzania to Namibia and South Africa , which is placed in its own family , Nuttalliellidae .
Nickimerus setosus is a species of beetle in the family Megalopodidae , the only species in the genus Nickimerus .
Leptopus , the maidenbushes , are a group of plants in the flowering plant family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1836 .
Chlaeniitae is a ground beetle supertribe in the subfamily Harpalinae .
Bornellidae is a family of sea snails or sea slugs , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Tritonioidea .
Golden loaches ( Sabanejewia ) is a genus of ray - finned fish in the Cobitidae family .
Iris ser . Longipetalae is a series of the genus Iris , in Iris subg . Limniris .
Plocamopherus is a genus of sea slugs , specifically nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod molluscs in the family Polyceridae , subfamily Triophinae .
The Javan rhinoceros ( Rhinoceros sondaicus ) , also known as the Sunda rhinoceros or lesser one - horned rhinoceros , is a very rare member of the family Rhinocerotidae and one of five extant rhinoceroses .
The Tien Shan shrew ( Sorex asper ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Trogloagonum novaehiberniae is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Trogloagonum .
Gomphoceras is a questionable nautiloid cephalopod genus assigned to the Oncocerida .
Ernogrammus is a genus of fish in the family Stichaeidae or pricklebacks .
The Himalayan field mouse ( Apodemus Gurkha ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Blunt - snouted dolphin ( Platalearostrum hoekmani , `` Albert Hoekman 's spoon - rostrum '' ) is a prehistoric pilot whale known from a single specimen ( NMR-9991 - 00005362 ) , consisting of a partial rostrum , partial maxilla , partial premaxilla , and partial vomer .
Cymbiola is a genus of large predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Pomatoschistus tortonesei , Tortonese 's goby , is a species of goby native to the Mediterranean Sea where it is known from Marsala , Sicily and the Farwah Lagoon in western Libya .
As of 2000 , the position of the Ictaluroidea within the Siluriformes order is not certain .
Gymnostena holosericea is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Gymnostena .
Cyclura rileyi nuchalis , commonly known as the Acklins ground iguana or Watling Island iguana , is an endangered subspecies of lizard of the genus Cyclura it is one of three subspecific forms of Cyclura rileyi in the family Iguanidae .
Aporosa is a genus of flowering plant belonging to the family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1825 .
Pergagrella monticola is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Dinocras is a genus of ' stoneflies ' belonging to the family Perlidae order Plecoptera , one of the oldest order of insects ( about 220 million of years ago ) .
Marchantiaceae is a family of liverworts in order Marchantiales .
The Bangwa forest warbler or Bangwa scrub warbler ( Bradypterus bangwaensis ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
Lamna is a genus of mackerel sharks in the family Lamnidae , containing two extant species : the porbeagle ( L. nasus ) of the North Atlantic and Southern Hemisphere , and the salmon shark ( L. ditropis ) of the North Pacific .
Breviraja ( Lightnose skates ) is a genus of fish in the Rajidae family .
The Peruvian spider monkey ( Ateles chamek ) also known as the Black - faced black spider monkey , is a species of spider monkey that lives not only in Peru , but also in Brazil and Bolivia .
Gall wasps , also called gallflies , are a family ( Cynipidae ) of the order Hymenoptera and are classified with the Apocrita suborder of wasps in the superfamily Cynipoidea .
Phrynobatrachus is a genus of Sub - Saharan frogs that form the monogeneric family Phrynobatrachidae .
Enneapterygius randalli , known commonly as the Rapa triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Heteroprox is an extinct genus of deer from the Miocene of Europe .

Tympanotonos is a genus of snail living in brackish water , a gastropod mollusk in the family Potamididae .
Agonops humerosa is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Agonops .
Potexvirus is a genus of pathogenic viruses in the order Tymovirales , in the family Alphaflexiviridae .
Bamboo mosaic virus ( BaMV ) is a plant pathogenic virus in the genus Potexvirus and the family Alphaflexiviridae .
The Barnes ' mastiff bat ( Molossus barnesi ) is a bat species endemic to French Guiana .
Cinachyrella is a large genus of marine sponges from Tetillidae family .
Praenuculinae is an extinct subfamily of prehistoric bivalves in the family Praenuculidae .
They define the Eryopoidea as all Euskelia in which the choana are relatively rounded and the iliac blade vertical .

The garden eels are the subfamily Heterocongrinae in the conger eel family Congridae .
The Boyacá spiny rat ( Proechimys chrysaeolus ) is a species of rodent in the family Echimyidae .
The Southern African anchovy ( Engraulis capensis ) is a species of anchovy which occurs in the southeast Atlantic Ocean near Namibia and South Africa .
Polietina is a genus within the Diptera family Muscidae .
The Minas Gerais tyrannulet ( Phylloscartes roquettei ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
False loose smut is a fungal disease of barley caused by Ustilago nigra .
The Guadeloupe woodpecker ( Melanerpes herminieri ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
Falsopseudomoxia tertia is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Falsopseudomoxia .
The Clear Lake splittail ( Pogonichthys ciscoides ) was endemic to California 's Clear Lake and its tributaries until its numbers severely declined due to competition from the introduced bluegill and alterations to the flow of inlet streams .
Monocyclanthus is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Annonaceae containing the single species Monocyclanthus vignei .
The Uzi fly ( Exorista sorbillans ) is a species of bristly fly in the family Tachinidae that is a parasitoid of caterpillars and is a problem for silkworm rearing in the tropical regions of South and Southeast Asia .
Mearns 's pouched mouse ( Saccostomus mearnsi ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Echiopsis is a genus of snake in the Elapidae family .
The Guayaquil woodpecker ( Campephilus gayaquilensis ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
Oligoaeschna is a genus of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
The Utah Lake sculpin , Cottus echinatus , was a species of freshwater sculpin endemic to Utah Lake , located in the north - central part of the U.S. state of Utah .
Collinia is a genus of parasitoid ciliate of the Colliniidae family .
Thaleropia is a genus of flowering plants in the family Myrtaceae first described as a genus in 1993 .
Iberanillus vinyasi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Iberanillus .
The genus Cryptolaemus consists of predatory beetles of the family Coccinellidae , whose larvae and adults mostly prey upon scale insects on ornamental plants .
The Japanese house bat or Japanese pipistrelle ( Pipistrellus abramus ) is a species of vesper bat .
Synchiropus ocellatus ( Ocellated dragonet or Scooter Dragonet ) is a species of tropical marine fish in the Dragonet ( Callionymidae ) family .
The Nitrosopumilaceae are a family of the Archaea order Nitrosopumilales .
Daphnandra is a genus of shrubs and trees in the family Atherospermataceae , or formerly Monimiaceae .
Pelodiscus is a genus of turtles in the family Trionychidae .
The Hottentot buttonquail ( Turnix hottentottus ) is a bird in the Turnicidae family formerly considered conspecific with the black - rumped buttonquail ( Turnix nanus ) .

Bistrialites is an involute , globose Clydonautilacean belonging to the Liroceratidae with a reniform whorl section , large funnel shaped umbilcus , smooth surface except for spiral ornament in the region of the umbilical shoulder .
The Garamba forest tree frog , Leptopelis oryi , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Uganda , and possibly Sudan .
Lycoseris is a genus of Latin American flowering plants in the Asteraceae family .
Stempfferia staudingeri , the Black - square Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .

Lepturdrys novemlineata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Lepturdrys .

Acanthobrama is a genus of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family found mostly in the Near East .
Asklepioceras is a genus in the Ceratitid family Arpaditidae from the Middle and Upper Triassic ( Ladinian and Carnian stages ) of Europe , Asia , and British Columbia .
The Caatinga antwren ( Herpsilochmus sellowi ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .

Blanford 's rock agama ( Psammophilus blanfordanus ) is an agamid lizard found in Peninsular India and is named after William Thomas Blanford ( 1832 - -1905 ) , member of the Geological Survey of India .
Velasquez 's woodpecker ( Melanerpes santacruzi ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family formerly considered conspecific with the golden - fronted woodpecker ( Melanerpes aurifrons ) .
The Barabuna tree frog ( Litoria contrastens ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
Stipa parishii , formerly classified as Achnatherum parishii , is a species of grass known by the common name Parish 's needlegrass .
The Puerto Rican amazon ( Amazona vittata ) , also known as the Puerto Rican parrot or iguaca , is the only bird endemic to the archipelago of Puerto Rico belonging to the Neotropical genus Amazona .

Raphicerus is a genus of small antelopes of the tribe Neotragini ( subfamily Antilopinae ) .
Parunxia scopifera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Parunxia .
The Rand 's warbler ( Randia pseudozosterops ) is a species in the Bernieridae family .
Bulwer 's pheasant ( Lophura bulweri ) is also known as Bulwer 's wattled pheasant , the wattled pheasant , or the white - tailed wattled pheasant .
Mindanao rasbora or Rasbora philippina is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Rasbora endemic to Mindanao .

The Persoonioideae are a subfamily of closely releted genera within the large and diverse Proteaceae family and incorporates such genera as Persoonia , Acidonia , Toronia and Placospermum .
Chetia is a genus of haplochromine cichlids endemic to riverine habitats in Africa .
Caudatoscelis is a genus of mantis in the family Amorphoscelididae .
Balizoma is a genus of trilobite from the family Encrinuridae .
Hepatitis B virus , abbreviated HBV , is a species of the genus Orthohepadnavirus , which is likewise a part of the Hepadnaviridae family of viruses .
Shepherdia , commonly called buffaloberries or bullberries , are a genus of small shrubs in the Elaeagnaceae Family .
Pholadidea is a taxonomic genus of marine bivalve molluscs in the family Pholadidae ( the piddocks ) .
Cedicoides is a genus of spiders in the Cybaeidae family made up of four species .
The Galápagos tortoise or Galápagos giant tortoise ( Chelonoidis nigra ) is the largest living species of tortoise .
Ludwigia lixoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Ludwigia .
Coloconger japonicus is an eel in the family Colocongridae ( worm eels / short - tail eels ) .
The Aulographaceae are a family of fungi with an uncertain taxonomic placement in the class Dothideomycetes .

Cassin 's sparrow ( Peucaea cassinii ) is a medium - sized sparrow .
Noritaceae is an extinct superfamily of cephalopods belonging to the Ammonite order Ceratitida .
†Pseudomelania is an extinct genus of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pseudomelaniidae .
The Caspian whipsnake ( Dolichophis caspius , sometimes also Coluber caspius ) also known as the large whipsnake ( among various other species in genus Dolichophis / Coluber ) , is a common species of whipsnake found in the Balkans and parts of Eastern Europe .
Van Heygen 's chameleon ( Kinyongia vanheygeni ) is a chameleon native to the Ngozi Crater in the Poroto Mountains of Tanzania .
Chloridea was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered to be a synonym of Heliothis .
The Chlamydiaceae are a family of bacteria that belongs to the phylum Chlamydiae , order Chlamydiales .
Heliotropium amplexicaule is a species of heliotrope known by several common names , including clasping heliotrope , blue heliotrope , and summer heliotrope .
The African chimaera ( Hydrolagus africanus ) is a species of fish in the Chimaeridae family found near Kenya , Mozambique , Namibia , and South Africa .
The Seram thrush ( Geokichla joiceyi ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
Kotshkorkia is an extinct genus of ants of the subfamily Dolichoderinae .

Macroglossus is a genus of megabats ( family Pteropodidae ) found in Indonesia and Southeast Asia .
The Mexican vole ( Microtus mexicanus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae found in Mexico and the United States .
The Orinoco lime tree frog , Sphaenorhynchus lacteus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Brazil , Colombia , Ecuador , French Guiana , Guyana , Peru , Suriname , Trinidad and Tobago , Venezuela , and possibly Bolivia .
Lottiidae is a family of sea snails , specifically true limpets , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Lottioidea and the clade Patellogastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Polyptychodon ( meaning ' shaped fin tooth ' ) is an extinct genus of sauropterygian reptile belonging to the family Pliosauridae that lived during the Cretaceous .
Gigantocamelus is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore the family Camelidae , endemic to North America from the Pliocene through Pleistocene 4.9 mya--300,000 years ago existing for approximately 4.68 million years .
Boeckops is a genus of trilobite in the order Phacopida , which existed in what is now the Czech Republic .
Trichopiezia stenotrachela is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Trichopiezia .
Jan Bol ( March 4 , 1924-February 11 , 2010 ) was a Dutch sailor who represented his country at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Acapulco .
Juho Halme ( Johan Valdemar Halme ; May 24 , 1888 in Helsinki -- February 1 , 1918 ) was a Finnish track and field athlete who competed in the 1908 Summer Olympics and in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Dimitrios Konstas is a Greek former water polo player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Dario Mangiarotti ( December 18 , 1915 -- April 9 , 2010 ) was an Italian fencer who competed at the 1948 and 1952 Summer Olympics and medaled in seven World Championships .
Noureddine Bouyahyaoui ( Arabic : نور الدين البويحياوي‎)(born 7 January 1955 ) is a Moroccan football defender who played for Morocco in the 1986 FIFA World Cup .
Jang Jong - hyun ( born 28 March 1984 ) is a South Korean field hockey player who competed in the 2004 , 2008 and in the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Thomas Richard Martin Bristow ( 15 November 1913 -- 31 July 2007 ) was a British doctor and rower who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics .
Hagar Badran ( Arabic : هاجر بدران ; born 20 May 1989 ) is an Egyptian synchronized swimmer who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Josef Německý ( December 6 , 1900 -- June 10 , 1943 ) was a Czechoslovakian cross country skier who competed in the 1924 Winter Olympics and in the 1928 Winter Olympics .
Wong Kam Kau ( born 13 September 1978 ) is a fencer from Hong Kong , China who won a bronze medal at the 2006 Asian Games in the men 's foil team competition .
An Innocent Man is the ninth studio album by American singer - songwriter Billy Joel , released on August 8 , 1983 .
Slow Dancing with the Moon is a Dolly Parton album released in February 1993 and , in addition to Parton , features a number of famous guest artists , including Collin Raye , Mary Chapin Carpenter , Kathy Mattea , Tanya Tucker , Maura O'Connell , Billy Dean , Pam Tillis , Marty Stuart and Billy Ray Cyrus .

Julian Sark is a recurring fictional character portrayed by David Anders on the ABC television series Alias .
More Experience is a posthumous live album by Jimi Hendrix released in March 1972 by Ember Records .
Trill OG is the third solo studio album by UGK member Bun B , and is the third album in his Trill series .

Fhtagn nagh Yog - Sothoth is the only demo album made by the funeral doom pioneers Thergothon .

Cuts Both Ways is American recording artist Gloria Estefan 's debut solo album , and final album with Miami Sound Machine , as they would simply become her backup band for her solo career after its release .
`` Only One Woman '' is a song and the first single by English duo The Marbles , written by Barry , Robin and Maurice Gibb of the Bee Gees .
Jardim Elétrico is the fourth album by the Brazilian Tropicália / psychedelic rock band Os Mutantes .

Pieter Langendijk ( Haarlem , 25 July 1683 -- Haarlem , 9 or 18 July 1756 ) was a damask weaver , city artist , dramatist , and poet .

Hans Frederick Blichfeldt ( 9 January 1873 in Illar , Denmark -- 16 November 1945 in Palo Alto , California ) was a Danish and American mathematician who worked on group theory and the geometry of numbers .

Goby Eberhardt ( Frankfurt , 29 March 1852 -- Lübeck , 13 September 1926 ) was a German violinist , teacher and composer .

Severino Di Giovanni ( Chieti , Italy , 17 March 1901 -- Buenos Aires , Argentina , 1 February 1931 ) , was an Italian anarchist who immigrated to Argentina , where he became the best - known anarchist figure in that country for his campaign of violence in support of Sacco and Vanzetti and antifascism .

He was furthermore employed on various diplomatic services after his mission to Rome in 1524 , on behalf of Gustav I of Sweden ( Vasa ) , to procure the appointment of Olaus Magnus ' brother , Johannes Magnus as archbishop of Uppsala .

He retired to the Villa Bianca ( now named `` Villa Grock '' ) , a 50-room house he had had built in the 1920s in Imperia , Italy , where he died in 1959 .

Alessandro Minuto - Rizzo ( born 10 September 1940 ) is an Italian diplomat who served as Deputy Secretary General of NATO from 2001 to 2007 , and as acting Secretary General of NATO from 17 December 2003 to 1 January 2004 , in between the tenures of George Robertson and Jaap de Hoop Scheffer .
Hans - Joachim Mann ( born 26 June 1935 ) is a retired German Vizeadmiral and former Inspector of the Navy from 1986 until 1991 .
Aristide Cavallari ( 8 February 1849 -- 24 November 1914 ) was a Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church who served as Patriarch of Venice .
Jaroslav Škarvada ( September 14 , 1924 in Královské Vinohrady -- June 14 , 2010 in Prague ) was the Roman Catholic titular bishop of Litomyšl and auxiliary bishop of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Prague , Czech Republic .
Abdullahi Bayero dan Muhammad Abbas ( 1881 - -1953 ) was Sarki ( Emir ) of Kano , with headquarters in Kano , Kano State , Nigeria from 1926 to 1953 .
Gösta Ingvar Carlsson ( born 9 November 1934 ) is a Swedish politician who twice served as Prime Minister of Sweden , first from 1986 to 1991 and again from 1994 to 1996 .
Psamtik I proved to be a great pharaoh by winning Egypt 's independence from the Assyrian Empire and restored Egypt 's prosperity through his long 54 Year reign .
Saint Exuperius of Bayeux ( Exupère ) , also known as Spirius ( Spire , Soupir , Soupierre ) , is venerated as the first bishop of Bayeux .
Amasis II ( Ancient Greek : Ἄμασις ) or Ahmose II was a pharaoh ( reigned 570 BCE -- 526 BCE ) of the Twenty - sixth dynasty of Egypt , the successor of Apries at Sais .
Agostino Valier ( 7 April 1531 -- 24 May 1606 ) , also Augustinus Valerius or Valerio , was an Italian cardinal and bishop of Verona .
Charles Curtis ( January 25 , 1860 -- February 8 , 1936 ) was an American attorney and politician , elected as the 31st Vice President of the United States ( 1929 - -33 ) with President Herbert Hoover .
Dismas Nsengiyaremye ( born 1945 ) served as Prime Minister of Rwanda from 2 April 1992 to 18 July 1993 .
Francisco Jiménez de Cisneros , O.F.M. ( 1436 -- November 8 , 1517 ) , known as Ximenes de Cisneros in his own lifetime , and commonly referred to today as simply Cisneros , was a Spanish cardinal , religious , and statesman .
Rafael Correa was officially declared President of Ecuador on 4 December 2006 by the country 's electoral court .
Soos ( Greek : Σόος ) was a partially mythological king of Sparta .
Mariano Crociata ( born 16 March 1953 ) has been bishop of the Diocese of Latina - Terracina - Sezze - Priverno since 19 November 2013 .
Eustache Antoine Francois Joseph Louis Borno ( September 20 , 1865 -- July 29 , 1942 ) was a lawyer and Haitian politician who served as President of Haiti from 1922 to 1930 during the period of the American occupation of Haiti ( 1915 - -34 ) .
The final God 's Father title is the one most associated with Ay , and was later incorporated into his royal name when he became pharaoh .
Plegmund ( or Plegemund ; died 2 August either 914 or 923 ) was a medieval English Archbishop of Canterbury .
Jean - Pierre Raffarin served as the Prime Minister of France from 6 May 2002 to 31 May 2005 , resigning after France 's rejection of the referendum on the European Union draft constitution .
Saint Leo of Catania , nicknamed the Thaumaturgus ( May 709 -- 20 February 789 ) was the fifteenth bishop of Catania , famed also for his love and care toward the poor .
Federico Gozi was Captain Regent of San Marino from October 1629 to March 1630 and again in 1634 from April to September .
André Plourde ( born 12 January 1937 in Rivière - du - Loup , Quebec ) was a Progressive Conservative member of the House of Commons of Canada .
William Crolly ( 8 June 1780 -- 8 April 1849 ) was the Roman Catholic Archbishop of Armagh from 1835 to 1849 .
William de Corbeil or William of Corbeil ( c. 1070 -- 1136 ) was a medieval Archbishop of Canterbury .
Vice Admiral Didier Ratsiraka ( born 4 November 1936 ) is a Malagasy politician who was President of Madagascar from 1975 to 1993 and from 1997 to 2002 .
Robert of Torigni ( also known as Roburtus de Monte ) ( c.1110 - -1186 ) was a Norman monk , prior , abbot and an important twelfth century chronicler .
Giovanni Cheli ( 4 October 1918 -- 8 February 2013 ) was a cardinal of the Catholic Church and was , along with Achille Silvestrini and Pio Laghi , one of the most prominent Vatican diplomats under Pope John Paul II .
John Selwyn Brooke Lloyd , Baron Selwyn - Lloyd CH CBE TD PC ( 28 July 1904 -- 18 May 1978 ) , known for most of his career as Selwyn Lloyd , was a British Conservative Party politician who served as Foreign Secretary from 1955 to 1960 , then as Chancellor of the Exchequer until 1962 .
Ross Bass ( March 17 , 1918 -- January 1 , 1993 ) was an American florist , postmaster , Congressman and United States Senator from Tennessee .
The identity of Narmer is the subject of ongoing debate , although mainstream Egyptological consensus identifies Narmer with the First Dynasty pharaoh Menes , who is also credited with the unification of Egypt , as the first pharaoh .
Eugene Hale ( June 9 , 1836 -- October 27 , 1918 ) was a Republican United States Senator from Maine .
Kevin Witkos is a Republican member of the Connecticut Senate , representing the 8th District since 2009 and serving as Minority Leader Pro Tempore since 2015 and Caucus Chairman for Outreach since 2013 .
Jean Hermil ( September 24 , 1917 , Charolles -- March 10 , 2006 , Viviers ) was Roman Catholic bishop of Viviers , France .
Henry Clay Sevier , Sr . , known as Happy Sevier ( January 24 , 1896 -- June 1 , 1974 ) , was a lawyer from Tallulah , Louisiana , who was from 1936 to 1952 a Democratic member of the Louisiana House of Representatives from Madison Parish .
Richard le Grant ( also known as Richard Grant or Richard Wethershed ) was Archbishop of Canterbury from 1229 to 1231 .
